Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.99,0:00:38.99,中英,,0,0,0,,好长的告示\NHow long De Gao Shi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.50,0:01:01.20,大3,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1000,0)\pos(646,720)\c&HFFFFFF&}{\c&HFFEE1A&\1a&H00&}欧洲
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.98,0:01:06.98,中英,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&}字幕制作 SlimChen\N\N字幕翻译 SlimChen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.98,0:01:11.27,中英,,0,0,0,,- 这部电影在欧洲发行之前\N- The poster that came out in Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.28,0:01:18.16,中英,,0,0,0,,它的海报已张贴在英国乃至全欧的街头\Nat least in England,I believe, before the movie was released\Nin Europe said,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.16,0:01:22.33,中英,,0,0,0,,上面写道:一波横扫美国的惧浪\N"The wave of terror that swept across America."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.33,0:01:25.50,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克恰到好处的掌控了观众的心理\NAnd Kubrick controlled the posters very carefully.{\s0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.50,0:01:28.67,中英,,0,0,0,,当你再观察一眼 便会觉得恍然大悟\NNow,it made you do a double take.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.67,0:01:30.08,中英,,0,0,0,,我记得在欧洲看到这张海报时\NI remember seeing it in Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.09,0:01:31.63,中英,,0,0,0,,我还是美国广播新闻台驻罗马分社的社长\NI was the Rome Bureau Chief at the time for ABC News.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.63,0:01:33.00,中英,,0,0,0,,我仍记得当时的情景\NAnd I remember looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.01,0:01:34.51,中英,,0,0,0,,上面写着：一波横扫美国的惧浪\NIt said, The wave of terror that swept across America.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.51,0:01:36.51,中英,,0,0,0,,他在说什么？\NWhat's he talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.51,0:01:41.26,中英,,0,0,0,,接着你会意识到...\NAnd you'd sort of think that he was talking about...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.26,0:01:43.36,中英,,0,0,0,,他说的是 小说《闪灵》所带来的冲击\Nthe impact of the book The Shining.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.36,0:01:44.60,中英,,0,0,0,,也许是\NMaybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.60,0:01:47.32,中英,,0,0,0,,而电影对社会的影响就像刚才说的那样吗？\NThe impact of the movie that had just opened over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.32,0:01:48.31,中英,,0,0,0,,也许是\NMaybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.31,0:01:49.85,中英,,0,0,0,,但并不准确\NIt didn't quite fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.86,0:01:51.65,中英,,0,0,0,,那股席卷全美的恐怖之潮\NThe wave of terror that swept across America
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.65,0:01:53.90,中英,,0,0,0,,从缅甸州的波特兰 刮到 俄勒冈州的波特兰*\Nfrom Portland, Maine,to Portland, Oregon,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.65,0:01:53.90,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(641,18)}*美国有两座名为 波特兰 的城市
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.90,0:01:56.70,中英,,0,0,0,,它是由种族屠杀引起的 那是 白人高举斧头\Nwas the genocidal armies and the white men with their ax
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.70,0:02:02.28,中英,,0,0,0,,清除了一切 并引入了采掘工业以及其它的技术\N clearing it all and bringing in extractive industries, among many other good things as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.28,0:02:04.54,中英,,0,0,0,,但那可是席卷全美的恐惧之潮\NBut that was the wave of terror that swept across America,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.54,0:02:08.21,中英,,0,0,0,,当然也吓坏了美国印第安人\Nterrifying, of course, the American Indians.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.20,0:02:28.14,大,,0,0,0,,{\fad(3000,0)\pos(658,562)}{\pos(900.000000,1005.000000)\\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&}237号房间
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.95,0:02:28.12,中英,,0,0,0,,{\fad(3000,0)\pos(658,608)}{\pos(915.000000,1005.000000)\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&}《闪灵》九调查
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.33,0:02:31.08,大,,0,0,0,,{\pos(634,616)}采访
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.23,0:02:34.28,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我在莱斯特广场影院看了这部电影\N- I went in to see this movie in Leicester Square Movie Theater,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.28,0:02:36.61,中英,,0,0,0,,就在伦敦莱斯特广场旁边\Nright near Leicester Square in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.62,0:02:38.45,中英,,0,0,0,,对当时 我记忆犹新...\NAnd I remember it quite clearly from...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.45,0:02:40.49,中英,,0,0,0,,我甚至记得当时的座位\NI can even remember the seats we were sitting in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.49,0:02:42.87,中英,,0,0,0,,现在要是能回到那个电影院 我可以指出来给你看\NIf I went back to that theater,I could point them to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.87,0:02:47.50,中英,,0,0,0,,是在后排靠左的位置\Nsort of near the back and over to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.50,0:02:53.25,中英,,0,0,0,,电影开场时 直升机令人毛骨悚然的噪音就吓到我了\NFrom the moment of the opening astonishing helicopter shot, I was terrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.25,0:02:54.88,中英,,0,0,0,,我不知道什么会到来\NI had no idea what was coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.88,0:02:56.72,中英,,0,0,0,,我还记得 坐在椅子前端\NI remember sort of sitting on the front edge
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.72,0:03:01.26,中英,,0,0,0,,以防自己摔倒\Nof my theater seat there to keep from falling off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.26,0:03:05.14,中英,,0,0,0,,我还用左手握住我的皮带扣\NAnd I remember gripping my belt buckle with my left hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.14,0:03:09.44,中英,,0,0,0,,应该是...对 是我的左手 防止自己从椅子上吓摔倒\NI think it was... yes, my left hand,sort of to keep from falling off
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.44,0:03:15.73,中英,,0,0,0,,并控制住我看电影时的恐惧\Nthe edge of the seat and to try to control my terror as I watched this movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.74,0:03:17.11,中英,,0,0,0,,我真的不知道会发生什么\NI had no idea what was coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.11,0:03:18.32,中英,,0,0,0,,我还没读过原作\NI hadn't read the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.32,0:03:20.74,中英,,0,0,0,,也没怎么看到过海报\NI had barely seen any of the posters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.74,0:03:25.87,中英,,0,0,0,,我记得电影放完后 我震惊了\NAnd I remember that I was stunned when the movie was over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.87,0:03:34.00,中英,,0,0,0,,我们离开电影院 到停车场 、开车回去\NWe left the theater, went in... down into our underground car park to get into the car to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.00,0:03:36.80,中英,,0,0,0,,当我们开出地下车库时\NAnd as we were driving up out of the car park,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.80,0:03:39.46,中英,,0,0,0,,我坐在左边的后座上\NI was sitting in the back left seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.46,0:03:41.55,中英,,0,0,0,,我在回想 那是什么？到底是什么？\NI was thinking, "What was that? What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.55,0:03:43.59,中英,,0,0,0,,是什么东西？是鬼吗？是不是鬼？\N"What was it? What was it? What was it?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.59,0:03:47.43,中英,,0,0,0,,我记得当哈洛伦和丹尼交谈时\NAnd I think my visual imagination
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.43,0:03:49.10,中英,,0,0,0,,我的目光停留在那个卡路美特牌发酵粉罐子上\Nlooked at that Calumet baking powder can,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.11,0:03:52.89,中英,,0,0,0,,哈洛伦脑袋右后方的那个\Nthe one right behind Hallorann's head when he was talking to Danny.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.89,0:03:54.19,中英,,0,0,0,,我清楚"卡路美特"的含义\NI knew what "calumet" meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.19,0:04:01.15,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(652,18)}*是北美印第安人用来表示和睦的烟斗
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.19,0:03:56.69,中英,,0,0,0,,是 和睦烟斗*\NIt meant "peace pipe."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.69,0:04:01.15,中英,,0,0,0,,接着我想:和睦烟斗 印第安人\NAnd I thought to myself, "peace pipe, Indians.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.15,0:04:02.45,中英,,0,0,0,,我的天哪\N"Oh, my goodness,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.45,0:04:04.49,中英,,0,0,0,,他们在影片中随处可见\Nthey're all over the place in that movie."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.20,0:04:13.92,中英,,0,0,0,,- 输的人要做家务\N- The loser has to keep America clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.09,0:04:21.63,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我马上和朋友说:\N- And I suddenly said to my friends：
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.63,0:04:24.56,中英,,0,0,0,,"这个电影是关于印第安人种族屠杀的"\N"That movie was about the genocide of the American Indians."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.56,0:04:26.72,中英,,0,0,0,,他们说:"你在说什么？"\NAnd they said: "What are you talking about?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.72,0:04:28.06,中英,,0,0,0,,接着我开始解释\NAnd I started explaining it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.06,0:04:30.81,中英,,0,0,0,,因为我注意到了那个卡路美特牌发酵粉罐子\Nbecause I'd noticed the Calumet baking soda can.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.81,0:04:32.86,中英,,0,0,0,,我们第一次见到这种罐子\NIn the first... the first time we seen one,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.86,0:04:36.10,中英,,0,0,0,,那是一个站立着的罐子\Nit's a single baking powder can straight on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.10,0:04:37.98,中英,,0,0,0,,你能够清楚的看到整个词语 "卡路美特"\NAnd you can see the whole word, "Calumet,"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.98,0:04:40.19,中英,,0,0,0,,所以这是毋庸置疑的\Nso there's no duplicity,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.19,0:04:41.91,中英,,0,0,0,,就像那对双胞胎女孩所代表的\Nlike the little girls represent later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.91,0:04:43.82,中英,,0,0,0,,这是个可靠的事实\NThis is an honest truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.82,0:04:45.91,中英,,0,0,0,,一个夹在他们之间的和睦烟斗\Nan honest peace pipe between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.91,0:04:47.62,中英,,0,0,0,,我们另一次看到发酵粉罐子\NThe other time we see the Calumet baking powder cans
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.63,0:04:49.87,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(611,18)}《闪灵》男主角扮演者\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.63,0:04:49.87,中英,,0,0,0,,是在杰克·尼克尔森*和格雷迪对话时\Nis when they're very carefully placed
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.87,0:04:53.67,中英,,0,0,0,,它们在尼克尔森脑袋后面\Nbehind Jack Nicholson's head when he's talking to Grady.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.38,0:05:00.63,中英,,0,0,0,,- 别戳我软肋了 格雷迪先生\N- No need to rub it in,Mr. Grady.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.26,0:05:06.05,中英,,0,0,0,,我一出去就会解决那个问题\NI'll deal with that situation as soon as I get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.05,0:05:08.80,中英,,0,0,0,,- 那里大概有六七个罐头叠在那儿\N- There's about six or seven of them stacked up,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.80,0:05:10.39,中英,,0,0,0,,同时朝着不同的方向\Nand they're all turned different ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.39,0:05:12.56,中英,,0,0,0,,所以你不能只凭其中一个解读出来\Nand you can't read any one of them completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:18.06,中英,,0,0,0,,我一直将此理解为破碎和欺骗的和睦烟斗\NIt's... I've always interpreted those as being broken, dishonest peace pipe treaties.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.06,0:05:21.07,中英,,0,0,0,,格雷迪和杰克他们俩\NThey're not... these two guys,Grady and Jack,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.07,0:05:24.15,中英,,0,0,0,,他们对彼此并不真诚\Nare not being honest with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.15,0:05:26.90,中英,,0,0,0,,格雷迪想借杰克之手杀了他全家\NGrady is trying to get Jack to go kill his family
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.91,0:05:28.24,中英,,0,0,0,,施行种族灭绝的犯罪\Nand commit genocide,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.25,0:05:29.74,中英,,0,0,0,,这部电影 从更广义的角度上来说\Nin the larger sense of the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.74,0:05:32.03,中英,,0,0,0,,我是说 库布里克\NYou know, I mean, Kubrick often,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.04,0:05:37.04,中英,,0,0,0,,在他的很多作品中 常以谜题结局\Nin many of his movies, he will end them with a puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.04,0:05:39.76,中英,,0,0,0,,因此当你走出影院 他总会让你说:\Nso that he forces you to go out of the theater saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.76,0:05:41.63,中英,,0,0,0,,"电影到底在说什么？"\N"What was that about?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.63,0:05:44.71,中英,,0,0,0,,同时 他还会在道具布景中\NAnd he would put things in the scenes
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.71,0:05:46.26,中英,,0,0,0,,使用一些证人道具\Nthat he knows will be,among other things,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.26,0:05:51.10,中英,,0,0,0,,作为人们解读电影主题时的关键\Nlike confirmers when people start to try to figure out what the movie is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.10,0:05:53.89,中英,,0,0,0,,我们知道 他很在意细节\NAnd we know he took this kind of care.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.89,0:05:55.89,中英,,0,0,0,,有一本书里的照片\NThere's a photograph in one of the books
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.89,0:05:57.52,中英,,0,0,0,,真实展现了库布里克\Nthat actually shows Kubrick
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.52,0:06:01.86,中英,,0,0,0,,对储藏室里货架的细致布局\Ncarefully arranging objects on the shelves in that dry goods room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.86,0:06:03.48,中英,,0,0,0,,后来 我苦思冥想\NI thought afterwards,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.48,0:06:06.61,中英,,0,0,0,,"为什么我可以看到其他人看不到的东西？"\N"How come I saw this and a lot of other people didn't?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.61,0:06:08.40,中英,,0,0,0,,我意识到了\NAnd I've thought about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.41,0:06:09.74,中英,,0,0,0,,原因是多方面的\NIt's a combination of factors.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.75,0:06:12.58,中英,,0,0,0,,首先 我在芝加哥长大\NFirst, I grew up in Chicago and, therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.58,0:06:14.95,中英,,0,0,0,,就在卡路美特海港北部\Njust north of the Calumet Harbor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.95,0:06:19.42,中英,,0,0,0,,因此在夏天 我能够在墨西哥湖边\Nand spent summers up in the sand dunes of Michigan,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.42,0:06:21.13,中英,,0,0,0,,和沙子一起愉快玩耍\Naround on the other side of Lake Michigan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.14,0:06:23.30,中英,,0,0,0,,父亲会带着我和妹妹（姐姐）\NMy father took me and my sister out
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.30,0:06:25.88,中英,,0,0,0,,收集印第安陶器碎片\Nto collect little bits of Indian pottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.88,0:06:31.80,中英,,0,0,0,,在1980年 黎巴嫩五年内战时期\NI'd already...I'd already covered, at that point in 1980, five years of the Lebanese civil war.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.80,0:06:34.18,中英,,0,0,0,,我作为社长 采访了\NI was, at that point, covering John Paul ll.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.18,0:06:35.68,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(686,18)}*罗马天主教第264任教宗
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.18,0:06:35.68,中英,,0,0,0,,若望·保禄二世*\NI was the Rome Bureau Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.68,0:06:38.60,中英,,0,0,0,,我还记得他的讲话...\NAnd listening to what he was saying about...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.61,0:06:41.23,中英,,0,0,0,,他亲身经历过大屠杀\Nbecause he had experienced the Holocaust at its epicenter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.23,0:06:43.36,中英,,0,0,0,,以及其他动乱\Nand also other horrors.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.36,0:06:46.40,中英,,0,0,0,,因此当我在看《闪灵》时\NAnd so all of those factors
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.40,0:06:50.32,中英,,0,0,0,,这些因素在我脑海中闪现出来\Nwere very much alive in my mind when we went to see The Shining,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.32,0:06:52.70,中英,,0,0,0,,而我还以为 它不过是库大神制作的\Nwhich I just thought was going to be some kind of horror movie
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.70,0:06:53.70,中英,,0,0,0,,一部简单的恐怖电影\Nby this great moviemaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.70,0:06:58.62,中英,,0,0,0,,而当这些因素蜂拥而至时 \NAnd all of those coming together along with the little key,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.62,0:07:01.50,中英,,0,0,0,,那个卡路美特罐子\Nthe Calumet baking soda can,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.50,0:07:08.96,中英,,0,0,0,,就成了我们在回去的车内争论时\Nis why I just happened to tune to it as we were driving up out of that underground parking garage
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.97,0:07:10.18,中英,,0,0,0,,解开这道谜题的钥匙\Njust off Leicester Square.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.18,0:07:16.73,中英,,0,0,0,,- 1980年 电影刚上映我就去看了\N- I first saw the movie in 1980 when it first came out
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.73,0:07:19.60,中英,,0,0,0,,应该是看了两次\Nand saw it probably two times.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.60,0:07:21.77,中英,,0,0,0,,我记得那张滑雪者的海报\NI can say that I remembered the skier poster.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.77,0:07:24.19,中英,,0,0,0,,那个让我百思不得其解的东西\NThat is one thing that really stuck with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.19,0:07:26.02,中英,,0,0,0,,还有窗户\NAnd the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.02,0:07:27.36,中英,,0,0,0,,那扇办公室里的窗户\NThe window in the office,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.36,0:07:29.53,中英,,0,0,0,,又一个让我极度抓狂的设定\Nthat's another thing that really stuck with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.78,0:07:34.58,中英,,0,0,0,,我记得 报纸上写出 人们看过后\NI remember, you know, in the newspapers afterwards,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.58,0:07:35.74,中英,,0,0,0,,对电影很失望\Npeople being disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.75,0:07:37.49,中英,,0,0,0,,我还记得\NAnd I remember people that I knew,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.49,0:07:39.09,中英,,0,0,0,,在和认识的人交谈后\Nyes, in dialogue afterwards,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.09,0:07:42.92,中英,,0,0,0,,他们很失望 觉得电影不够恐怖 \Nbeing disappointed that it was not more a horror film.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.92,0:07:47.25,中英,,0,0,0,,但是 库导出品 必属精品\NWell, no Kubrick film's really just a regular movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.25,0:07:49.09,中英,,0,0,0,,对于对句话的理解\NI understood that from,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.09,0:07:51.89,中英,,0,0,0,,是我在十岁时 第一次看《2001：太空漫游》\Nwell, when I was 10 years old and I first saw 2001.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.89,0:07:52.88,中英,,0,0,0,,我离场了\NI walked away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.88,0:07:54.43,中英,,0,0,0,,我心里想:\NI thought, This is a film
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.43,0:07:56.48,中英,,0,0,0,,这是一部会让我思考的电影\Nthat's supposed to make me think.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.77,0:08:02.23,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我第一次感到虔诚\N- I had my first religious experience
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.23,0:08:07.77,中英,,0,0,0,,是在1968年看《2001：太空漫游》的时候\Nseeing the film 2001: A Space Odyssey in 1968.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.77,0:08:14.24,中英,,0,0,0,,我是个热爱艺术的小神童\NI was a smart kid and liked art,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.24,0:08:16.57,中英,,0,0,0,,可我一点也不喜欢看电影\Nbut I really did not like movies
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.57,0:08:20.24,中英,,0,0,0,,觉得电影不是真正的艺术\Nand thought that they were really a substandard art.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.25,0:08:21.75,中英,,0,0,0,,你知道 那时的电影\NAnd, you know, films like
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.75,0:08:24.79,中英,,0,0,0,,都是《窈窕淑女》《怪医杜立德》之类的烂片\NMy Fair Lady and Doctor Dolittle were out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.79,0:08:29.92,中英,,0,0,0,,60年代是电影艺术的惨淡期\NAnd it was a rather pathetic time in the '60s for films.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.92,0:08:32.42,中英,,0,0,0,,我的女朋友先提到了这部影片\NAnd my girlfriend, she pulled up
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.42,0:08:36.09,中英,,0,0,0,,她跟我说 昨晚她看了部电影\Nand told me that she'd seen a movie the night before
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.09,0:08:38.10,中英,,0,0,0,,想再看一遍\Nand she wanted to see it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.10,0:08:42.47,中英,,0,0,0,,然后她带着我去电影院去看了\NSo she took me to the theater,the Cinerama Dome,and I watched it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.48,0:08:46.81,中英,,0,0,0,,我这辈子都没想到过\NAnd I had never in my life envisioned that a movie
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.81,0:08:49.27,中英,,0,0,0,,一部电影可以做成这样\Ncould do what this movie was doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.27,0:08:52.12,中英,,0,0,0,,效果上 它让我大开眼界\NAnd it was showing me things that I had never seen,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.12,0:08:54.78,中英,,0,0,0,,内容上 也很考验观众的思维能力\Nand it was intellectually challenging.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.78,0:08:59.62,中英,,0,0,0,,从各个方面来看 这都是一部艺术巨作\NAnd it was an artistic masterpiece in every way,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.62,0:09:04.12,中英,,0,0,0,,从声效 到视觉 到情节\Nfrom the soundtrack to the visuals to the story line.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.12,0:09:07.05,中英,,0,0,0,,当影片结束时 我甚至不能站起来\NAnd when the movie ended,I couldn't get out of my seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.05,0:09:09.46,中英,,0,0,0,,我震惊了\NI was frozen in the seat,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.46,0:09:13.09,中英,,0,0,0,,完全被自己看到的东西麻痹了\Ncompletely paralyzed by what I'd just witnessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.09,0:09:16.72,中英,,0,0,0,,最后是引座员把我带了出去\NAnd the usher actually had to come and get me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.72,0:09:19.43,中英,,0,0,0,,厅内只有我和女友两个人\NAnd I was the last person,me and her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.43,0:09:21.85,中英,,0,0,0,,我百感交集的走出了电影院\NAnd I staggered out of the theater
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.85,0:09:24.56,中英,,0,0,0,,成了一个更完整的人类\Ncompletely changed as a human being
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.56,0:09:25.81,中英,,0,0,0,,在那时 我决定\Nand decided at that moment
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.81,0:09:29.48,中英,,0,0,0,,我余生最想做的事\Nthat the only thing that I wanted to do for the rest of my life
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.48,0:09:32.98,中英,,0,0,0,,就是去拍出类似这样的电影\Nwas to make films in one fashion or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.98,0:09:35.11,中英,,0,0,0,,而我已经做到了\NAnd so I have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.11,0:09:40.03,中英,,0,0,0,,因此我要感谢库布里克和他的《2001：太空漫游》\NSo I owe Stanley Kubrick and his film 2001: A Space Odyssey
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.03,0:09:44.70,中英,,0,0,0,,感谢他让这一切成为我的生活\Neverything for everything that I have become in my life, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.01,0:10:03.86,中英,,0,0,0,,- 在研究库布里克的电影之前\N- I saw a number of Kubrick films
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.86,0:10:06.98,中英,,0,0,0,,我就看了他的许多作品\Nbefore I had an academic interest in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.98,0:10:11.52,中英,,0,0,0,,1980年 我去看了《闪灵》\NAnd then I went to see The Shining in 1980.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.52,0:10:14.36,中英,,0,0,0,,坦白的说 我当时觉得它不怎么样\NAnd frankly,I didn't think that much of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.36,0:10:16.86,中英,,0,0,0,,我看过他的其它作品\NI thought the other Kubrick films that I'd seen
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.86,0:10:19.86,中英,,0,0,0,,都比这部优秀很多\Nwere far superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.86,0:10:24.58,中英,,0,0,0,,后来 我回想 这部电影...\NBut as I thought about the film afterwards...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.58,0:10:26.75,中英,,0,0,0,,就算我没有刻意的去想它...\Nand even when I wasn't thinking about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.75,0:10:29.00,中英,,0,0,0,,仍有一些东西在扰乱我的思路\Nthere were things that bothered me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.00,0:10:32.21,中英,,0,0,0,,好像我忽略了什么\NIt seemed as if I had missed something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.21,0:10:35.38,中英,,0,0,0,,所以我又回影院二刷\NAnd so I went back to see it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.38,0:10:42.05,中英,,0,0,0,,我开始注意到一些之前忽略了的细节\NAnd I began to see atterns and details that I hadn't noticed before
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.05,0:10:46.39,中英,,0,0,0,,于是我一遍又一遍的看\NAnd so I kept watching the film again and again and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.39,0:10:49.35,中英,,0,0,0,,我是一名历史学家\NAnd since I'm trained as an historian
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.35,0:10:51.81,中英,,0,0,0,,我主要研究\Nand my special expertise
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.81,0:10:56.69,中英,,0,0,0,,德国与纳粹德国的的历史\Nis in the history of Germany and Nazi Germany in particular,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.69,0:10:58.29,中英,,0,0,0,,因此我越来越相信\NI became more and more convinced
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.29,0:11:02.07,中英,,0,0,0,,在这部电影中\Nthat there is,in this film,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.07,0:11:06.04,中英,,0,0,0,,对纳粹大屠杀 有着隐蔽的暗示\Na deeply laid subtext that takes on The Holocaust.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.91,0:11:12.83,中英,,0,0,0,,我觉得那台打字机\NI think it probably was the typewriter,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.83,0:11:16.92,中英,,0,0,0,,那台德国牌的打字机 看上去也许是随便找来的\Nwhich was a German brand,which might seem arbitrary,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.92,0:11:20.38,中英,,0,0,0,,但在那时 我已经很了解库布里克\Nbut by that time,I knew enough about Kubrick
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.38,0:11:26.10,中英,,0,0,0,,我知道他的影片中 几乎没有什么是随便的\Nthat most anything in his films can't be regarded as arbitrary,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.10,0:11:29.14,中英,,0,0,0,,尤其是道具和颜色的使用\Nthat anything...especially objects and colors
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.15,0:11:36.11,中英,,0,0,0,,以及音乐和其他方面 或多或少都是故意的\Nand music and anything else,probably have some intentional as well as unintentional meaning to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.11,0:11:37.32,中英,,0,0,0,,这让我很费解\NAnd so that struck me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.33,0:11:39.07,中英,,0,0,0,,为什么是一台德国牌打字机？\NWhy a German typewriter?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.07,0:11:41.15,中英,,0,0,0,,由此\NAnd in connection with that,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.15,0:11:47.03,中英,,0,0,0,,我在电影中发现了数字 42\NI began to see the number 42 appear in the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.04,0:11:50.83,中英,,0,0,0,,而在德国历史中 你将数字 42\NAnd for a German historian,if you put the number 42
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.83,0:11:53.08,中英,,0,0,0,,和一台德国打字机放在一起\Nand a German typewriter together,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.08,0:11:54.46,中英,,0,0,0,,你得到的是纳粹大屠杀\Nyou get the Holocaust,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.46,0:11:59.88,中英,,0,0,0,,因为德国在1942年\Nbecause it was in 1942 that the Nazis made the decision
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.88,0:12:03.51,中英,,0,0,0,,通过了消灭犹太人的决议\Nto go ahead and exterminate all the Jews they could.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.51,0:12:09.72,中英,,0,0,0,,独裁的他们就像杀人机器一样进行屠杀\NAnd they did so in a highly mechanical, industrial, and bureaucratic way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.72,0:12:13.64,中英,,0,0,0,,所以我深深地意识到\NAnd so the juxtaposition of the number 42
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.65,0:12:16.57,中英,,0,0,0,,数字42和打字机的并列使用\Nand the typewriter was really where it started for me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.57,0:12:19.98,中英,,0,0,0,,是为了在电影中表达历史事实\Nin terms of the historical content of the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.98,0:12:22.49,中英,,0,0,0,,当然 "阿德勒"在德文中的意思是"鹰"的意思\NOf course "adler"in German means "eagle."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.49,0:12:24.99,中英,,0,0,0,,而老鹰是纳粹德国的象征\NAnd eagle, of course,is a symbol of Nazi Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.99,0:12:27.29,中英,,0,0,0,,也是美国的象征\NIt's also a symbol of the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.29,0:12:29.50,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克通常会用老鹰\NAnd Kubrick generally has recourse to eagles
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.50,0:12:31.29,中英,,0,0,0,,来象征国权\Nto symbolize state power.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.83,0:12:42.53,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(627,18)}*澳裔政治学家 历史学家
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.83,0:12:40.21,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克读过劳尔·希尔伯格*的论作\NKubrick read Raul Hilberg's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.21,0:12:42.55,中英,,0,0,0,,《欧洲犹太人的灭绝》\NThe Destruction of the European Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.55,0:12:44.89,中英,,0,0,0,,而希尔伯格书中的主题\NAnd Hilberg's major theme in there
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.89,0:12:49.55,中英,,0,0,0,,就是关于杀人武器的\Nis that he focuses on the apparatus of killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.56,0:12:52.15,中英,,0,0,0,,他还特别强调纳粹的独裁性\NAnd he emphasizes how bureaucratic it was
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.15,0:12:56.19,中英,,0,0,0,,并解释了名单和打字机的的含义\Nand how it was a matter of lists and typewriters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.19,0:12:58.81,中英,,0,0,0,,斯皮尔伯格在《辛德勒的名单》中采用了这一指代\NSpielberg picked that up in Schindler's List, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.82,0:13:02.57,中英,,0,0,0,,我是说 电影开场就出现了打字机和名单\NI mean, the film begins with typewriters and lists
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.57,0:13:04.70,中英,,0,0,0,,并以名单结束\Nand ends with a list,of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.70,0:13:07.11,中英,,0,0,0,,电影就是这样传达它的主题的\NAnd so that informs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.12,0:13:09.83,中英,,0,0,0,,我曾在劳尔·希尔伯格访问阿尔比恩学院时\Nand I had a chance to talk to Raul Hilberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.83,0:13:11.17,中英,,0,0,0,,和他交谈过\NHe visited Albion College.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.17,0:13:13.54,中英,,0,0,0,,他说自己和库布里克在这一点上有着共识\NAnd he said that he and Kubrick corresponded about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.54,0:13:16.67,中英,,0,0,0,,他之后知道了另一个事实\NAnd the fact that he read it then, in the 1970s,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.67,0:13:19.04,中英,,0,0,0,,十九世纪七十年代 掀起了一阵\Nwhen there was a big wave of interest in Hitler
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.05,0:13:22.34,中英,,0,0,0,,研究希特勒 大屠杀以及纳粹的浪潮\Nand the Holocaust and the Nazis,I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.34,0:13:25.38,中英,,0,0,0,,我觉得这说明 那台打字机\NI think just tells us that that typewriter,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.38,0:13:27.01,中英,,0,0,0,,那台德国牌打字机\Nthat German typewriter...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.01,0:13:30.14,中英,,0,0,0,,在指出一个异常重要的历史事件的同时\Nwhich by the way, changes color in the course of the film,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.14,0:13:32.73,中英,,0,0,0,,也改变了这部电影的基调\Nwhich typewriters don't generally do...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.73,0:13:34.85,中英,,0,0,0,,这发挥出了\Nis terribly,terribly important
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.85,0:13:37.70,中英,,0,0,0,,打字机不一般的作用\Nas a referent to that particular historical event.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.58,0:13:54.12,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我曾在电影资料馆工作了十年\N- I worked in a film archive for a decade,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.12,0:13:56.91,中英,,0,0,0,,那感觉就像 以快进的速度\Nkind of like fast-forwarding
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.91,0:14:01.25,中英,,0,0,0,,一天浏览十次二战\Nthrough World War II ten times a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.25,0:14:03.00,中英,,0,0,0,,但是 你知道 当你一遍又一遍的\NBut, you know, like,when you see things
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.00,0:14:04.67,中英,,0,0,0,,看东西时\Nover and over and again,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.67,0:14:06.55,中英,,0,0,0,,它们的含义也在改变\Ntheir meanings change for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.55,0:14:14.85,中英,,0,0,0,,比如说 当你看到这些二战的新闻影像资料时\NLike, when you see these... see,like, World War ll newsreels,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.85,0:14:17.60,中英,,0,0,0,,看了一段时间过后 你会觉得\Nlike, after a while,you come to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.60,0:14:20.40,中英,,0,0,0,,这些影像都是假的\Nthat it's all faked on film.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.40,0:14:25.19,中英,,0,0,0,,你看到的不是诺曼底登录\NYou are not seeing troops storming Normandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.19,0:14:30.28,中英,,0,0,0,,你看到的是军队登录好莱坞的一个沙滩\NYou're seeing troops storming a beach in Hollywood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.28,0:14:35.12,中英,,0,0,0,,再比如 你看到的不是一架飞往日本的战机\NYou know, like, you're not seeing a plane flying to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.12,0:14:40.13,中英,,0,0,0,,而是飞往新墨西哥州\NYou're seeing a plane flying over, you know, New Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.29,0:14:46.09,中英,,0,0,0,,你所看到的都是舞台上的英雄主义\NWhat you're really being shown is, like, staged heroism.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.09,0:14:50.68,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以看到士兵们在车上\NYou know, like, you're seeing men moving with machines,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.68,0:14:54.05,中英,,0,0,0,,但是你却看不到他们交谈\Nbut you're not seeing what they're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.06,0:14:57.78,中英,,0,0,0,,我认为这正是库布里克的表现方式\NAnd I think that that's something that Kubrick plays on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.78,0:15:02.90,中英,,0,0,0,,他既利用你所看到的画面\NLike, he plays on your acceptance of visual infor...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.90,0:15:06.32,中英,,0,0,0,,也利用着你忽略的画面\Nand also your ignorance of visual information.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.32,0:15:10.74,中英,,0,0,0,,比如 他经常使用一些你在角落中才能看到的\NLike he'll often, like,put little special clues
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.74,0:15:13.83,中英,,0,0,0,,细微线索\Nthat you see,like, in the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.29,0:15:21.50,中英,,0,0,0,,每一个场景都有着匪夷所思的设定\NEvery scene,there's an impossibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.50,0:15:24.84,中英,,0,0,0,,比如这台没有电线的电视\Nlike the TV doesn't have a cord
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.84,0:15:27.39,中英,,0,0,0,,或者更简单直白一些的 比如\Nor even something as simple as,like, them...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.39,0:15:30.84,中英,,0,0,0,,他们入住酒店的时候带了很多行李\Nthey, like...they bring too much luggage up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.84,0:15:34.55,中英,,0,0,0,,在电影中 杰克瞥了一眼\NThey, like... Jack, you know,glances over at a pile
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.55,0:15:36.02,中英,,0,0,0,,他们带来的那一堆行李\Nof their luggage that they brought,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.02,0:15:39.27,中英,,0,0,0,,大概有一辆轿车那么大\Nand ifs about the size of a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.27,0:15:40.27,中英,,0,0,0,,此外 影片中还有很多笑点\NYou know, a lot of it is jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.27,0:15:43.19,中英,,0,0,0,,比如 在游览时\NLike, they're taking the tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.19,0:15:47.61,中英,,0,0,0,,他们穿过迷宫前的那条路\NThey're crossing the street from the maze
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.61,0:15:49.45,中英,,0,0,0,,去参观车库\Nto go check out the garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.45,0:15:52.53,中英,,0,0,0,,有一辆车眼看着就要撞上他们\NLike, a car is just about to hit them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.53,0:15:54.53,中英,,0,0,0,,但在发生之前却剪掉了\NAnd then it cuts right before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.94,0:16:05.98,大,,0,0,0,,{\pos(620,608)}浓缩
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.17,0:16:08.84,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我在上映之前就看过这部电影\N- I had anticipated the film
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.84,0:16:11.55,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(608,18)}*《闪灵》作者
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.84,0:16:11.55,中英,,0,0,0,,同时也阅读了史蒂芬金*的小说\Nand had read the Stephen King novel
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.55,0:16:16.05,中英,,0,0,0,,我发现这是一个非常吸引人的故事\Nbefore the film came out and found it a very appealing story.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.05,0:16:18.39,中英,,0,0,0,,我花了很多时间\NAnd I had spent a lot of time
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.39,0:16:23.23,中英,,0,0,0,,去研究了科罗拉多州 埃斯蒂斯公园的斯坦利酒店\Nat the Stanley Hotel in Estes Park, Colorado,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.23,0:16:27.15,中英,,0,0,0,,这里是史蒂芬金写《闪灵》的灵感来源\Nwhich is where he was inspired to write the book The Shining.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.15,0:16:31.40,中英,,0,0,0,,因此 我对小说的创作背景比较了解\NAnd so I, you know... I knew a little bit of the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.40,0:16:33.24,中英,,0,0,0,,而当电影上映时\NAnd when Kubrick's film came out,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.24,0:16:35.58,中英,,0,0,0,,我是第一批看过的人\NI was first in line to see it,of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.58,0:16:38.87,中英,,0,0,0,,但我很失望\NAnd I was just really disappointed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.87,0:16:40.99,中英,,0,0,0,,我中途离场了\Nand walked out of the theater
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.00,0:16:43.67,中英,,0,0,0,,想着我刚才看的是什么鬼东西\Nwondering what the hell I had just witnessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.67,0:16:50.67,中英,,0,0,0,,自那之后 我对史丹利·库布里克的崇拜\NAnd, I... actually,my reverence for Stanley Kubrick
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.67,0:16:52.67,中英,,0,0,0,,一落千丈\Ndiminished after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.43,0:16:58.60,中英,,0,0,0,,尽管如此 我还是每隔几年就再看一遍\NI was disappointed, but I still watched it every few years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.60,0:17:02.10,中英,,0,0,0,,我不知道为什么会被\NI couldn't understand why I was so attracted to watching a film
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.10,0:17:04.10,中英,,0,0,0,,一部不喜欢的电影吸引着\Nthat I actually didn't like.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.10,0:17:08.02,中英,,0,0,0,,而在看了这么多遍之后\NAnd now in all these years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.02,0:17:11.61,中英,,0,0,0,,我知道它为什么是一部伟大电影了\NI know why it is a great film.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.61,0:17:13.07,中英,,0,0,0,,是一部杰作\NIt is a masterpiece,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.07,0:17:15.66,中英,,0,0,0,,但不是绝大多数人所说的原因\Nbut not for the reasons that most people think.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.83,0:17:25.12,中英,,0,0,0,,我们在和一个智商200的人打交道\NWe are dealing with a guy who has a 200 IQ.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.12,0:17:27.83,中英,,0,0,0,,我相信在斯坦利·库布里克\N believe that when Stanley Kubrick
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.83,0:17:33.34,中英,,0,0,0,,在完成《巴里·林登》之后 百无聊赖\Nfinished with Barry Lyndon,he was bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.34,0:17:36.84,中英,,0,0,0,,他已经征服了电影场景的设计\NHe had conquered the filmmaking landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.84,0:17:41.51,中英,,0,0,0,,他也做到了拍出一部又一部的伟大的作品\NHe had succeeded in making masterpiece after masterpiece,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.51,0:17:44.35,中英,,0,0,0,,他寂寞了\Nand he was bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.35,0:17:47.06,中英,,0,0,0,,《巴里·林登》也是一部无聊的电影\NBarry Lyndon is a boring movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.06,0:17:48.61,中英,,0,0,0,,它拍摄完美\NIt is wonderfully shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.61,0:17:50.61,中英,,0,0,0,,服装精致\NIt is beautifully costumed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.61,0:17:54.73,中英,,0,0,0,,但这是由一个寂寞的人拍出来的\NBut it is a film made by a guy who is bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.74,0:17:57.45,中英,,0,0,0,,我看的出来\NAnd I could see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.45,0:18:01.83,中英,,0,0,0,,所以我觉得库布里克在《巴里·林登》之后就转型了\NAnd so I think Stanley retreated after Barry Lyndon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.83,0:18:06.96,中英,,0,0,0,,他开始研究一种新的类型\NAnd he began working on a new kind of film,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.96,0:18:11.21,中英,,0,0,0,,一种他从未尝试过的类型\Na film that had never been made before,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.21,0:18:14.50,中英,,0,0,0,,一部由一个寂寞的天才\Na film that was made by a bored genius
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.51,0:18:21.09,中英,,0,0,0,,在抛弃一切丰功伟绩之后\Nwho had thoroughly emptied the jug of everything
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.10,0:18:23.31,中英,,0,0,0,,所拍出的电影\Nthat could be done in filmmaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.32,0:18:26.14,中英,,0,0,0,,他开始寻觅\NAnd he was looking for the next thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.14,0:18:31.52,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(622,18)}*美国作家
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.14,0:18:31.52,中英,,0,0,0,,他读了威尔逊·布赖恩·基*的《潜意识的诱惑》\NAnd what he did was he began reading Subliminal Seduction
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.52,0:18:34.95,中英,,0,0,0,,还有一些关于广告商是如何\Nand a number of other books which were about how advertisers
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.95,0:18:40.82,中英,,0,0,0,,如何将 潜意识图片\Nwere injecting...injecting images,subliminal images,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.82,0:18:44.58,中英,,0,0,0,,注入广告 来提高销量的书籍\Ninto advertising to sell products more.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.58,0:18:48.29,中英,,0,0,0,,- "头屑去无踪,秀发更出众"\N- "Suggestible trends".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.29,0:18:51.21,中英,,0,0,0,,- 比如在钻石金酒的广告中\N- You know, there'll be an ad for Gilbey's Gin,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.21,0:18:55.21,中英,,0,0,0,,冰块内部是各种生殖器的形状和\Nand inside, the ice cubes will be various sex organs
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.21,0:19:00.81,中英,,0,0,0,,一些其他的性暗示\Nand things to add a subliminal appeal to the ad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.43,0:19:05.93,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克去了这些广告公司\NKubrick went to these advertisers,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.93,0:19:09.06,中英,,0,0,0,,询问了这类广告的研究方法\Nand he asked them what their methods were.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.06,0:19:11.10,中英,,0,0,0,,并将这一方法\NAnd then he took those methods
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.10,0:19:15.15,中英,,0,0,0,,使用在《闪灵》中\Nand he applied them to The Shining.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.15,0:19:22.41,中英,,0,0,0,,《闪灵》里有许多潜意识画面\NInside The Shining are hundreds of subliminal images and shot line-ups.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.41,0:19:25.83,中英,,0,0,0,,这些画面\NAnd what these images are telling
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.83,0:19:32.37,中英,,0,0,0,,是非常恐怖和有着强烈性暗示意味的\Nis an extremely disturbing story about sexuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.38,0:19:36.54,中英,,0,0,0,,这一情节的潜台词\NAnd the subtext of the story,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.55,0:19:40.05,中英,,0,0,0,,与其他情节不同\Nbesides the other subtexts of the story,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.05,0:19:46.55,中英,,0,0,0,,它所说的是幽灵 魔鬼\Nis a story of haunted phantoms and demons
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.56,0:19:52.10,中英,,0,0,0,,在两性方面 勾引着人类\Nwho are sexually attracted to humans
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.10,0:19:55.61,中英,,0,0,0,,并以人类为食\Nand are feeding off of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.61,0:20:02.11,中英,,0,0,0,,你不一定非得像我这样狂热的去发现这些\NYou'd have to be able to be a complete fanatic like I am in order to find all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.11,0:20:04.58,中英,,0,0,0,,我会告诉你我最钟意的发现\Nbut, you know,I'll give you my favorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.58,0:20:08.79,中英,,0,0,0,,我最最钟意的那一个\NI'm only gonna give you one,but I'll give you my favorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.79,0:20:12.66,中英,,0,0,0,,在电影一开头\NWhen Jack meets Stewart Ullman in the office
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.67,0:20:14.79,中英,,0,0,0,,当杰克与斯图尔特·厄尔曼在办公室会见时\Nat the very beginning of the movie
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.79,0:20:18.47,中英,,0,0,0,,厄尔曼起身与杰克握手\Nand he reaches over to shake Jack Nicholson's hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.47,0:20:21.56,中英,,0,0,0,,让我们慢速播放这个场景\Nand so step through that scene frame by frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.56,0:20:23.55,中英,,0,0,0,,逐秒逐帧的看\NAnd the minute,the moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.55,0:20:27.80,中英,,0,0,0,,当厄尔曼的手碰到杰克时\Nthe frame that he and Jack Nicholson touch hands
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.81,0:20:31.47,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(652,18)}*斯图尔特·厄尔曼扮演者
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.81,0:20:31.47,中英,,0,0,0,,在巴里·尼尔森*\Nand right after the line that Barry Nelson says,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.48,0:20:34.64,中英,,0,0,0,,说了"很高兴见到你"之后\Nwhich is, "Nice to see you,"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.65,0:20:41.03,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以看到一个...\Nyou can see that there's a paper...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.03,0:20:44.70,中英,,0,0,0,,一个放在桌上的文件盒\Na paper tray on the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.70,0:20:48.95,中英,,0,0,0,,当他们刚接触到彼此的手\NAnd as soon as they touch hands,the paper tray
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.95,0:20:53.54,中英,,0,0,0,,那个文件盒就变成了\Nturns into a very large straight-on hard-on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.54,0:20:56.84,中英,,0,0,0,, \N巴黎·尼尔森勃起的象征\Ncoming out of Barry Nelson.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.54,0:20:57.06,中英,,0,0,0,,{\c&H01FFF1&\\pos(528.8,619)} ↑
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.08,0:20:59.04,中英,,0,0,0,,呵呵呵呵呵呵\NYeah, it's hilarious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.04,0:21:04.01,中英,,0,0,0,,这是个笑话 一个由库布里克构思的严肃笑话\NIt's a joke... a very serious joke... but a joke by Stanley.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.01,0:21:06.72,中英,,0,0,0,,诸如此类的电影中还有很多\NAnd there's many of these in the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.72,0:21:11.14,中英,,0,0,0,,其中也有一些让人感到困扰\NAnd very disturbing,some of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.14,0:21:14.19,中英,,0,0,0,,我的电影《魔术师库布里克》会告诉大家全部的细节\NAnd this will all be in my film,Kubrick the Magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.19,0:21:15.48,中英,,0,0,0,,我再说一个\NI'll give you one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.48,0:21:17.69,中英,,0,0,0,,一个更难发现的细节\NThis one's harder to find, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.69,0:21:20.36,中英,,0,0,0,,首先你得知道 库布里克\NAnd you have to know what Stanley Kubrick looked like
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.36,0:21:23.57,中英,,0,0,0,,在拍《闪灵》时 长什么样\Nduring the making of The Shining to know this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.57,0:21:25.82,中英,,0,0,0,,在影片的开场\NBut if you go to the opening credits
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.82,0:21:27.66,中英,,0,0,0,,你逐帧的播放\Nand you pan the frame...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.66,0:21:30.24,中英,,0,0,0,,一帧一帧的看\Nyou... you go through the frames,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.24,0:21:34.16,中英,,0,0,0,,在字幕"导演 斯坦利·库布里克"\Nright after it says "Directed by Stanley Kubrick,"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.16,0:21:38.88,中英,,0,0,0,,就要滚出屏幕时\Nas soon as his name passes off the frame,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.88,0:21:44.51,中英,,0,0,0,,暂停 你会发现 库布里克的面容\Nstop and you will see that the clouds have Stanley Kubrick
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.51,0:21:49.39,中英,,0,0,0,,隐藏在了云层之中\Nairbrushed into them,his face...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.39,0:21:52.73,中英,,0,0,0,,包括他的胡子 头发 整个面庞\Nwith the beard and the wild hair and the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.73,0:21:54.77,中英,,0,0,0,,我知道这发现这个有点困难（看出来的请豆油我）\NI know this one's a little harder to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.77,0:21:56.06,中英,,0,0,0,,我甚至...\NAnd I will have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.06,0:21:59.31,中英,,0,0,0,,甚至需要把它PS出来 别人才能发现\NI will have to Photoshop this one to show people it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.32,0:22:03.19,中英,,0,0,0,,但这里绝对是把一张库布里克的照片\Nbut there is definitely the photograph of Stanley Kubrick
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.19,0:22:07.99,中英,,0,0,0,,在一帧里将其与云层叠画\Nin one frame airbrushed into the clouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.66,0:22:13.04,中英,,0,0,0,,- 在大多数电影中 叠化转场\N- In most films,a dissolve is used
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.04,0:22:16.83,中英,,0,0,0,,常被用在象征两个时间跨度较长的场景\Nto indicate a long passage of time between two scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.83,0:22:20.25,中英,,0,0,0,,但在《闪灵》中 叠化转场的持续时间非常久\NBut in The Shining,the dissolves go on for so long
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.26,0:22:22.63,中英,,0,0,0,,以至于它们能够创造出\Nthat they create a superimposition,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.63,0:22:27.26,中英,,0,0,0,,由两个场景相互叠加作用出的新场景\Nwhere different scenes seem to be interacting with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.26,0:22:31.26,中英,,0,0,0,,比如说 这里你有一个外景\NFor example,you have the exterior image
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.26,0:22:35.39,中英,,0,0,0,,接着是一个酒店大堂的轨道平移拍摄\Na tracking shot of the lobby
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.39,0:22:39.81,中英,,0,0,0,,摄影机沿着西边的墙运动\Nof the camera moving along the western wall
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.81,0:22:42.94,中英,,0,0,0,,酒店入口面朝南边\Nsouth towards the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.94,0:22:49.78,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以看到一个清洁员在拖地\NAnd you see a janitor mopping the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.78,0:22:52.37,中英,,0,0,0,,但叠化使这个画面看上去\Nbut it looks like he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.37,0:22:54.46,中英,,0,0,0,,看上去像 他拿着一个巨大的拖把\Nit looks like a he's a giant, mopping,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.46,0:22:58.16,中英,,0,0,0,,在打扫森林\Nlike, clearing the forest
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.16,0:23:03.50,中英,,0,0,0,,因为那儿正好是森林里的一块空地\Nbecause he's mopping, like,a vacant area in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.50,0:23:07.67,中英,,0,0,0,,还有那个\NAnd then the...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.67,0:23:12.09,中英,,0,0,0,,那个立着的梯子\Nthen the ladder lines up...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.09,0:23:16.76,中英,,0,0,0,,和金字塔形的酒店外观同时出现\Nlines up with the pyramid form of the exterior of the hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.77,0:23:22.13,中英,,0,0,0,,而在酒店外的场景中 金字塔三角形消失了\Nwhich, in the exterior set,disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.15,0:23:23.36,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(702,711)}就像不存在一样\NLike, we don't see...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.36,0:23:26.20,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(864,709)}我们只在林线旅馆看到了金字塔形的屋顶\Nwe only see that in the Timberline exteriors.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.20,0:23:29.82,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(806,715)}但在英格兰的拍摄场景中\NBut the England movie set exteriors of the hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.82,0:23:31.91,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(742,701)}金字塔外形不见了\Nlike, the pyramid is missing,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.96,0:23:53.28,右1,,0,0,0,,{\pos(804.2,425)}{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&}胡德堡   俄勒冈州
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.96,0:23:53.28,右2,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&\pos(976,408.4)}林线旅馆
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.96,0:23:53.32,左2,,0,0,0,,{\pos(284,542.8)}{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&}远望酒店外景
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.96,0:23:53.32,左1,,0,0,0,,{\pos(156,683.2)}{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&}埃尔斯特里制片厂   英格兰
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.91,0:23:37.66,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(854.6,705.6)}看起来 远望酒店\Nand it seems as if the hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.66,0:23:44.46,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(833.2,697.2)}只模仿建造了林线酒店的两侧\Nthen takes both sides of the Timberline Hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.46,0:23:47.68,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(874.2,713.8)}这就像合二为一的手法\Nand then kind of, like,makes a composite of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.68,0:23:50.80,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(823.2,707)}因此 这种转换\NSo it's... you know,it's a perceptual shift
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.80,0:23:54.99,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(791.8,701.4)}让角色看起来像是巨人\Nof making people look like giants,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.01,0:24:00.93,中英,,0,0,0,,也让酒店看起来或大或小\Nalso making the hotel look larger or smaller than it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.94,0:24:03.28,中英,,0,0,0,,我认为这些东西让电影更丰满\NI mean, these things kind of litter the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.28,0:24:06.73,中英,,0,0,0,,但随着机位的移动\NBut then the shot goes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.73,0:24:08.78,中英,,0,0,0,,我们看到...\NWe see a...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.78,0:24:14.95,中英,,0,0,0,,看到一个门卫推着一台装有折叠床的货车\Nwe see a janitor pushing a folded-up bed on wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.41,0:24:21.20,中英,,0,0,0,,他后面跟着...\NAnd then he's followed by another...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.21,0:24:25.29,中英,,0,0,0,,另一个人 抬着一个...\Nhe's followed by another guy,who's carrying, like, one...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.29,0:24:27.75,中英,,0,0,0,,像是咖啡桌\Nlike, one coffee table?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.75,0:24:31.05,中英,,0,0,0,,接着还有一个人抬着一张椅子\NAnd then another... like, another guy is carrying one chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.05,0:24:36.22,中英,,0,0,0,,他们抬着这些轻货物是去哪儿呢?\NLike, where are these guys going with, like, these light loads, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.31,0:24:42.60,中英,,0,0,0,,然后我们看到杰克坐在沙发上 吃午饭\NThen we see Jack sitting on a chair, eating lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.60,0:24:46.15,中英,,0,0,0,,接着酒店管理员和他的助手\NAnd the manager and his assistant crosses paths
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.15,0:24:47.81,中英,,0,0,0,,穿过两个女人走的那条路上\Nwith two women who...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.82,0:24:50.44,中英,,0,0,0,,正当管理员走到屏幕角落的时候\Nand just as he's in the corner of the screen...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.44,0:24:52.24,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以看到\Nyou just see it for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.24,0:24:54.41,中英,,0,0,0,,其中一个女人身上穿着写有 13 的衣服\NYou see one of the women is wearing, like, a 13,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.41,0:24:55.66,中英,,0,0,0,,写着13的运动衫\Na number 13 jersey?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.12,0:24:59.12,中英,,0,0,0,,你听到了吗\NCan you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.12,0:25:01.91,中英,,0,0,0,,我儿子在叫（这熊孩子）\NMy boy, yelling?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.91,0:25:02.91,中英,,0,0,0,,等我一下\NHold on one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.91,0:25:04.08,中英,,0,0,0,,我去看看（能不能打死他）...\NI'm gonna see if I can...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.08,0:25:05.92,中英,,0,0,0,,我去让他老实点儿\NI can see if I can calm him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.09,0:25:14.76,中英,,0,0,0,,杰克靠在沙发上\NYou know,so, like, he's like,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.76,0:25:16.76,中英,,0,0,0,,吃着三明治\Nleaning back and eating a sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.76,0:25:19.39,中英,,0,0,0,,他双腿之间夹着一本杂志\NAnd he's got, you know,a magazine in his lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.39,0:25:22.52,中英,,0,0,0,,而在他起身向管理员打招呼时\NAnd as he stands up to greet them,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.52,0:25:23.94,中英,,0,0,0,,他把杂志扔在了沙发上\Nhe, like, throws it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.94,0:25:26.10,中英,,0,0,0,,如果你仔细观察...\NAnd if you look at"look at...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.10,0:25:28.40,中英,,0,0,0,,看杂志的封面\Nlook at it, you know,close up,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.40,0:25:32.98,中英,,0,0,0,,你会发现它是一本《花花女郎》\Nit's an actual Playgirl magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.99,0:25:36.36,中英,,0,0,0,,在酒店的大堂里看《花花女郎》杂志\NYeah, a Playgirl magazine in the lobby of a hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.37,0:25:39.12,中英,,0,0,0,,而且就在上班的第一天 在他的老板面前\Nright in front of his boss,like on his first day at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.45,0:25:42.99,中英,,0,0,0,,没错\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.00,0:25:46.80,中英,,0,0,0,,那一期的封面是 人们筹备新年\NLike, the cover is like, people getting ready for New Year's.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.80,0:25:49.29,中英,,0,0,0,,书内有一篇关于乱伦的文章\NThere's an article about incest.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.80,0:25:52.29,小字,,0,0,0,,{\c&H8BF5F9&\pos(625,212)}乱伦：为什么父母要带小孩睡觉←
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.29,0:25:52.84,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(630,18)}*删减版无此情节
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.29,0:25:52.84,中英,,0,0,0,,在电影的开头 丹尼受到了身体上的虐待*\NAt the beginning of the film,Danny's been physically abused.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.84,0:25:54.09,中英,,0,0,0,,但有一个关于\NBut there's a suggestion
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.09,0:25:56.64,中英,,0,0,0,,他也被性侵的暗示\Nthat he's been sexually abused as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.72,0:26:02.93,中英,,0,0,0,,有一个镜头\NYou know, so like,just in that one...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.93,0:26:09.56,中英,,0,0,0,,有一个镜头是各种复杂的事物\None shot, there's all these,like, you know, complex things
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.56,0:26:10.86,中英,,0,0,0,,在画面背景中 碰到了一块儿\Ngoing on in the background,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.86,0:26:13.15,中英,,0,0,0,,就像是被设计\Nlike things that are choreographed
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.15,0:26:14.49,中英,,0,0,0,,让它们刚好联系起来\Nto match up exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.49,0:26:16.24,中英,,0,0,0,,比如 我们看到一个人...\NLike, we see a guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.24,0:26:20.16,中英,,0,0,0,,一个人背着...\Nwe see a guy, carrying a...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.16,0:26:25.83,中英,,0,0,0,,背着一条地毯 进入楼上的房间\Nentering the room,carrying a rug.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.83,0:26:28.50,中英,,0,0,0,,而这个场景就要结束时\NAnd by the time the scene is just ending,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.50,0:26:30.59,中英,,0,0,0,,我们看到他上楼了\Nwe see him walking up the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.59,0:26:35.05,中英,,0,0,0,,就像他穿过了整个大堂\NLike, he's crossed the entire place,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.05,0:26:36.05,中英,,0,0,0,,分秒不差\Nyou know, timed exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.05,0:26:37.05,中英,,0,0,0,,实在是...\NI don't even...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.59,0:26:41.60,中英,,0,0,0,,好厉害\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.52,0:26:51.65,中英,,0,0,0,,- 当厄尔曼带着托伦斯一家\N- When Ullman is leading the Torrances
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.65,0:26:55.73,中英,,0,0,0,,走出电梯 进入科罗拉多休息室时\Nout of the elevator and into the Colorado Lounge
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.73,0:27:01.03,中英,,0,0,0,,在上一个场景中 大厅里有一堆行李箱\Nfor the first time,there's a pile of suitcases.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.03,0:27:03.95,中英,,0,0,0,,而在叠化至这一场景时\NAnd in the dissolve into that scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.95,0:27:08.41,中英,,0,0,0,,变成了一群游客\Nthe scene before,a group of tourists
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.41,0:27:09.75,中英,,0,0,0,,站在那儿\Nare standing in the lobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.75,0:27:13.00,中英,,0,0,0,,形成了行李箱和游客之间的叠化\NAnd those tourists dissolve into the suitcases.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.00,0:27:15.17,中英,,0,0,0,,作为大屠杀历史的研究者\NNow, as an historian of the Holocaust,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.18,0:27:17.84,中英,,0,0,0,,当时我就震惊了\NI find that very, very striking
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.84,0:27:19.22,中英,,0,0,0,,而这绝不是巧合\Nand certainly not accidental
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.22,0:27:22.68,中英,,0,0,0,,因为叠化转场是一种画面上的结合\N'cause he's using those sort of cross-dissolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.68,0:27:25.10,中英,,0,0,0,,这和那个梯子一样\NNow, that could be,along with the ladder,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.10,0:27:27.82,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克想要制造出实质的\Nwhere he's trying to make substantive connections
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.82,0:27:29.53,中英,,0,0,0,,有迹可循的关联\Nas well as formal ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.40,0:27:37.90,中英,,0,0,0,,- 哦~厄尔曼办公室的窗户\N- Oh, the window in Ullman's office,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.90,0:27:39.95,中英,,0,0,0,,美艳至极\Nit is absolutely beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.24,0:27:43.71,中英,,0,0,0,,一般的观众\NThe casual viewer isn't going to see
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.71,0:27:46.37,中英,,0,0,0,,在库布里克的电影中是看不到如此多的细节的\Nso many things in Kubrick's films,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.37,0:27:49.37,中英,,0,0,0,,他们也许会感觉画面不舒服\Nalthough I think they may register unconsciously.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.37,0:27:51.29,中英,,0,0,0,,但是他们不能\NYou know, but they're not going to, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.29,0:27:52.75,中英,,0,0,0,,不能道出个所以然\Nperceive perhaps these things
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.76,0:27:53.92,中英,,0,0,0,,因为就像我说的\Nbecause as I've said,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.92,0:27:56.96,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克让假的东西看起来真实\Nhe presents them as being real.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.96,0:27:58.26,中英,,0,0,0,,《闪灵》是现实主义\NYou know, it's realism.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.26,0:28:00.01,中英,,0,0,0,,它并不是一部典型的恐怖片...\NAnd it's not your typical horror...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.01,0:28:01.26,中英,,0,0,0,,只有在影片最后\Nyou don't have a horror film
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.26,0:28:03.31,中英,,0,0,0,,温蒂跑入冷色调的大厅里\Nexcept for this one section at the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.31,0:28:07.64,中英,,0,0,0,,到处都是蜘蛛网\Nright where Wendy walks in and the lobby is blue
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.64,0:28:09.31,中英,,0,0,0,,你才觉得这是一部恐怖片\Nand you've got the cobwebs all around.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.31,0:28:10.48,中英,,0,0,0,,这就像\NAnd it's almost like
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.48,0:28:12.40,中英,,0,0,0,,在周末 看着正能量晨间剧时\Na Saturday morning kind of horror film
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.40,0:28:13.94,中英,,0,0,0,,突然出现了好几只贞子\Nsuddenly there for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.94,0:28:15.40,中英,,0,0,0,,你的反应会是\NAnd you kind of go
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.40,0:28:18.74,中英,,0,0,0,,"天哪 这些乱入的骷髅和蜘蛛网是个啥？"\NOoh, what is this with the skeletons and the cobwebs?"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.74,0:28:20.28,中英,,0,0,0,,有点儿庸俗\NAnd it's kind of cheesy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.28,0:28:22.82,中英,,0,0,0,,在那个场景之后\NBut then, after that,following that,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.83,0:28:25.12,中英,,0,0,0,,温迪跑在红色的走廊里\Nyou've got her going down the red hallway,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.12,0:28:28.28,中英,,0,0,0,,在大屏幕上看 让人石化\Nwhich...on the big screen, that's petrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.29,0:28:30.50,中英,,0,0,0,,所以我认为 之前的那种庸俗\NSo I think the kind of cheesiness before it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.51,0:28:32.62,中英,,0,0,0,,推动了红色走廊场景的建立\Nhelps set up that red hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.04,0:28:37.13,中英,,0,0,0,,哎我刚才说哪儿了？\NSo anyway, what was I saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.13,0:28:38.30,中英,,0,0,0,,噢对窗户\NRight, the windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.30,0:28:40.46,中英,,0,0,0,,当杰克进入大厅\NSo you got... Jack has entered.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.46,0:28:42.39,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以看到\NAnd you can see...you are...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.39,0:28:43.80,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克向你展现\NKubrick shows you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.80,0:28:46.90,中英,,0,0,0,,向你展现了这个大堂 你可以看到...\NBut he shows you this lobby,and you get to see...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.90,0:28:51.10,中英,,0,0,0,,随着杰克穿过大堂 你可以看到前方的电梯\Nas Jack moves across the lobby,you see the elevator beyond.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.10,0:28:53.15,中英,,0,0,0,,还有一条通道\NAnd you see beyond that,a hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.15,0:28:56.36,中英,,0,0,0,,你不知道它后面有多长\NYou don't see yet how far back it goes, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.36,0:28:59.36,中英,,0,0,0,,对于后面那条路 你有印象\Nthe other things back there,but you have an impression
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.36,0:29:02.82,中英,,0,0,0,,这个地方是面朝酒店中间的\Nthat this place is towards the middle of the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.83,0:29:04.99,中英,,0,0,0,,你只是印象中觉得\NYou just have that impression that it's towards
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.99,0:29:06.66,中英,,0,0,0,,它面朝酒店中间\Nthe middle of the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.66,0:29:10.21,中英,,0,0,0,,你跟着杰克从大厅进入总经理的办公室\NAnd you go from the lobby into the general manager's office
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.21,0:29:15.41,中英,,0,0,0,,接着是厄尔曼的办公室 窗户在那里\Nand then into Ullman's office, and there's this window.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.42,0:29:17.34,中英,,0,0,0,,一扇强有力的窗户\NAnd the window's a powerful window.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.34,0:29:19.71,中英,,0,0,0,,我是说 阳关穿过玻璃 折射出耀眼的光芒\NI mean, the light coming through there is glaring.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.71,0:29:22.09,中英,,0,0,0,,窗户就像一个角色\NIt's like a character in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.09,0:29:24.22,中英,,0,0,0,,它像一个主宰者\NIt takes over.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.22,0:29:27.68,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以看到 一些杂乱弯曲 不吉利的树\NAnd you've got these tendril-y,sinister kind of trees
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.68,0:29:29.06,中英,,0,0,0,,种在窗户外面\Nthat are outside the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.06,0:29:30.68,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以感觉到\NAnd you've got...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.68,0:29:32.35,中英,,0,0,0,,光束抓住了一切\Nit's just such a forceful presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.35,0:29:34.07,中英,,0,0,0,,彰显着强大的存在感\Nthis light that comes over everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.07,0:29:36.06,中英,,0,0,0,,但是你感到\NAnd, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.06,0:29:39.02,中英,,0,0,0,,这里有些不对劲\NAnd there's something wrong with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.02,0:29:40.19,中英,,0,0,0,,肯定有不合常理的地方\NThere's something wrong with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.20,0:29:42.82,中英,,0,0,0,,我认为这显现出了一个错误\Nand I think it registers as something wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.82,0:29:44.49,中英,,0,0,0,,这是一扇不存在的窗户\NThis is an impossible window.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.49,0:29:46.78,中英,,0,0,0,,它不存在\NIt's not... it is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.78,0:29:48.20,中英,,0,0,0,,它是实际上的不存在\NIt is physically impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.20,0:29:49.20,中英,,0,0,0,,它不应该在那\NIt cannot be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.20,0:29:50.70,中英,,0,0,0,,它不可能出现\NIt should not be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.70,0:29:54.70,中英,,0,0,0,,酒店里没有地方设立这个窗户\NThere's no place in the hotel for this window to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.71,0:29:55.71,中英,,0,0,0,,只有在...\NIt's only toward...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.71,0:29:57.17,中英,,0,0,0,,在影片的最后\Nfinally,towards the end of the film,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.18,0:30:00.54,中英,,0,0,0,,你会意识到在厄尔曼的办公室后面\Nthat you have the realization that there are several hallways
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.54,0:30:04.21,中英,,0,0,0,,有好几条走廊\Nin succession behind the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.21,0:30:06.97,中英,,0,0,0,,当温迪走下楼\NYou see it when Wendy,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.97,0:30:10.14,中英,,0,0,0,,看到迪克·哈洛伦\Nwhen she's later down there and she sees Dick Hallorann's body
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.14,0:30:11.93,中英,,0,0,0,,死去的尸体时\Nafter he's been killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.93,0:30:16.19,中英,,0,0,0,,你知道她是在...在办公室后面的过道上\NYou have her behind... in that hallway behind the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.65,0:30:22.32,中英,,0,0,0,,我该怎么跟你描述酒店的平面图呢？\NSo really, now, what can I tell you about the maps?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.32,0:30:24.32,中英,,0,0,0,,不行 我得画个图\NNo, I did not sit down with graph paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.32,0:30:27.07,中英,,0,0,0,,我不按比例 画个草图\NI did not even begin to attempt to do them to scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.07,0:30:28.28,中英,,0,0,0,,让我想一下\NLet me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.28,0:30:30.12,中英,,0,0,0,,我不知道从哪个房间开始\NI can't say which room I started off with.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.12,0:30:31.87,中英,,0,0,0,,我忘了\NI don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.87,0:30:34.25,中英,,0,0,0,,我打算从...\NI just went through and decided I was going to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.25,0:30:37.25,中英,,0,0,0,,我尽量说的详细一些...\Ntry to do as much as I could,feeling that...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.25,0:30:39.04,中英,,0,0,0,,我认为 我可以划分出\NI felt, eventually,that there were places
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.04,0:30:43.09,中英,,0,0,0,,两个女孩被杀死的房间\Nthat I could plot out, such as where the girls were killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.09,0:30:44.96,中英,,0,0,0,,我不是很确认\NI was not absolutely sure at that point,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.96,0:30:46.43,中英,,0,0,0,,那个房间是不是\Nwhen I started out doing the maps,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.43,0:30:47.68,中英,,0,0,0,,我画地图的起始点\Nwhere the girls were killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.68,0:30:53.72,中英,,0,0,0,,（这段她说的乱and我翻的也乱...）
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.68,0:30:50.14,中英,,0,0,0,,应该是在后面\NBut I felt that it was somewhere back around
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.14,0:30:53.72,中英,,0,0,0,,他们居住的区域\Nthe area where they lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.72,0:30:55.26,中英,,0,0,0,,房间号是...\NSuite number, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.27,0:30:57.06,中英,,0,0,0,,他们住3号房\NThey lived at suite number 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.69,0:31:04.57,中英,,0,0,0,,- 当杰克坐在那儿打字时\N- When Jack is sitting,typing at his typewriter,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.57,0:31:07.12,中英,,0,0,0,,温迪走出来 在他工作时\Nand Wendy comes in and interrupts him
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.12,0:31:08.61,中英,,0,0,0,,打扰到了他\Nwhile he's working...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.61,0:31:10.20,中英,,0,0,0,,而在杰克的一个画面中...\Nand in one shot of Jack...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.20,0:31:11.54,中英,,0,0,0,,- 你今天写了很多吗？\N- You get a lot written today?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.54,0:31:14.28,中英,,0,0,0,,- 坐在打字机前的那个镜头里\N- Sitting at the typewriter,a one shot,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.28,0:31:15.41,中英,,0,0,0,,在他的后面\Nyou look back behind him.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.41,0:31:17.13,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以很清楚的看到\NAnd of course,you can see very clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.13,0:31:20.66,中英,,0,0,0,,因为库布里克是景深大师\N'cause Kubrick was the master of depth of field.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.67,0:31:23.92,中英,,0,0,0,,他让一切处于焦距范围内 所以他能够让你\NHe kept everything in focus so he would have lots of space
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.92,0:31:27.14,中英,,0,0,0,,注意到他故意设置的细节\Nin which to puts things that he wanted you to notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.14,0:31:31.38,中英,,0,0,0,,在这个镜头中 杰克坐在打字机前\NAnd in the first shot,behind Jack sitting at his typewriter,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.39,0:31:35.44,中英,,0,0,0,,在他身后 大约10或12或者15英尺的墙边\Nback against a wall, behind him probably 10 or 12 or 15 feet
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.44,0:31:36.48,中英,,0,0,0,,有一张椅子\Nis a chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.81,0:31:42.06,中英,,0,0,0,,接着是一个温迪说话的镜头\NAnd then there's a switch to a one-shot of Wendy saying something.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.06,0:31:45.69,中英,,0,0,0,,- 嘿 天气预报说今晚下雪\N- Hey, the weather forecast said it's gonna snow tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.69,0:31:48.94,中英,,0,0,0,,- 接着镜头回到杰克身上\N- And then the camera switches back to Jack,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.94,0:31:51.15,中英,,0,0,0,,他身后的椅子不见了\Nand the chair is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.15,0:31:52.83,中英,,0,0,0,,- 下雪我有什么办法？\N- What do you want me to do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.33,0:31:58.50,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我和学生们总是乐此不疲\N- And my students and I always have fun with that,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.50,0:32:01.33,中英,,0,0,0,,"是不是穿帮了？"\Nsaying,"Well, continuity error?"
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.33,0:32:02.83,中英,,0,0,0,,也许是\NCould be.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.83,0:32:06.63,中英,,0,0,0,,也许刻意使然\NOr it's not,and the answer, if it's not...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.63,0:32:08.50,中英,,0,0,0,,如果是穿帮\Nor if it was originally
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.51,0:32:10.97,中英,,0,0,0,,那么库布里克发现了它 并决定保留\Nand then Kubrick saw it and decided to keep it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.98,0:32:15.22,中英,,0,0,0,,这种山寨恐怖片的行为\Nis that he's parodying horror films
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.22,0:32:21.27,中英,,0,0,0,,是在提醒观众 这不是一部简单的恐怖片\Nin order to remind you that this isn't just a horror film.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.27,0:32:23.57,中英,,0,0,0,,而在电影中 还有一幕 我认为\NAnd there's another one in The Shining that's, I think,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.57,0:32:25.19,中英,,0,0,0,,更不容易被发现\Nless well-noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.19,0:32:30.19,中英,,0,0,0,,我觉得这一点更真实可靠\NAnd I think it's even more clearly substantive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.19,0:32:35.74,中英,,0,0,0,,当丹尼第一次看到电梯血涌时\NWhen Danny has his first vision of the elevator gushing blood
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.74,0:32:39.03,中英,,0,0,0,,摄影机在向他移动\Nand the camera is tracking toward him,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.04,0:32:42.12,中英,,0,0,0,,穿过他卧室的门\Npast the open door of his bedroom
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.12,0:32:44.67,中英,,0,0,0,,朝着走廊和浴室前移\Nand toward the hall and the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.67,0:32:46.96,中英,,0,0,0,,接着横穿过道 到了浴室门口\Nthe open bathroom door across the hall...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.97,0:32:51.38,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以看的出 他卧室门上\Nand his bedroom door, as you would expect a kid's door,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.38,0:32:54.30,中英,,0,0,0,,贴着很多动漫人物\Nhas lots of cartoon characters on it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.30,0:32:57.47,中英,,0,0,0,,最明显的那一个贴纸\NAnd, the one who is most apparent,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.47,0:32:59.31,中英,,0,0,0,,在门的右侧边缘\Nbecause it's right at the edge of the door
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.31,0:33:01.53,中英,,0,0,0,,它是你可以看到的最完整的一个\Nand it's the largest one that you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.53,0:33:05.90,中英,,0,0,0,,也是在摄影机运动时 你能看到的最后一个人物贴纸\Nand it's the last one you can see as the camera moves past it,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.90,0:33:08.06,中英,,0,0,0,,它是七个小矮人中的一个\Nis one of the Seven Dwarves.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.06,0:33:11.41,中英,,0,0,0,,它叫迷糊鬼\NAnd it happens to be Dopey,okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.07,0:33:16.41,中英,,0,0,0,,后来 在丹尼昏过去之后（删减版无此情节）\NSubsequently,after Danny has passed out,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.41,0:33:19.41,中英,,0,0,0,,当温迪和儿科医生\NWendy and the pediatrician leave Danny's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.41,0:33:21.75,中英,,0,0,0,,离开丹尼的房间时\NAnd as they do, they,of course, go out his door.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.75,0:33:23.33,中英,,0,0,0,,你又可以看到那扇门\NAnd you again see the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.34,0:33:26.25,中英,,0,0,0,,贴着卡通人物的开着的门\Nthe open door with all the cartoon characters on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.26,0:33:29.00,中英,,0,0,0,,迷糊鬼不在那儿了\Nand Dopey isn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.00,0:33:31.92,中英,,0,0,0,,又是穿帮吗？\NNow, again continuity error?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.92,0:33:33.42,中英,,0,0,0,,我不这么认为\NI don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.42,0:33:36.14,中英,,0,0,0,,我觉得库布里克是在说\NI think what Kubrick is saying is that before,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.14,0:33:41.10,中英,,0,0,0,,丹尼对世界有了更多的了解\NDanny had no idea about the world, and now he knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.10,0:33:43.06,中英,,0,0,0,,他不再是一个迷糊鬼了\NHe is no longer a dope about things.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.06,0:33:44.56,中英,,0,0,0,,他被启发过了\NHe has been enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.02,0:33:50.77,中英,,0,0,0,,你说了算 劳埃德\N- - Anything you say, Lloyd.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.77,0:33:52.24,中英,,0,0,0,,你说了算\NAnything you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.12,0:34:08.29,中英,,0,0,0,,- 接着发生了意外\N- The the advocaat is spilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.29,0:34:09.29,中英,,0,0,0,,荷兰产蛋酒洒了出来\NThere's the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.29,0:34:10.46,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克像是设计了\NKubrick is setting it up
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.46,0:34:12.76,中英,,0,0,0,,一个圆 让人物绕着它走位\Nas where they come around in a circle,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.76,0:34:14.97,中英,,0,0,0,,我觉得摄影机就是这样运动的\N'cause I feel like that's what the camera does.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.97,0:34:17.81,中英,,0,0,0,,我感觉摄影机在带着我们绕圈\NI feel like the camera brings us around in a circle
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.81,0:34:19.72,中英,,0,0,0,,带着我们回到原点\Nso that we're coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.72,0:34:24.85,中英,,0,0,0,,洗手间似乎是在金色大厅上面\NThe bathroom seems to be overlaying the Gold Room and...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.85,0:34:27.23,中英,,0,0,0,,在洗手间 处理那个意外时\Nso that the advocaat situation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.23,0:34:28.85,中英,,0,0,0,,他们站立的地点大概和\Nin the bathroom is occurring about
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.86,0:34:31.20,中英,,0,0,0,,在金色大厅发生的地点一致\Nin the same area that it did in the Gold Room.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.28,0:34:38.53,中英,,0,0,0,,- 他们使用摄影机\N- They use the camera
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.53,0:34:42.62,中英,,0,0,0,,在观众脑海里创造出一个看似合理的建筑\Nto create an emotional architecture in your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.62,0:34:45.29,中英,,0,0,0,,但同时 又证明你错了\Nbut at the same time,showing you that it's false.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.29,0:34:48.91,中英,,0,0,0,,整个场景的可塑性如此之高\NThe set is complete...so completely plastic
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.92,0:34:51.69,中英,,0,0,0,,以至于各种矛盾都堆积在你的潜意识中\Nthat its contradictions pile up in your subconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.73,0:34:57.82,中英,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&\pos(636,608)}走出C3                                              进入C4
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.30,0:34:58.47,中英,,0,0,0,,哈洛伦向...\NHallorann is showing...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.47,0:35:02.14,中英,,0,0,0,,向温迪展示了后面的情节中\Nshowing Wendy, you know,the place where she will,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.14,0:35:08.31,中英,,0,0,0,,她会困住杰克的地方\Nyou know, basically,entrap Jack...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.31,0:35:10.69,中英,,0,0,0,,无论是生理\Nentrap him both physically,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.69,0:35:16.82,中英,,0,0,0,,还是心理上 对杰克都是最后一击\Nbut also, like, that will be the last straw for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.82,0:35:20.86,中英,,0,0,0,,这也是对酒店的最后一击\Nlast straw for the management of the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.86,0:35:22.87,中英,,0,0,0,,在储藏室中 杰克决定\NIt's in the store room that he finally is like,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.87,0:35:27.20,中英,,0,0,0,,开始还击\N"Okay.Now I'm gonna do it."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.20,0:35:29.63,中英,,0,0,0,,而那扇门的开启\NAnd, you know,the opening of that door
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.63,0:35:35.21,中英,,0,0,0,,是影片中唯一不可思议的\Nis the famous, like,only thing that's supernatural
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.21,0:35:38.22,中英,,0,0,0,,无法解释的超自然情节\Nhappens in the movie that can't be explained any other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.22,0:35:40.22,中英,,0,0,0,,是的\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.93,0:35:45.14,中英,,0,0,0,,除了另一种说法\NBut except that it can be explained another way,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.14,0:35:46.89,中英,,0,0,0,,那就是 丹尼把他放了出来\Nin that Danny lets him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.56,0:35:56.03,中英,,0,0,0,,而我的确认为\NI do have this idea that Danny
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.03,0:35:58.45,中英,,0,0,0,,丹尼是自发的杀了他的父亲\Nis a lot more consciously murdering his father
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.45,0:36:00.41,中英,,0,0,0,,而不是情节使然\Nthan the narrative lets on.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.08,0:36:11.08,中英,,0,0,0,,我也说不清 很诡异\NI don't know.It's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.08,0:36:13.25,中英,,0,0,0,,比如 当温迪和杰克在休息室对峙时\NLike, you notice how, like,Wendy's walking backwards
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.26,0:36:20.76,中英,,0,0,0,,你有没有注意到 她是如何后退的\Nwhen she's having that confrontation with Jack in the lounge, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.76,0:36:27.76,中英,,0,0,0,,她像是被什么往后拉\NAnd she's being drawn up to the hexagonal hallway room.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.76,0:36:31.56,中英,,0,0,0,,而丹尼也是在那儿闪灵的\NAnd you see Danny shining at the beginning of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.56,0:36:34.10,中英,,0,0,0,,他在屋子里\NHe's in his room,and there's, like,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.10,0:36:36.65,中英,,0,0,0,,眼睛里像有火焰闪烁\Nlights flickering in his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.07,0:36:40.11,中英,,0,0,0,,就像丹尼...\NLike, is Danny drawing...you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.12,0:36:44.61,中英,,0,0,0,,在拉他的母亲后退 以使她能够\Ndrawing his mother up the stairs so that she can, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.61,0:36:49.21,中英,,0,0,0,,在高处击中杰克 像是一个诡异的金字塔\Nsacrifice Jack on top of that,you know, weird pyramid?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.67,0:37:00.22,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我曾经在丹佛做报道\N- When I had a chance...when I was doing a story
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.22,0:37:02.01,中英,,0,0,0,,我们去了埃斯蒂斯公园\Nout in Denver,we went up to Estes Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.01,0:37:03.80,中英,,0,0,0,,那是在旅游淡季\NIt was in the off-season.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.80,0:37:06.68,中英,,0,0,0,,在史丹利酒店 我请求和经理见一面\NWent into the Stanley Hotel,and I asked to see the manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.68,0:37:09.02,中英,,0,0,0,,于是他们和他一起吃了中饭\NAnd he came out, and we were just having lunch with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.02,0:37:11.52,中英,,0,0,0,,我问他：“可以采访你吗？我在写《闪灵》的报道”\NAnd I said, "Can we talk to you?I write about The Shining."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.52,0:37:12.73,中英,,0,0,0,,他说：“真的吗？”\NHe said, "Really?"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.73,0:37:14.48,中英,,0,0,0,,他告诉我\NThis fellow told me
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.48,0:37:19.27,中英,,0,0,0,,他接到了库布里克的电话 对方说：\Nthat he got a phone call from Stanley Kubrick, who said,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.27,0:37:21.62,中英,,0,0,0,,“我想拍一部关于《闪灵》的电影\N”"I think I want to make a movie about The Shining."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.62,0:37:26.78,中英,,0,0,0,,之后他们谈了很久\NAnd then he would keep this fellow on the phone for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.78,0:37:29.20,中英,,0,0,0,,经理说：“我们谈了很多\NHe said, "We had many long, long conversations
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.20,0:37:31.75,中英,,0,0,0,,他几乎把什么都跟我说了”\Nin which he picked my brain about everything."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.75,0:37:32.95,中英,,0,0,0,,他又说\NAnd at that point, he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.95,0:37:34.75,中英,,0,0,0,,“库布里克计划来这里拍一部电影”\N"Kubrick was talking about maybe coming here
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.75,0:37:38.34,中英,,0,0,0,,而这正是他期待的\Nto make the movie here,"which I expect, at that point,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.34,0:37:40.09,中英,,0,0,0,,酒店经理喜欢这个想法 因为\Nthat fellow liked the idea of,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.09,0:37:41.59,中英,,0,0,0,,这会让酒店更有名气\Nso it would make his hotel famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.59,0:37:44.26,中英,,0,0,0,,接着 库布里克说：“我要先让考察团去看看”\NAnd Kubrick said, "I'd like to send out a research team."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.26,0:37:46.26,中英,,0,0,0,,接着考察团就来了...\NAnd so he then sent out...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.26,0:37:48.35,中英,,0,0,0,,经理说 有两三个人\Nthe man said it was something like two or three people
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.35,0:37:49.85,中英,,0,0,0,,在酒店那儿住了\Nwho came out here and stayed here
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.85,0:37:54.27,中英,,0,0,0,,两三个月 到处拍照取景\Nfor two or three months,taking photographs everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.27,0:37:56.19,中英,,0,0,0,,他们也花了很多时间研究丹佛\NAnd they spent a lot of time also down in Denver
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.19,0:37:58.06,中英,,0,0,0,,和科罗拉多州的历史\Nn the Colorado state archives,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.06,0:38:00.61,中英,,0,0,0,,他们理清了\Nfinding out,as I would now expect,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.61,0:38:04.40,中英,,0,0,0,,科罗拉多州的历史\Nthe full history of Colorado,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.40,0:38:06.00,中英,,0,0,0,,包括不同地方代表的旗帜\Nwhich... the flag of which plays a part.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.00,0:38:09.99,中英,,0,0,0,,还有淘金 科罗拉多淘金热\NAnd the gold rush,the Colorado Gold Rush
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.99,0:38:11.41,中英,,0,0,0,,也是相当大的事件\Nwas also a very big event.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.41,0:38:12.83,中英,,0,0,0,,还有很多...\NAnd there's all...there's still a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.83,0:38:15.75,中英,,0,0,0,,还有在科罗拉多州 白人、印第安人\Nof American Indian/white people tension in Colorado
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.75,0:38:19.04,中英,,0,0,0,,和纳瓦霍人、阿拉帕霍人的对立\Nwith Navajos and Arapahos just to the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.04,0:38:21.13,中英,,0,0,0,,这个调查团队找出了关于\NThis research team found out absolutely everything
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.13,0:38:23.38,中英,,0,0,0,,科罗拉多 关于埃斯蒂斯公园\Nabout Colorado,about Estes Park,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.38,0:38:25.88,中英,,0,0,0,,关于斯坦利酒店的一切一切\Nabout the Stanley Hotel,about its entire history,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.88,0:38:28.47,中英,,0,0,0,,拍了各个地方的照片\Ntook photographs all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.47,0:38:30.39,中英,,0,0,0,,我的印象中 这三个月就是\NThree months was the impression that I have
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.39,0:38:32.98,中英,,0,0,0,,他所描述的那样\Nof what he said about how this research team
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.98,0:38:35.56,中英,,0,0,0,,收集了一切\Ngathered absolutely everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.56,0:38:38.90,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克发掘了科罗拉多州的\NKubrick unearthed an enormous amount about the real history
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.90,0:38:41.44,中英,,0,0,0,,大量历史事实\Nof Colorado, where this takes place,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.44,0:38:45.82,中英,,0,0,0,,他所做的是去发现一条\Nbecause what he has done is found a way to dig
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.82,0:38:48.57,中英,,0,0,0,,探索我们文明的道路\Ninto all of the patterns of our civilization,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.57,0:38:50.91,中英,,0,0,0,,探索我们的时代 我们的文化\Nour times and our cultures,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.91,0:38:53.41,中英,,0,0,0,,甚至那些我们不屑一顾的东西\Nand the things that we don't want to look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.41,0:38:56.75,中英,,0,0,0,,而这部电影也是关于\NAnd this movie is very much also about denial
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.75,0:38:58.54,中英,,0,0,0,,白人对大屠杀的否认\Nof the genocides that we committed...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.54,0:39:00.29,中英,,0,0,0,,欧洲白人\Nwe white folk from Europe...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.29,0:39:03.13,中英,,0,0,0,,在此犯下罪恶\Ncommitted here and not that...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.13,0:39:05.35,中英,,0,0,0,,然而并不是只有白人进行了大屠杀\Nnot that white folks are the only people who do genocide.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.35,0:39:08.26,中英,,0,0,0,,全人类都有过大屠杀 库布里克在电影中表达的很清楚\NAll humans do, as Kubrick makes clear in this movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.26,0:39:11.22,中英,,0,0,0,,他会将电影中出现的一切事物\NHe would research everything and the full history and nature
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.23,0:39:14.44,中英,,0,0,0,,一切历史 自然 都调查清楚\Nof everything you're gonna see in the movie on the screen
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.44,0:39:19.27,中英,,0,0,0,,之后将它们合为一体\Nand then boil it down and boil it down
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.27,0:39:21.36,中英,,0,0,0,,形成一个普遍的 总体的模式\Nuntil he got the universal human and global patterns
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.36,0:39:24.36,中英,,0,0,0,,这让电影更加真实\Nthat make it so real.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.36,0:39:27.69,中英,,0,0,0,,- 白人的负担啊 劳埃德\N - White man's burden,Lloyd, my man.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.69,0:39:29.45,中英,,0,0,0,,真是白人的负担\NWhite man's burden.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.54,0:39:37.83,中英,,0,0,0,,我喜欢你 劳埃德\NI like you, Lloyd.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.83,0:39:39.71,中英,,0,0,0,,我一直都喜欢你\NI always liked you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.71,0:39:42.29,中英,,0,0,0,,你一直是最棒的\NYou were always the best of 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.29,0:39:44.75,中英,,0,0,0,,从延巴克图到缅甸州的波特兰\NThe best goddamned bartender
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.75,0:39:48.13,中英,,0,0,0,,到俄勒冈州的波特兰\Nfrom Timbuktu to Portland, Maine,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.13,0:39:50.63,中英,,0,0,0,,你一直是最好的调酒师\Nor Portland, Oregon,for that matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.64,0:39:52.35,中英,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢你的承认\N- Thank you for saying so.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.35,0:39:53.59,中英,,0,0,0,,- 这是什么意思？\N- What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.60,0:39:55.02,中英,,0,0,0,,杰克所说的 "从延巴克图开始\NJack saying, "You always were the best of 'em."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.02,0:39:56.27,中英,,0,0,0,,你一直是最棒的\NStarting in Timbuktu?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.27,0:39:58.27,中英,,0,0,0,,作为一名作家 杰克从未去过延巴克图\NJack the schoolteacher was never in Timbuktu,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.27,0:40:00.73,中英,,0,0,0,,但作为普通人民\Nbut Jack the universal weak male
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.73,0:40:02.98,中英,,0,0,0,,曾被征兵参战的杰克\Nhired by armies to go commit atrocities
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.98,0:40:04.61,中英,,0,0,0,,去过那儿\Nhas always been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.98,0:40:07.07,中英,,0,0,0,,毫无疑问 "波特兰"是指\NNow, of course,the word "Portland"
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.08,0:40:08.91,中英,,0,0,0,,我们当时登陆的地方\Nis neat because it means where we landed
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.91,0:40:12.20,中英,,0,0,0,,或者说是英国 欧洲人登陆的地方\Nor where the British or the Europeans landed.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.20,0:40:14.79,中英,,0,0,0,,而俄勒冈州的波特兰则指他们\NAnd Portland, Maine... Oregon is where they may have taken off
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.79,0:40:16.08,中英,,0,0,0,,去往远东的出发地\Nfrom to go further west.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.49,0:40:20.25,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克考虑了\NKubrick is thinking about the implications
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.25,0:40:22.25,中英,,0,0,0,,一切存在事物的涵义\Nof everything that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.00,0:40:26.00,中英,,0,0,0,,美国伟大诗人理查德·威尔伯曾说\NYou know, the power of the genie is in its confinement,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.00,0:40:28.88,中英,,0,0,0,,鬼怪的力量存在于限制之中\Nas the great American poet Richard Wilbur said.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.88,0:40:31.92,中英,,0,0,0,,神灯里有一万年的精华\NBoiling it down, you know,10,000 years in a little lamp,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.93,0:40:33.22,中英,,0,0,0,,你得赶快行动\Nyou got to get your act together.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.22,0:40:34.39,中英,,0,0,0,,但那正是伟大艺术的来源\NBut that's the essence of great art.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.39,0:40:35.76,中英,,0,0,0,,就像梦一样\NIt's like a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.76,0:40:38.18,中英,,0,0,0,,伟大艺术将一切熔在一个象征之中\NIt's boiled everything down to an emblematic symbol
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.18,0:40:40.02,中英,,0,0,0,,熔出了生活\Nthat's got all of life in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.35,0:40:44.53,中英,,0,0,0,,请允许我再拓展一下\NNow, if you'll allow me to make a little bit of a link here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.53,0:40:46.44,中英,,0,0,0,,最近我一直在思考一个问题\NAs I've thinking of this more in recent years,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.44,0:40:50.36,中英,,0,0,0,,我们所理解的就是我们梦想的本质\Nwhat we now understand to be the nature of what dreams are,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.37,0:40:55.03,中英,,0,0,0,,我是说 通常的理论是\NI mean, it seems to be,the general theory is,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.03,0:40:57.41,中英,,0,0,0,,大脑将我们先前的经验\Nthat it's a way for the brain to boil down
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.41,0:40:59.03,中英,,0,0,0,,归纳 总结为一体\Nall of the previous experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.04,0:41:01.46,中英,,0,0,0,,再加上那一天的经历\Nand then add in that day's experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.46,0:41:04.42,中英,,0,0,0,,我们可以发现\Nas well to see what kind of overall universal patterns
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.27,0:41:11.72,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(632,52)}希区柯克·《爱德华大夫》
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.43,0:41:06.54,中英,,0,0,0,,一个普遍的模式\Nthere are to be found,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.54,0:41:09.34,中英,,0,0,0,,这样你就会知道那个模式是什么样的\Nso that you can be aware of what the patterns are out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.34,0:41:11.72,中英,,0,0,0,,就可以在看到危险发生时\Nso that your subconscious will be all the more ready
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.72,0:41:14.22,中英,,0,0,0,,或者在重要的事情发生时\Nto react suddenly when you see something dangerous happen
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.22,0:41:20.97,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以提前作出反应\Nor something important happen that may lead you to a mate or to some food or away from danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.72,0:41:20.97,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(660,18)}大致意思应该就是吃一堑长一智和应激
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.97,0:41:27.56,中英,,0,0,0,,因此 库布里克拍电影的方式\NAnd therefore, the way Kubrick made movies was not unlike
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.56,0:41:30.44,中英,,0,0,0,,就是根据这些理论的\Nthe way, according to these current theories,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.44,0:41:35.15,中英,,0,0,0,,我们的大脑可以创造出记忆\Nour brains create memories and, for that matter, dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.15,0:41:39.32,中英,,0,0,0,,这就是库布里克拍《闪灵》的基本原则\NThat's the ultimate shining that Kubrick does.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.33,0:41:41.33,中英,,0,0,0,,他就像有着巨型大脑\NHe is like a mega brain for the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.33,0:41:44.67,中英,,0,0,0,,能够将全世界的大量研究\Nwho is boiling down with all of this extensive research,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.67,0:41:47.58,中英,,0,0,0,,和各种模式结合起来\Nall of these patterns of our world
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.58,0:41:50.01,中英,,0,0,0,,之后还给我们一个梦一般的电影\Nand then giving them back to us in a dream of a movie...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.01,0:41:51.76,中英,,0,0,0,,因为电影就像梦一样...\Nbecause movies are like a dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.76,0:41:54.05,中英,,0,0,0,,所以我认为\Nand that's related to why I think
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.05,0:41:55.77,中英,,0,0,0,,在电影《闪灵》中\Nthere's a lot of evidence that what Kubrick
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.77,0:42:01.01,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克给了我们许多关于过去的证据\Nalso gave us in The Shining is a movie about the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.01,0:42:02.43,中英,,0,0,0,,不是随随便便的过去\NNot just any past.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.43,0:42:04.14,中英,,0,0,0,,过去\NThe past.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.14,0:42:06.44,中英,,0,0,0,,我是指历史性的\NI mean past-ness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.44,0:42:11.27,中英,,0,0,0,,这是一部关于过去所带来的冲击的电影\NIt's a movie about how the past impinges.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.27,0:42:13.28,中英,,0,0,0,,这也是鬼怪的含义\NThat's what ghosts are.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.28,0:42:16.12,中英,,0,0,0,,就像电影开头的诡异音乐\NThat's what those skitter-y voices in the opening shot
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.12,0:42:18.61,中英,,0,0,0,,无形中追随着你\Nthat are following are about.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.61,0:42:20.83,中英,,0,0,0,,当我想到《闪灵》时 通常用两个\NThere's two phrases from T.S.Eliot that I often think of
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.83,0:42:21.95,中英,,0,0,0,,艾略特*所写的句子的来形容\Nwhen I'm thinking about The Shining.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.83,0:42:21.95,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(642,18)}*美国诗人
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.95,0:42:23.54,中英,,0,0,0,,一个是"噩梦"...\NOne of them is "The night"...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.54,0:42:24.79,中英,,0,0,0,,我觉得应该都是艾略特的句子\NI think they're both from T.S. Eliot...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.79,0:42:26.04,中英,,0,0,0,,历史噩梦...\NThe nightmare of history...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.04,0:42:28.79,中英,,0,0,0,,"我们如何从历史噩梦中醒来？"\N"how can we awake from the nightmare of history?"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.88,0:42:34.13,中英,,0,0,0,,- 另一个词是...艾略特所说的...\N- And the other is his phrase...T.S. Eliot's phrase...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.13,0:42:37.01,中英,,0,0,0,,"历史总是狡兔三窟"\N"History has many cunning passages."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.47,0:42:42.55,中英,,0,0,0,,我认为这两句都直接而恰当的\NAnd I think both of those phrases are directly apt
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.56,0:42:44.39,中英,,0,0,0,,形容了《闪灵》 正如我们所见\Nfor The Shining,in which we see
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.40,0:42:47.48,中英,,0,0,0,,酒店和树篱迷宫里都有许多道路\Nmany cunning passages in the maze and in the hotel itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.48,0:42:50.23,中英,,0,0,0,,在那儿 过去成了噩梦\Nand in which the past becomes a nightmare,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.23,0:42:53.07,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克向你展示了 如何通过\Nand in which Kubrick shows us how you escape
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.07,0:42:56.61,中英,,0,0,0,,原路折返 逃离过去的噩梦\Nfrom the nightmare of the past by retracing your steps,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.61,0:42:57.83,中英,,0,0,0,,就像丹尼最后所做的\Nas Danny does in that last line,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.83,0:42:59.32,中英,,0,0,0,,这意味着 只有当你\Nwhich means acknowledging what happened
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.32,0:43:03.03,中英,,0,0,0,,看清各种模式时\Nand learning about the past and then getting out,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.03,0:43:05.75,中英,,0,0,0,,你才知道如何避免\Nonly if you are going to be able to shine
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.75,0:43:06.95,中英,,0,0,0,,才能够去追寻美好的事物\Nand see what the patterns are
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.95,0:43:08.17,中英,,0,0,0,,才能了解 掌握现实\Nso you know to get away from them
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.17,0:43:10.96,中英,,0,0,0,,才能在过去中吸取经验\Nand avoid them and go for the good things.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.96,0:43:15.59,中英,,0,0,0,,我是说 《闪灵》是库布里克关于家庭分裂的电影\NI mean, The Shining is his movie about how families break down,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.59,0:43:17.01,中英,,0,0,0,,不管他们是个体小家庭\Nwhether they are an individual family
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.01,0:43:22.43,中英,,0,0,0,,还是一个即将分裂的大家庭\Nor the larger societal family that tries to break up individual families.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.43,0:43:24.43,中英,,0,0,0,,他的最后一部电影 《大开眼界》则恰恰相反\NAnd his lats movie,Eyes Wide Shut is the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.43,0:43:28.35,中英,,0,0,0,,它是关于家庭的痛苦尝试\NIt's about a family sorely tried,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.35,0:43:30.52,中英,,0,0,0,,比尔·哈特福特和他的妻子 儿女们\NBill Hartford and his wife and child,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.52,0:43:32.52,中英,,0,0,0,,成功抵制了各种根植在\Nthat survives all the horrible temptations
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.52,0:43:34.15,中英,,0,0,0,,我们基因中的诱惑\Nthat are in our DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.84,0:43:43.35,大,,0,0,0,,{\pos(632,608)}走出迷宫
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.53,0:43:45.95,中英,,0,0,0,,- 这就是我们著名的树篱迷宫\N- This is our famous hedge maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.95,0:43:47.49,中英,,0,0,0,,这里很好玩\NIt's a lot of fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.50,0:43:48.79,中英,,0,0,0,,但我不想进去试试\NBut I wouldn't want to go in there
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.79,0:43:51.01,中英,,0,0,0,,除非我有一个小时的时间 才能找到出口\Nunless I had an hour to spare to find my way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.33,0:43:54.75,中英,,0,0,0,,- 几年后可以租《闪灵》的光碟时\N- I did not look at it again for a number of years
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.76,0:43:56.55,中英,,0,0,0,,我才看了第二遍\Nuntil it came out in rental.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.55,0:43:59.51,中英,,0,0,0,,之后我又看了好几遍\NAnd then I picked it up a couple of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.51,0:44:02.47,中英,,0,0,0,,那时候租一次碟可以看三天\NAnd, what, you had three days in order to watch a rental?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.47,0:44:03.69,中英,,0,0,0,,所以我记得在那三天\NAnd so, I can remember watching
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.69,0:44:05.89,中英,,0,0,0,,看了一遍又一遍\Nit over and over again during those three days
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.89,0:44:07.76,中英,,0,0,0,,每一遍都仔仔细细的看\Nand really taking a good look at it then.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.77,0:44:11.06,中英,,0,0,0,,当时我就像 "对 我记得这里\NAnd I was able to think "Oh,yes, this is what I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.06,0:44:12.40,中英,,0,0,0,,我本来以为是那样的"\NThis is what I thought I saw,"
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.40,0:44:13.65,中英,,0,0,0,,然后捕捉到了更多的细节\Nand then catching more things.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.65,0:44:15.90,中英,,0,0,0,,而在看DVD之前 我都没有发现这些\NBut it wasn't, of course,until DVD came out
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.90,0:44:17.74,中英,,0,0,0,,有了DVD之后 我可以坐下\Nthat I was really able to sit down
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.74,0:44:21.58,中英,,0,0,0,,认真的 完整的看这部电影\Nand take a good look at it as far as just running through it
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.58,0:44:25.53,中英,,0,0,0,,一遍又一遍\Nover and over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.53,0:44:29.87,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克将这些事物表现的\NKubrick presents these things where it's, you know, real...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.87,0:44:31.41,中英,,0,0,0,,更加真实\Nyou know, it's realistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.41,0:44:33.46,中英,,0,0,0,,你不清楚真正发生的是什么\NYou're not supposed to see what's actually going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.46,0:44:34.58,中英,,0,0,0,,比如丹尼\NYou've got Danny.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.58,0:44:36.21,中英,,0,0,0,,他在游戏房里 然后转身\NHe's in the game room.He turns around.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.21,0:44:39.46,中英,,0,0,0,,我们的注意力应该在那两个女孩身上\NWe're supposed to be focused on the two girls there.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.47,0:44:41.51,中英,,0,0,0,,可是...我看见...在左边\NAnd than you... I saw...over on the left,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.51,0:44:42.80,中英,,0,0,0,,我看到了那个滑雪者的海报\NI see this skiing poster.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.80,0:44:45.22,中英,,0,0,0,,这里的细节是关于杰克的\NAnd the thing is that you already have Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.22,0:44:47.10,中英,,0,0,0,,杰克之前询问过能否滑雪\NHe's already asked about skiing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.10,0:44:48.81,中英,,0,0,0,,但是...他当时说"能滑雪吗\NBut why isn't... you know,"What about skiing?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.82,0:44:50.85,中英,,0,0,0,,在酒店这儿可以滑雪吗？"\NIsn't the skiing good here in the hotel?"
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.85,0:44:53.69,中英,,0,0,0,,但他已经被告知为何滑雪不好\NAnd he's already given the story of why it isn't good,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.69,0:44:55.02,中英,,0,0,0,,为何不能滑雪\Nwhy they can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.02,0:44:56.02,中英,,0,0,0,,但是 这里依然贴着滑雪海报\NBut you got the skiing poster.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.02,0:44:57.19,中英,,0,0,0,,我的眼神被拉了过去\NAnd my eye is drawn to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.20,0:44:59.94,中英,,0,0,0,,我意识到 这不是一个滑雪者\NAnd I realize that's not a skier.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.94,0:45:01.41,中英,,0,0,0,,这是...这是一个牛头人\NThat's a... that's a minotaur.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.41,0:45:03.20,中英,,0,0,0,,我注意到了它\NIt just leaped out at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.20,0:45:04.20,中英,,0,0,0,,后来我在录像带上\NAnd so that was something
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.20,0:45:06.41,中英,,0,0,0,,又仔细看了看\Nthat I was able to look at later on VHS
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.41,0:45:09.37,中英,,0,0,0,,之后说"没错 那儿就是一个牛头人"\Nand say, "Yes, I had actually seen a minotaur there,"
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.37,0:45:12.12,中英,,0,0,0,,他的上半身 的确是\Nwhere the upper body, you've got this really, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.12,0:45:14.75,中英,,0,0,0,,一个夸张的身体形态\Noverblown physique,very physical physique.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.75,0:45:16.30,中英,,0,0,0,,你注意到了一个细节...\NAnd then you've got the suggestion...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.30,0:45:19.50,中英,,0,0,0,,就是那个滑雪杖\Nyou have a suggestion of a skiing pole there,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.50,0:45:21.22,中英,,0,0,0,,但它并不在那\Nbut it's not really there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.22,0:45:22.68,中英,,0,0,0,,它只是一个暗示\NIt's just a suggestion of one.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.68,0:45:25.01,中英,,0,0,0,,它的下半身被固定\NAnd the lower body is positioned,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.01,0:45:26.39,中英,,0,0,0,,双腿摆放的姿势\Nthe way the legs are,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.39,0:45:27.97,中英,,0,0,0,,整体造型 都像是一个牛头人\Nit's like a minotaur,the build is.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.97,0:45:29.52,中英,,0,0,0,,而且尾巴也出现在图中\NAnd you've actually got the tail there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.52,0:45:31.35,中英,,0,0,0,,所以它就是一个牛头人\NAnd so it is a minotaur.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.35,0:45:34.73,中英,,0,0,0,,在右边... 在门的另一边\NAnd this is in...on the opposite side of the door
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.73,0:45:38.31,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以看到骑在马背上的牛仔\Nyou have a cowboy on a bucking bronco, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.31,0:45:40.36,中英,,0,0,0,,因此你可以看的出这是一种对应\Nand so you got a kind of echo there,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.36,0:45:41.73,中英,,0,0,0,,你在门的一边\Nwhere you got the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.73,0:45:43.82,中英,,0,0,0,,看到牛头人\Nminotaur on one side,the bull man,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.83,0:45:46.41,中英,,0,0,0,,而在另一边 是一个牛仔\Nand on the other side,you got the cowboy,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.41,0:45:48.82,中英,,0,0,0,,骑在野马身上的人\Nthe man on the bucking bronco.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.82,0:45:51.95,中英,,0,0,0,,而这个场景是紧跟在\NAnd this is just following the scene where they...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.95,0:45:54.83,中英,,0,0,0,,厄尔曼带着杰克和温迪\NUllman has been taking Jack and Wendy
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.83,0:45:56.21,中英,,0,0,0,,穿过科罗拉多休息室\Nthrough the Colorado Lounge,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.21,0:45:58.05,中英,,0,0,0,,带领他们参观的那个场景之后\Nshowing off the Colorado Lounge.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.05,0:45:59.83,中英,,0,0,0,,当他们进入大厅\NAnd they go into the hall
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.84,0:46:01.63,中英,,0,0,0,,在科罗拉多休息室的后面\Nbehind the Colorado Lounge.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.63,0:46:04.21,中英,,0,0,0,,在这里的墙上\NAnd what's there,but on the wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.22,0:46:06.84,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以看到一幅关于美国印第安人\Nthere is a painting of an American Indian
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.84,0:46:09.34,中英,,0,0,0,,带着水牛头饰的画\Nwith a buffalo headdress on.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.35,0:46:12.02,中英,,0,0,0,,而在那时 厄尔曼在和温迪讨论\NAnd at that point,Ullman is discussing with Wendy
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.02,0:46:14.02,中英,,0,0,0,,哪些人曾经住过这家酒店\Nwho has stayed there at the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.02,0:46:17.24,中英,,0,0,0,,名门望族 上流人士 璀璨之星\NRoyalty, the best people,stars have stayed there.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.24,0:46:19.31,中英,,0,0,0,,- 名门望族？\N - Royalty?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.31,0:46:21.07,中英,,0,0,0,,- 都是最上等的人\N- All the best people.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.28,0:46:27.70,中英,,0,0,0,,- 在海报底部 你可以看到"君主"这个词\N- You have "monarch" on the bottom, which, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.70,0:46:29.61,中英,,0,0,0,,这是皇室的核心词\Nkeys in with royalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.62,0:46:32.37,中英,,0,0,0,,同样你也可以看到关于明星的暗示\NAnd you also have this whole idea of the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.37,0:46:36.29,中英,,0,0,0,,而君主的名字 应该是阿斯忒里俄斯*\NAnd the minotaur's name is,what, Asterius?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.37,0:46:36.29,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(639,18)}*希腊神话里的国王
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.29,0:46:39.33,中英,,0,0,0,,他名字的含义是"星光闪耀的"\NHis name is Asterius,which means "starry."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.33,0:46:41.05,中英,,0,0,0,,因此 你可以得到一些\NSo you know, you got several things there
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.05,0:46:42.92,中英,,0,0,0,,关于神话的联系\Nto do with mythology that fit in.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.92,0:46:44.17,中英,,0,0,0,,这让我很兴奋\NIt's very exciting to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.17,0:46:45.42,中英,,0,0,0,,这是一种...一种\NThat was the... you know,that's the kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.42,0:46:46.64,中英,,0,0,0,,这是一种很刺激的感受\Nleap-up-end-down moment where you go,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.64,0:46:49.84,中英,,0,0,0,,"哇偶 看看库布里克做了些什么"\N"Oh, wow, look at what Kubrick has there."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.84,0:46:52.64,中英,,0,0,0,,我知道 牛头人住在迷宫的核心地带\NYeah, I mean the minotaur lives at the heart of the labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.64,0:46:53.81,中英,,0,0,0,,他是迷宫的一部分\NHe's a part of the labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.81,0:46:54.98,中英,,0,0,0,,而迷宫 至少在神话中\NThe labyrinth,at least in the myth...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.98,0:46:56.19,中英,,0,0,0,,这个特殊的神话\Nyou know,in this particular myth...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.19,0:46:58.56,中英,,0,0,0,,是为牛头人而打造的\Nwas built for the minotaur.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.56,0:47:00.98,中英,,0,0,0,,这个酒店...就是一个迷宫\NThe hotel is... you know,it is the labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.99,0:47:03.40,中英,,0,0,0,,而杰克就是那个牛头人\NAnd Jack is the minotaur.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.40,0:47:06.65,中英,,0,0,0,,在一些场景里...\NYou have scenes with him where he...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.65,0:47:08.61,中英,,0,0,0,,他在...那叫啥？\Nsuch as in...what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.61,0:47:10.03,中英,,0,0,0,,在 星期二 那个场景里\NThe Thursday scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.03,0:47:11.91,中英,,0,0,0,,冬雪初降\NThe snowfall has started.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.91,0:47:15.45,中英,,0,0,0,,温迪和丹尼在外面玩雪\NYou have Wendy and Danny outside playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.45,0:47:17.25,中英,,0,0,0,,杰克在科罗拉多休息室里\NAnd Jack is inside the Colorado Lounge,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.25,0:47:18.71,中英,,0,0,0,,注视着外面的母子俩\Nand he's looking out at them.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.71,0:47:22.05,中英,,0,0,0,,脑袋略微下低 眼睛...\NHis head is tilted down,and his eyes are somewhat...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.05,0:47:23.42,中英,,0,0,0,,眼睛向上抬\Nhis eyes are elevated.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.42,0:47:24.42,中英,,0,0,0,,它们在朝上看\NThey're pointing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.42,0:47:26.17,中英,,0,0,0,,然后他的眉毛向上弯曲\NAnd his eyebrows are drawn up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.17,0:47:28.05,中英,,0,0,0,,但他脸上的表情\NBut he has this expression on his face
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.05,0:47:30.68,中英,,0,0,0,,脸上像公牛一样的表情 在电影中\Nthat he gets progressively throughout the film
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.68,0:47:32.14,中英,,0,0,0,,逐渐增多 形象起来\Nthat is very bull-like.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.14,0:47:34.43,中英,,0,0,0,,这是很像牛头人的表情\NIt has a very minotaur-like expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.43,0:47:36.23,中英,,0,0,0,,这和库布里克在其他电影中\NIt's the same kind of expression that Kubrick
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.23,0:47:37.44,中英,,0,0,0,,使用的表情 是一样的\Npulls out in other films,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.44,0:47:39.43,中英,,0,0,0,,比如在电影《全金属外壳》中\Nsuch as it was on Private Pyle's face
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.44,0:47:42.10,中英,,0,0,0,,浴室里狂暴的二等兵\Nin the berserker scene in the bathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.10,0:47:43.81,中英,,0,0,0,,派尔的脸上\Nin Full Metal Jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.81,0:47:46.44,中英,,0,0,0,,因此 这并不是《闪灵》所特有的\NSo it's, you know,not specific to this film.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.71,0:47:45.21,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(603,18)}《2001：太空漫游》
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.44,0:47:49.91,中英,,0,0,0,,还有很多的牛头人和神话意象\NThere's more minotaur imagery and labyrinth imagery.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.21,0:47:47.55,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(616,18)}《发条橙》
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.91,0:47:52.41,中英,,0,0,0,,比如 在金色大厅中\NThere's the Gold Room.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.41,0:47:53.41,中英,,0,0,0,,在金色大厅的前段\NIn front of the Gold Room,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.41,0:47:56.28,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以看到"休息时间"的标志\Nyou have the "Unwinding Hours" sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.29,0:47:58.13,中英,,0,0,0,,而这和迷宫是有联系的\NAnd that plays in with the labyrinth,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.13,0:47:59.79,中英,,0,0,0,,我联想到...\Nwhere you have...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.79,0:48:01.50,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(637,18)}*希腊神话中的雅典国王
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.79,0:48:01.50,中英,,0,0,0,,提修斯*进入迷宫\NTheseus enters into the labyrinth,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.50,0:48:02.75,中英,,0,0,0,,那时他的身上带着线球\Nand he has the thread with him
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.75,0:48:04.97,中英,,0,0,0,,系在自己身上\Nthat he ties at the beginning that,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.97,0:48:07.30,中英,,0,0,0,,借助线球进入迷宫\Nyou know, assists him in going through the labyrinth,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.30,0:48:09.01,中英,,0,0,0,,这样可以顺利的找到回路\Nwhere he can find his way back out.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.01,0:48:11.68,中英,,0,0,0,,所以当我看到"休息时间"的标志时\NAnd so I see the "Unwinding Hours" sign
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.68,0:48:14.47,中英,,0,0,0,,我觉得和那个线球有关系\Nas having to do with that thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.47,0:48:17.14,中英,,0,0,0,,我还注意到了那个棒球棒\NFor a while there,I was into baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.14,0:48:19.77,中英,,0,0,0,,对球棒的研究又让我很兴奋\NAnd I get very excited with baseball when I'm into baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.77,0:48:20.89,中英,,0,0,0,,我可以做自己\NYou know, I can be by myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.89,0:48:22.64,中英,,0,0,0,,可以带我装逼带我飞\Nand I will be leaping up and down.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.65,0:48:24.48,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克对我来说就像那样\NAnd Kubrick is like that for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.49,0:48:28.15,中英,,0,0,0,,我看到那个牛头人海报 \Nwhere all I have to do is see the minotaur poster there,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.15,0:48:31.03,中英,,0,0,0,,感叹道 "噢天哪 看这里！\N"and I go, "Oh, my goodness.Look at this!"
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.03,0:48:34.45,中英,,0,0,0,,因为一般人是看不到这个牛头人的\NBecause you're not supposed to see the minotaur.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.54,0:48:40.66,中英,,0,0,0,,- 影片中 丹尼骑着他的车逛酒店\N - Danny is shown riding his big wheel
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.67,0:48:43.54,中英,,0,0,0,,一共有三次\Nthrough the hotel three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.54,0:48:48.34,中英,,0,0,0,,第一次 我觉得是关于现实主义的\NThe first ride, I think, is about realism.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.34,0:48:50.05,中英,,0,0,0,,丹尼他...\NThat's Danny is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.05,0:48:56.05,中英,,0,0,0,,他在转圈\NDanny is doing a loop around the lounge set.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.05,0:48:58.39,中英,,0,0,0,,他绕着服务台的走廊\NYou know, he goes through the service hallway
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.39,0:48:59.81,中英,,0,0,0,,然后穿过休息室\Nand then he goes through the lounge
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.81,0:49:02.53,中英,,0,0,0,,之后回到服务台的走廊\Nand then he goes back into the service hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.53,0:49:05.65,中英,,0,0,0,,因此 当你第一次看这段\NAnd, you know,when you first see the movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.65,0:49:07.74,中英,,0,0,0,,你会觉得 他只在闲逛\Nyou're like,"He's just wandering around.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.74,0:49:09.48,中英,,0,0,0,,这很疯狂 但是...\NIt's crazy, it's just"...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.48,0:49:10.70,中英,,0,0,0,,但是...它很...\NBut it... no, it's very...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.70,0:49:13.03,中英,,0,0,0,,它只是一个简单的圆圈\Nit's just a very simple loop.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.03,0:49:14.82,中英,,0,0,0,,他绕了一圈\NHe does it once.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.82,0:49:18.58,中英,,0,0,0,,但是这让你对这个地方\NBut that gives you an idea of where...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.58,0:49:20.74,中英,,0,0,0,,有了初步的概念\Nof what that place is.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.74,0:49:22.29,中英,,0,0,0,,我是说 你了解到\NI mean, you know,all right, you understand
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.29,0:49:24.79,中英,,0,0,0,,这是个圆\Nthat that set is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.79,0:49:26.96,中英,,0,0,0,,这是一个长镜头\NYou know, like,it's a continuous shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.96,0:49:28.26,中英,,0,0,0,,不会有花招\NThere are no tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.26,0:49:32.92,中英,,0,0,0,,第二次骑车 是在六角走廊里\NIn the second ride,in the hexagonal hallway,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.92,0:49:33.92,中英,,0,0,0,,这里有很多...\Nthere are a lot of...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.92,0:49:35.39,中英,,0,0,0,,有很多把戏\Nthere are more tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.39,0:49:37.34,中英,,0,0,0,,比如 他并没有继续绕圈\NLike, he doesn't do a loop.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.34,0:49:42.06,中英,,0,0,0,,他的路线是钥匙形的\NHe does kind of like a key-shaped...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.06,0:49:48.06,中英,,0,0,0,,或者说是P形路线\Nyou know, or a p-shaped loop around this hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.06,0:49:54.37,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以看到这和休息室之间实际存在的联系\NAnd you see the realism of the connection to the lounge set.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.66,0:50:09.97,中英,,0,0,0,,你也同样会发现电梯的虚假性\NAnd... but you also see the fakery of the fake elevators.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.71,0:50:13.21,中英,,0,0,0,,你可以看到 只有一秒钟\NAnd you see...for just one second,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.21,0:50:16.94,中英,,0,0,0,,角落边的有色玻璃大窗户\Nyou see the big stained glass windows out of the corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.94,0:50:19.93,中英,,0,0,0,,在角落的框框里\Nin the corner of the frame
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.93,0:50:24.18,中英,,0,0,0,,在丹尼绕着电梯转弯之前\Nright before he takes a turn around the elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.18,0:50:26.28,中英,,0,0,0,,这是难以置信的 因为\NLike, that's incredible because,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.28,0:50:30.44,中英,,0,0,0,,感觉那个窗户连接了走廊\Nlike, that connects that whole hallway
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.44,0:50:34.61,中英,,0,0,0,,和巨大的科罗拉多休息室\Nto the giant Colorado Lounge set.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.61,0:50:35.95,中英,,0,0,0,,我是说 就那一秒\NI mean,that's just for one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.95,0:50:37.87,中英,,0,0,0,,其实 他们没必要这么设置\NThey didn't have to do that,you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.87,0:50:43.83,中英,,0,0,0,,但是 这是一种暗喻\NBut it's also... you know,it's a metaphor
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.83,0:50:45.62,中英,,0,0,0,,因为丹尼的高度提高了\Nbecause he's also elevated.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.62,0:50:48.47,中英,,0,0,0,,他比之前的位置提高了一层\NHe's one level up from where he was before.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.47,0:50:53.55,中英,,0,0,0,,感觉就像 他在同一个地方开始 但是上了一层楼\NLike, he starts in the same place, just one floor up,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.55,0:50:56.26,中英,,0,0,0,,在休息室的东北部\Nyou know, in the northeast corner of the set.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.26,0:50:59.81,中英,,0,0,0,,因此 他现在处于东北角 而且比原来高了一层\NSo now he's in the northeast corner and one level up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.81,0:51:02.80,中英,,0,0,0,,如果你把它看做是一个隐喻的话\NAnd if you take it as a metaphor of, like,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.81,0:51:08.73,中英,,0,0,0,,这就像从普通的现实上升到了你脑中\Ngoing from a mundane reality to up into your head
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.73,0:51:11.19,中英,,0,0,0,,一个更加虚、幻的现实\Nto more of a fantastical reality...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.19,0:51:14.90,中英,,0,0,0,,第三次骑车更加诡异\NThe third one is even stranger,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.90,0:51:17.03,中英,,0,0,0,,因为他从后勤部开始\N'cause he starts off in the service unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.03,0:51:18.28,中英,,0,0,0,,还是同一个地方\NHe starts off in the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.28,0:51:21.45,中英,,0,0,0,,在休息室的东北角\Nyou know, northeast corner of the lobby hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.45,0:51:24.12,中英,,0,0,0,,从后勤部的走廊出发\Nof the lobby service hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.12,0:51:28.83,中英,,0,0,0,,然后他转弯 突然 他就在楼上了\NAnd then he takes a turn,and suddenly he's upstairs
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.83,0:51:34.46,中英,,0,0,0,,到了他们公寓的外面\Nin the area outside their apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.05,0:51:38.64,中英,,0,0,0,,所以 这就像是在前两次\NSo, like,it's a kind of a combination
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.64,0:51:41.13,中英,,0,0,0,,他是在下面 而第三次他就到了楼上\Nof the first two,where like he's down low and then he's up high
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.80,0:51:45.31,中英,,0,0,0,,接着他转了弯 然后他突然...\NAnd then he takes a turn,and he's suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.31,0:51:49.89,中英,,0,0,0,,突然就到了黄蓝相间的墙纸那儿\Nhe's in that that yellow,yellow and blue wallpaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.89,0:51:53.06,中英,,0,0,0,,我们称这里为服务台的走廊地区\NLet's say that's in the service hallway area.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.06,0:51:55.53,中英,,0,0,0,,现在 他在父母房间的外面\NHe's, you know, right outside his parents' bedroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.53,0:51:59.53,中英,,0,0,0,,因此 在骑车和幻觉之间\Nso there's this connection between him
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.53,0:52:03.03,中英,,0,0,0,,有所关联\Ngoing on these big wheel rides and dreaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.03,0:52:05.28,中英,,0,0,0,,就像他在自己卧室旁边\NLike, he's near his bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.28,0:52:09.04,中英,,0,0,0,,他在...我们知道他的父母在楼下工作\NHe's near... like, you see his parents are working downstairs,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.04,0:52:11.62,中英,,0,0,0,,但是现在他在楼上\Nbut he's upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.62,0:52:15.71,中英,,0,0,0,,就像我们看到他的母亲在打电话\NYou know, like, you see his mom on the telephone,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.71,0:52:18.67,中英,,0,0,0,,而他在飞快的骑车\Nand then he's flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.67,0:52:22.47,中英,,0,0,0,,他骑到了位于她工作地点\NHe goes above her to the bedroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.47,0:52:24.27,中英,,0,0,0,,上方的卧室\Nwhich is above where she's working,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.27,0:52:27.68,中英,,0,0,0,,就像骑在位于他爸爸工作地点的上方\Njust as the hexagonal hallway
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.68,0:52:30.77,中英,,0,0,0,,那条六角走廊里\Nis above where his dad is working.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.77,0:52:34.24,中英,,0,0,0,,所以他的三轮车成了探索父母脑海\NSo these big wheel rides become like a visionary way
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.24,0:52:38.32,中英,,0,0,0,,虚幻的工具\Nof Danny to explore his parents' headspace.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.40,0:52:44.86,中英,,0,0,0,,而237房间\NYou know, like,room 237 is his, like...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.87,0:52:47.91,中英,,0,0,0,,就像他父亲的幻想密室\Nthat's his father's fantasy chamber
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.91,0:52:51.04,中英,,0,0,0,,他在那儿碰到了女巫\Nwhere, like, he gets it on with the witches.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.50,0:53:01.84,中英,,0,0,0,,那对双胞胎就像他母亲的幻想...\NAnd the twins are like his mother's fantasy...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.84,0:53:07.47,中英,,0,0,0,,他母亲的幻想空间 她们就像\Nfantasy headspace where, like,they're these double blue women
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.47,0:53:10.52,中英,,0,0,0,,这对想和丹尼一直玩下去的女人\Nwho want to play with Danny forever and ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.52,0:53:13.48,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我们会过的很开心的\N- We're all gonna have a real good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.40,0:53:23.08,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我对《闪灵》的理解是\N- My interpretation of The Shining
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.08,0:53:26.99,中英,,0,0,0,,这部电影有许多层面\Nis that there's many levels to this film.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.99,0:53:29.12,中英,,0,0,0,,就像一个三维的国际象棋\NThis is like three-dimensional chess.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.12,0:53:35.00,中英,,0,0,0,,而导演试着告诉我们一些看似分离\NAnd he's trying to tell us several stories
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.00,0:53:39.79,中英,,0,0,0,,却有着密切联系的故事\Nthat appear to be separate but actually are not.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.80,0:53:45.22,中英,,0,0,0,,他也通过电影脚本来实现这一点\NAnd he's doing this both through the overt script that he wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.22,0:53:48.97,中英,,0,0,0,,他利用商业技巧来表达\NHe's telling it through tricks of the trade,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.97,0:53:52.27,中英,,0,0,0,,通过潜意识的和大量重复的影像\Nthe subliminal imagery and these constant retakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.27,0:53:55.35,中英,,0,0,0,,和一些独特的视角 道具等来吸引你\Ngiving him odd angles and things.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.35,0:53:58.48,中英,,0,0,0,,而他通过对\NAnd he's also telling you
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.48,0:54:04.15,中英,,0,0,0,,史蒂芬·金小说的改动 来让你感受到不同\Nthrough the changes that he made to the Stephen King novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.15,0:54:06.03,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(624,18)}*小说 剧本 电影
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.15,0:54:06.03,中英,,0,0,0,,因此 如果你将这三者*结合\NSo if you watch those three things,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.03,0:54:09.49,中英,,0,0,0,,你会对电影有更深的了解\Nyou begin to understand this deeper story.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.49,0:54:14.33,中英,,0,0,0,,而这个蕴含着着库布里克想法的\NAnd this deeper story has its birth, I guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.33,0:54:18.17,中英,,0,0,0,,更深层次的故事\Nin the idea that Stanley Kubrick
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.17,0:54:22.04,中英,,0,0,0,,我认为和阿波罗登月造假有关\Nwas involved with faking the Apollo moon landings.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.05,0:54:24.76,中英,,0,0,0,,事实上 我主张 某种程度上 《2001：太空漫游》\NIn fact, I contend that 2001: A Space Odyssey,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.76,0:54:27.97,中英,,0,0,0,,是为了阿波罗影像的需要\Nin part, was a research and development project
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.97,0:54:30.52,中英,,0,0,0,,而研究 发展的项目\Nfor the Apollo footage that was shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.52,0:54:32.64,中英,,0,0,0,,我并不是说我们从未上过月球\NI'm not saying we didn't go to the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.64,0:54:34.89,中英,,0,0,0,,我是指 我们所看到的 是假的\NI'm just saying that what we saw was faked
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.89,0:54:37.69,中英,,0,0,0,,我们被库布里克蒙骗了\Nand that it was faked by Stanley Kubrick.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.69,0:54:40.23,中英,,0,0,0,,60到70年代的好莱坞\NAnd I've had Hollywood special effects people
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.23,0:54:44.15,中英,,0,0,0,,前屏特效专家告诉我\Nfrom the '60s and '70s who were front-screen projection experts
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.15,0:54:47.95,中英,,0,0,0,,我完全揭露除了阿波罗登月影像\Ntell me that I absolutely have nailed the Apollo footage
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.95,0:54:51.87,中英,,0,0,0,,是视频特效的结果\Nas being the result of front-screen projection.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.87,0:54:54.37,中英,,0,0,0,,只要浏览任何阿波罗的页面\NJust go to any Apollo site and look,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.37,0:54:59.04,中英,,0,0,0,,你都会发现 他们挡住了视频的底部\Nand you'll see that they have to hide the bottom of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.04,0:55:03.17,中英,,0,0,0,,你在每一个阿波罗的影像 照片中\NAnd you can always see the set/screen separation line
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.17,0:55:07.13,中英,,0,0,0,,你总能看到菜单和视频之间的分界线\Nin every Apollo footage,every Apollo image,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.13,0:55:11.14,中英,,0,0,0,,视频影像总有一个背景\Nand the video footage that has a background.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.14,0:55:13.97,中英,,0,0,0,,研究者理查德·霍格兰\NAnd Richard Hoagland,the researcher,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.97,0:55:15.94,中英,,0,0,0,,调查了阿波罗登月的照片\Nhas looked into the Apollo imagery.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.94,0:55:19.31,中英,,0,0,0,,他找出了各种各样的问题\NAnd he has found all sorts of problems with it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.31,0:55:21.56,中英,,0,0,0,,比如在宇航员周围的天空里\Nbecause in the sky around the astronauts,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.57,0:55:26.90,中英,,0,0,0,,他发现了灯光的反射和其他东西的折射\Nhe's found reflecting lights and refracting things and...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.90,0:55:31.07,中英,,0,0,0,,一种舢板船几何形的物体\Nkind of a junk and geometry of things that are in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.07,0:55:33.87,中英,,0,0,0,,但他也错误地总结出\NAnd he concluded, wrongly,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.87,0:55:38.25,中英,,0,0,0,,太空里有玻璃制成的巨大外星城市\Nthat there are gigantic alien cities made out of glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.25,0:55:42.42,中英,,0,0,0,,他觉得自己看到的是玻璃屏幕上\NWhat he's really seeing is the reflections of light
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.42,0:55:46.63,中英,,0,0,0,,细小玻璃粉的反光\Nof the tiny beads on the scotch light screen
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.63,0:55:50.18,中英,,0,0,0,,而那块玻璃是用来前屏的投影转换处理的\Nwhich is being used in the front-screen projection process.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.18,0:55:54.80,中英,,0,0,0,,并且 我仔细研究过阿波罗影像资料的\NAnd so, once I nailed the front-screen projection process
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.81,0:55:57.85,中英,,0,0,0,,前屏的投影转换\Ninside the Apollo footage,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.85,0:56:02.56,中英,,0,0,0,,然后我对库布里克是否在他后来的作品里\Nthen I became interested in seeing if Kubrick left any clues
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.56,0:56:06.19,中英,,0,0,0,,留下过任何关于阿波罗登月\Nin the rest of his career to his possible involvement
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.19,0:56:08.86,中英,,0,0,0,,是自己造假的线索 产生了兴趣\Nin faking the Apollo moon footage.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.86,0:56:14.37,中英,,0,0,0,,而大概在两年前 当我收到\NAnd I was overjoyed about two years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.37,0:56:18.49,中英,,0,0,0,,《闪灵》的蓝光碟时 我乐坏了\Nwhen I received my Blue-Ray copy of The Shining.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.50,0:56:20.84,中英,,0,0,0,,我用蓝光机播放了它\NAnd I put it in my Blue-Ray machine
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.84,0:56:23.21,中英,,0,0,0,,坐下看了一整夜\Nand sat down one night to watch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.21,0:56:29.21,中英,,0,0,0,,我想象了任何库布里克可能使用过的\NAnd I realized that all of the things that one could imagine
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.21,0:56:31.89,中英,,0,0,0,,关于阿波罗登月视频影像\Nthat Stanley Kubrick would have had to go through
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.89,0:56:35.26,中英,,0,0,0,,造假的事物\Nto fake the Apollo moon footage...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.26,0:56:36.73,中英,,0,0,0,,而在电影中\Nand there in the movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.73,0:56:41.10,中英,,0,0,0,,每一次库布里克对史蒂芬金的小说有所改动\Nevery time that Stanley deviated from the Stephen King novel,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.10,0:56:44.52,中英,,0,0,0,,他也会加入一些新的问题\Nhe deviated into those exact questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.52,0:56:46.77,中英,,0,0,0,,比如 与美国政府打交道的感觉\NYou know, what was it like to make a deal
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.78,0:56:48.20,中英,,0,0,0,,是什么样的？\Nwith the U.S. Government?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.20,0:56:53.24,中英,,0,0,0,,无意间透露了自己正在做的事情\NWhat was it like to accidentally tell someone what you were doing
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.24,0:56:57.37,中英,,0,0,0,,然后看着人们取笑你的不诚实\Nand to watch them possibly have to suffer the consequences
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.37,0:56:59.33,中英,,0,0,0,,这种感觉是什么样的？\Nof your lack of integrity?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.33,0:57:03.33,中英,,0,0,0,,欺骗自己的妻子\NWhat was it like to lie to your wife
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.33,0:57:05.50,中英,,0,0,0,,为自己的言行不一找借口\Nand tell her that you were doing one thing
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.50,0:57:07.05,中英,,0,0,0,,这种感觉是什么样的？\Nwhen you were doing another?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.05,0:57:09.51,中英,,0,0,0,,而当妻子发现你暗地里在做的事情时\NWhat was it like when your wife found out
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.51,0:57:11.26,中英,,0,0,0,,这种感觉又是什么样的？\Nwhat you were really doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.26,0:57:14.18,中英,,0,0,0,,这些问题就是在我八九年之后\NThese are the questions that I had long before
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.18,0:57:15.43,中英,,0,0,0,,再看《闪灵》时\NI had seen The Shining again
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.43,0:57:18.56,中英,,0,0,0,,所想知道的\Nafter a maybe an eight...or nine-year absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.56,0:57:23.02,中英,,0,0,0,,我在电影的前一个小时里 并没有找到答案\NAnd I didn't... wasn't sure I was right for the first hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.02,0:57:25.27,中英,,0,0,0,,我不知道自己是否...\NI wasn't sure that I had actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.27,0:57:27.74,中英,,0,0,0,,是否模糊了\Nyou know, I wasn't sure if I was blurring the line
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.74,0:57:32.03,中英,,0,0,0,,自己想看到的和正在看的\Nbetween what I wanted to see and what I was seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.03,0:57:34.70,中英,,0,0,0,,而在电影的58分钟\NAnd then at about 58 minutes in the film
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.70,0:57:37.95,中英,,0,0,0,,是丹尼在玩玩具车时的那个著名场景\Nis the famous scene where Danny's playing with his trucks,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.95,0:57:39.95,中英,,0,0,0,,然后他站了起来\Nand he stands up
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.95,0:57:41.70,中英,,0,0,0,,而他当时穿的毛衣上 印着\Nand he's wearing the Apollo 11 sweater
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.71,0:57:43.62,中英,,0,0,0,,即将升空的阿波罗十一号\Nwith the rocket taking off.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.62,0:57:46.54,中英,,0,0,0,,我知道自己捕捉到了它\NThen I knew I'd nabbed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.54,0:57:50.46,中英,,0,0,0,,之后 我带着热情 继续看这部电影\NAnd then I started watching the film with an intensity
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.46,0:57:53.06,中英,,0,0,0,,就当从未看过一样\Nthat I don't think I'd ever watched a movie before,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.06,0:57:56.88,中英,,0,0,0,,然后发现每一句台词都显得真实\Nand every line began ringing true.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.89,0:58:02.01,中英,,0,0,0,,比如 "温迪 这真像你做出的事\NYou know, "Wendy, that is just so typical of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.02,0:58:03.36,中英,,0,0,0,,你难道...你难道不知道\NDon't you... don't you know
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.36,0:58:05.89,中英,,0,0,0,,我要尽到一个员工的职责吗？\NI have obligations to my employers?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.89,0:58:09.02,中英,,0,0,0,,你知道协议是什么意思吗?\NDo you have any idea what a contract is?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.02,0:58:11.07,中英,,0,0,0,,你知道合同是什么意思吗？"\NDo you know what an agreement is?"
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.07,0:58:15.36,中英,,0,0,0,,杰克·尼克尔森（应该说杰克·托伦斯）对妻子的的长篇大论\NJack Nicholson's whole tirade against his wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.36,0:58:17.70,中英,,0,0,0,,这是史丹利\Nthat's Stanley.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.70,0:58:21.62,中英,,0,0,0,,这是史丹利在告诉前妻 在他们离婚后\NThat's Stanley telling his wife that after she discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.62,0:58:24.59,中英,,0,0,0,,自己正在忙活的 是在制作阿波罗等于影像\Nwhat he was doing,which was the Apollo footage.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.52,0:58:37.78,中英,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&}库布里克曾说 在所取景的酒店的请求下 \N他将原作中的“217房间”改为了“237房间”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.78,0:58:44.75,中英,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&}由于酒店的确有217号房间\N他们担心顾客看过《闪灵》之后 不敢入住
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.75,0:58:59.01,大,,0,0,0,,{\pos(397,502)}{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&}林 线 酒 店\N胡德山 俄勒冈州
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.89,0:58:46.31,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,719)}不 这不是真的\NNo, that's actually not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.31,0:58:48.77,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(642,719)}如果你打给度假酒店\NIf you call the Mount Hood Resort
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.77,0:58:50.81,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,719)}预订217房间\Nand you ask for room 217
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.81,0:58:53.16,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,719)}你会被告知 没有这间客房\Nyou will find there is no such room.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.16,0:58:54.94,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(644,719)}因此 库布里克说的是假的\NSo that's just not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.94,0:58:56.99,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(636,719)}那个说法是假的\NThat statement's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.99,0:59:00.85,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,719)}所以...\NAnd so what...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.87,0:59:02.45,中英,,0,0,0,,史丹在说谎\NStanley was lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.45,0:59:04.62,中英,,0,0,0,,从217改为237并不是\NIts not the reason that he changed the room number
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.63,0:59:07.66,中英,,0,0,0,,那个原因\Nfrom 217 to 237.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.66,0:59:11.46,中英,,0,0,0,,他这么做\NThe reason that he changed it from 217 to 237
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.46,0:59:17.17,中英,,0,0,0,,是因为 电影中的237房间...\Nwas because the room,room 237 in the film is...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.17,0:59:20.90,中英,,0,0,0,,代表了他所在的登月工作室\Nrepresents the moon landing stage where he worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.06,0:59:30.52,中英,,0,0,0,,而关于月球 科学教材里说到...\NAnd the moon, the standard science textbook said...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.52,0:59:32.02,中英,,0,0,0,,并且现在也这么说...\Nand they still say...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.02,0:59:35.15,中英,,0,0,0,,尽管现在有了激光测距 我们可以更精确\Nbut now with lasers, we've gotten a little better reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.15,0:59:39.78,中英,,0,0,0,,但是...书上写到 月球\NBut... is that the mean distance of the moon
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.78,0:59:44.03,中英,,0,0,0,,到地球之间的距离 刚好是237,000英里\Nfrom the earth is exactly 237,000 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.03,0:59:47.21,中英,,0,0,0,,因此 他做出这样的改变是为了让你认识到\NSo he changed that so that you would understand
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.21,0:59:49.46,中英,,0,0,0,,这是一间月舍\Nthat this was the moon room.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.46,0:59:51.17,中英,,0,0,0,,因此 当丹尼站起来\NSo Danny stands up.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.17,0:59:53.58,中英,,0,0,0,,他穿着阿波罗十一号的毛衣\NHe's got the Apollo 11 sweater on.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.59,0:59:58.76,中英,,0,0,0,,开始走向237房间\NHe begins walking down the hallway towards room 237.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.76,1:00:01.68,中英,,0,0,0,,在门锁上 插着钥匙\NAnd there's a key in the lock.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.68,1:00:03.55,中英,,0,0,0,,在钥匙上...\NAnd on the key are...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.55,1:00:07.97,中英,,0,0,0,,写着词语"房间"和"不"\Nis the words "room" and then the word "n-o,"
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.97,1:00:11.48,中英,,0,0,0,,英语里 "号"的缩写是"不"\Nwhich is an old acronym for "number."
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.48,1:00:13.19,中英,,0,0,0,,因此这是237房间\NSo "room number 237,"
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.19,1:00:16.11,中英,,0,0,0,,除此之外 钥匙上的大写字母分别是\Nexcept that the only capital letters on the key
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.11,1:00:20.57,中英,,0,0,0,,R-O-O-M 和N-O里的N\Nare r-o-o-m and then the "n" from the acronym n-o.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.57,1:00:23.91,中英,,0,0,0,,而此时 你所能想到的带这些字母的单词\NAnd if there's only two words that you can come up with
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.91,1:00:25.95,中英,,0,0,0,,只有两个\Nthat have those letters in 'em.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.95,1:00:27.70,中英,,0,0,0,,那就是"月亮"和"房间"\NAnd that's "moon" and "room."
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.70,1:00:32.96,中英,,0,0,0,,因此钥匙上写着的就是"月亮屋"\NAnd so on the key, the tag,it says "moon room."
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.96,1:00:34.38,中英,,0,0,0,,就是月舍了\NAnd that is the moon room.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.38,1:00:35.75,中英,,0,0,0,,这就是一切都会发生的地方\NThis is where everything happens,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.75,1:00:37.29,中英,,0,0,0,,但不能是真实的\Nand none of it's real.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.30,1:00:39.55,中英,,0,0,0,,它们必须被谎言掩盖\NAnd it all has to be lied about.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.55,1:00:42.30,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克不能让人知道237房间\NAnd he can't let anyone know what's really going on
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.30,1:00:44.93,中英,,0,0,0,,到底发生了什么\Nin room 237.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.93,1:00:48.93,中英,,0,0,0,,此外 电影中还有很多对原作\NAnd there's many, many other deviations from the book
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.93,1:00:50.06,中英,,0,0,0,,改动的地方\Nto the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.06,1:00:51.73,中英,,0,0,0,,- 这是真的\N- It isn't real.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.73,1:00:54.78,中英,,0,0,0,,- 这些改动让史蒂芬·金抓狂了\N- The deviations drove Stephen King out of his mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.78,1:00:57.48,中英,,0,0,0,,这么多年来 他一直痛骂《闪灵》\NHe just ranted and ranted for years
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.48,1:00:59.57,中英,,0,0,0,,咆哮着有多痛恨它\Nhow much he hated The Shining.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.57,1:01:01.45,中英,,0,0,0,,他痛恨是因为 他给了库布里克\NAnd he hated it because he'd given Kubrick
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.45,1:01:02.95,中英,,0,0,0,,如此好的拍摄题材\Nall this great source material
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.95,1:01:05.57,中英,,0,0,0,,但他却丢弃了\Nand Kubrick threw it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.57,1:01:10.70,中英,,0,0,0,,而这最好的证明就是\NAnd the whole idea of this is best exemplified
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.70,1:01:15.00,中英,,0,0,0,,迪克·哈洛伦在高速上开车的场景\Nby the scene where Dick Hallorann  is driving up the highway,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.00,1:01:18.00,中英,,0,0,0,,暴风雪中 开往远望酒店的路上\Ntrying to get to the Overlook during a winter storm
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.01,1:01:20.25,中英,,0,0,0,,他路过了一起车祸\Nand he passes a wreck.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.26,1:01:23.42,中英,,0,0,0,,车祸现场是一辆挂车\NAnd in the wreck,a semi has crashed
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.43,1:01:27.22,中英,,0,0,0,,压在一辆红色的大众轿车上面\Nand crushed a red Volkswagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.22,1:01:31.10,中英,,0,0,0,,这是一个库布里克向史蒂芬发出的直接信息\NAnd this is a direct message from Kubrick to King,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.10,1:01:33.27,中英,,0,0,0,,因为在小说中\Nbecause in the novel,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.27,1:01:36.73,中英,,0,0,0,,杰克·托伦斯的车是红色大众\NJack Torrance's car is a red Volkswagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.73,1:01:39.15,中英,,0,0,0,,但是在电影里 却是黄色大众\NBut in the movie,it's a yellow Volkswagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.15,1:01:41.62,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克这是在对史蒂芬·金说\NAnd what Kubrick is saying in that scene
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.62,1:01:44.74,中英,,0,0,0,,**大爷\Nis a big "F you"to Stephen King.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.74,1:01:47.91,中英,,0,0,0,,他在说 这是老子的车\NHe's saying,This is my vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.91,1:01:49.95,中英,,0,0,0,,"我已经把你的车撞飞了\N"I have wrecked your vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.95,1:01:52.91,中英,,0,0,0,,世人见证 我将你打败\NAnd everybody in the world can see it.'
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.91,1:01:54.63,中英,,0,0,0,,这让史蒂芬炸毛\NAnd this drove King crazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.63,1:01:56.29,中英,,0,0,0,,理应如此\NAnd it should have.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.29,1:01:57.79,中英,,0,0,0,,但现实所发生的\NBut what was really going on
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.79,1:02:03.96,中英,,0,0,0,,以及关于这一切可以让人联想的\Nand what is just much more deliciously fascinating
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.97,1:02:07.26,中英,,0,0,0,,事实上 是在表达\Nabout all of this is that, in fact,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.26,1:02:11.56,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克 打着拍摄史蒂芬金小说的幌子\NKubrick was faking the making of the Stephen King novel
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.56,1:02:15.48,中英,,0,0,0,,实际上是在泄露关于他制造\Nin order to reveal the idea of what he went through
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.48,1:02:17.95,中英,,0,0,0,,阿波罗登月影像的经历\Nto do the Apollo moon footage.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.63,1:02:26.13,大,,0,0,0,,{\pos(616,640)}通往墓地的电梯
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.57,1:02:29.49,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我认为 库布里克是一个\N- My argument,as far as Kubrick goes,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.49,1:02:32.84,中英,,0,0,0,,观察力逆天的小孩\Nis that he was a preternaturally observant child.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.84,1:02:35.00,中英,,0,0,0,,他一直在观察\NHe read omnivorously.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.00,1:02:37.16,中英,,0,0,0,,他一直都去电影院\NHe went to movies all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.17,1:02:41.09,中英,,0,0,0,,我相信 如果你看三十 四十年代的电影\NAnd I think if you're going to movies and reading in the 1930s
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.09,1:02:45.21,中英,,0,0,0,,你会发现你看到的都是关于\Nand the 1940s, a lot of what you're seeing and reading
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.22,1:02:49.22,中英,,0,0,0,,希特勒 纳粹以及战争题材的\Nis Hitler and the Nazis and the war.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.22,1:02:55.52,中英,,0,0,0,,因此 作为一个敏锐的小孩 他对这些一定很敏感\NSo as a sensitive kid, he must have been alive to these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.52,1:02:58.61,中英,,0,0,0,,我不认为他曾忽略过这些\NAnd I don't think he ever forgot anything, and this is...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.61,1:03:01.15,中英,,0,0,0,,所以他的电影内容丰富\Nwhich is why his films are so rich.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.36,1:03:04.86,中英,,0,0,0,,- 小猪 小猪\N- Little pigs, little pigs,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.86,1:03:06.83,中英,,0,0,0,,让我进去\Nlet me come in.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.57,1:03:11.62,中英,,0,0,0,,不要啰嗦 不要说话\NNot by the hair on your chinny-chin-chin?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.58,1:03:17.54,中英,,0,0,0,,我吹 我吹 我用力的吹\NThen I'll huff and I'll puff...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.54,1:03:19.08,中英,,0,0,0,,- 吹倒你的屋子吃了你\N- And I'll blow your house in!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.08,1:03:20.30,中英,,0,0,0,,- 《三只小猪》\N - Well,The Three Little Pigs,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.30,1:03:21.92,中英,,0,0,0,,我是说 我不记得...\NI mean, I don't remember...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.92,1:03:24.47,中英,,0,0,0,,这也许是杰克·尼克尔森\NThat might have been one of the things
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.47,1:03:29.09,中英,,0,0,0,,诸多临场发挥的场景之一\Nthat Jack Nicholson might've ad-libbed initially.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.09,1:03:30.89,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克是即兴发挥的虔诚者\NKubrick was a great believer in that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.89,1:03:34.31,中英,,0,0,0,,但就算这是临场发挥 我觉得\NBut even if it was,I think the selection
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.31,1:03:38.31,中英,,0,0,0,,对那段儿歌的选择\Nof that particular little rhyme
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.31,1:03:41.77,中英,,0,0,0,,是非常适合当时氛围的\Ncertainly fits in with the time periodization
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.77,1:03:43.36,中英,,0,0,0,,我的意思是说\NI've just been talking about,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.37,1:03:47.28,中英,,0,0,0,,当库布里克在这个场景里\Nbecause Kubrick would've run across that
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.28,1:03:49.53,中英,,0,0,0,,联想到了在1933年（应是1934年）\Nwhen he saw The Three Little Pigs
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.53,1:03:53.41,中英,,0,0,0,,获得奥斯卡最佳动画的电影 《三只小猪》\Nas an Academy Award winning cartoon in 1933.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.41,1:03:56.74,中英,,0,0,0,,电影诞生在那个特殊的时期\NAnd so it comes out of that period.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.75,1:04:01.71,中英,,0,0,0,,因此 在三十年代 狼的意象\NAnd so the whole idea of a wolf,which, during the 1930s,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.71,1:04:08.26,中英,,0,0,0,,渐渐从它本身作为\Ngradually transformed itself in popular mythology
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.26,1:04:11.09,中英,,0,0,0,,大萧条时期 人所皆知的\Nand popular culture from being a symbol
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.09,1:04:16.18,中英,,0,0,0,,饥饿 欲望的符号\Nof want and of hunger in the Great Depression
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.18,1:04:19.73,中英,,0,0,0,,转变成了敌人的象征\Ninto a symbol of enemies;
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.73,1:04:22.60,中英,,0,0,0,,敌人 敌国\NEnemy nations,enemy peoples,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.60,1:04:23.90,中英,,0,0,0,,军事侵略\Nmilitary aggression.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.90,1:04:26.82,中英,,0,0,0,,当然 这也反映了 法西斯和纳粹\NAnd of course, this reflects the rise of fascism
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.82,1:04:28.11,中英,,0,0,0,,在欧洲的崛起\Nand Nazis in Europe.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.11,1:04:31.45,中英,,0,0,0,,但是 门前的狼\NBut initially,the wolf at the door
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.45,1:04:35.95,中英,,0,0,0,,最开始是讽刺以及反犹太的象征\Nwas an anti-Semitic stereotype and caricature
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.95,1:04:39.91,中英,,0,0,0,,一开始 狼伪装自己\Nthat... initially the wolf wears a disguise.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.91,1:04:41.13,中英,,0,0,0,,而背景音乐明显是\NAnd the background music
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.13,1:04:44.67,中英,,0,0,0,,东欧的犹太人演奏的乐曲\Nis clearly Eastern European sort of klezmer
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.67,1:04:46.29,中英,,0,0,0,,或是意第绪音乐\Nor Yiddish music.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.29,1:04:49.09,中英,,0,0,0,,而在三十年代 这是一个典型的\NAnd it's a classic example
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.09,1:04:53.43,中英,,0,0,0,,迪士尼动画反犹太的例子\Nof early 1930s Walt Disney anti-Semitism.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.43,1:04:56.47,中英,,0,0,0,,所以我认为 在《三只小猪》中\NSo I think there are layers of meaning
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.47,1:04:58.31,中英,,0,0,0,,有着多层含义\Nin The Three Little Pigs."
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.31,1:05:04.60,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(667,18)}*奥地利犹太心理学家、精神病医师
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.31,1:05:00.31,中英,,0,0,0,,此外 库布里克相信弗洛伊德*学说\NAnd since Kubrick was a Freudian
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.31,1:05:04.60,中英,,0,0,0,,我们也知道 他在《闪灵》的剧本中\Nand we know that he used Freudian work
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.60,1:05:07.53,中英,,0,0,0,,使用了弗洛伊德的研究成果\Nin doing the screenplay for The Shining...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.53,1:05:10.78,中英,,0,0,0,,比如 布鲁诺·贝托尔海姆*的著作《童话的魅力》...\NBruno Bettelheim's The Uses of Enchantment...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.53,1:05:10.78,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(627,18)}*美国心理学家
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.78,1:05:14.45,中英,,0,0,0,,这是弗洛伊德学派对童话意义的分析\Nand it's a Freudian analysis of the meaning of fairy tales.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.45,1:05:17.16,中英,,0,0,0,,在《闪灵》中 当他们频繁的引用\NAnd in The Shining,we can see the fruits of that
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.16,1:05:20.33,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(634,18)}*德国童话
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.16,1:05:20.33,中英,,0,0,0,,《糖果屋历险记》*时 我们可以看到其成果\Nwhen they're constantly making references to Hansel and Gretel.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.33,1:05:21.88,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我感觉我每次到这 都要在身后\N- I feel like I'll have to leave a trail of bread crumbs
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.88,1:05:23.71,中英,,0,0,0,,丢下面包屑才行\Nevery time we come in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.71,1:05:25.83,中英,,0,0,0,,浴缸里的巫婆 小孩被炙烤等等\N- The witch in the oven and children being burned
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.83,1:05:27.30,中英,,0,0,0,,这些应该都是\Nand so forth,which of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.30,1:05:31.22,中英,,0,0,0,,对大屠杀的暗示\Nis also perhaps, suggestive when it comes to the Holocaust.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.18,1:05:37.77,中英,,0,0,0,,血涌应该是几个恐怖场景之一\N- The blood is one of the main ghosts
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.77,1:05:39.81,中英,,0,0,0,,甚至是这部电影中\Nand perhaps the overarching ghost,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.81,1:05:41.52,中英,,0,0,0,,最重要的一个场景\Nin a certain sense,in this movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.52,1:05:45.10,中英,,0,0,0,,我们第一次看到血涌是在电影的开头\NWe first see it when Danny,at the beginning of the movie,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.10,1:05:46.57,中英,,0,0,0,,当丹尼在丹佛或者博尔德的公寓里\Nis at the sink in the little apartment
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.57,1:05:50.86,中英,,0,0,0,,水槽的旁边\Ndown in Denver or Boulder or wherever it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.86,1:05:52.24,中英,,0,0,0,,托尼在和丹尼交谈\NAnd he's talking to Danny,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.24,1:05:53.86,中英,,0,0,0,,"你为什么不想去那儿?"\N"Why don't you want to go there?"
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.41,1:06:00.04,中英,,0,0,0,,接着突然 丹尼给他看了血涌\NAnd then suddenly Danny shows him blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.04,1:06:03.75,中英,,0,0,0,,后来我们知道\NAnd as we learn a little bit later,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.75,1:06:06.67,中英,,0,0,0,,远望酒店是于1907到1909年之间建在\Nthe Overlook was built on the Indian burial ground
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.67,1:06:08.33,中英,,0,0,0,,印第安坟地上的\Nbetween 1907 and 1909.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.33,1:06:10.84,中英,,0,0,0,,- 1907年开始建造\N- Construction started in 1907.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.84,1:06:13.01,中英,,0,0,0,,1909年竣工\NIt was finished in 1909.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.01,1:06:14.35,中英,,0,0,0,,这个地方是\NThe site is supposed to be located
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.35,1:06:15.72,中英,,0,0,0,,印第安人的墓场\Non an Indian burial ground,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.72,1:06:17.14,中英,,0,0,0,,我也相信 他们在建造时\Nand I believe they actually had
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.14,1:06:19.68,中英,,0,0,0,,击退过一些印第安人的攻击\Nto repel a few Indian attacks as they were building it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.60,1:06:24.60,中英,,0,0,0,,- 因此 我们可以想象出\N- So presumably,we can imagine the elevator
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.60,1:06:27.95,中英,,0,0,0,,电梯是可以下降到印第安人的\Nshaft sinks down into the very bodies of the Indians,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.95,1:06:29.15,中英,,0,0,0,,坟地里的\Nso to speak.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.15,1:06:31.15,中英,,0,0,0,,这也就是涌血的出处了\NAnd that's where the blood is coming from;
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.15,1:06:33.12,中英,,0,0,0,,是印第安人的血\NLiteral blood of the Indians.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.75,1:06:52.30,中英,,0,0,0,,除了别的之外 这也是一部关于\NAnd this movie is a movie about,among other things,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.30,1:06:55.21,中英,,0,0,0,,血肉筑城的国家的电影\Nthe blood on which nations are built;
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.22,1:06:56.39,中英,,0,0,0,,没错 是关于有着\NCertainly the United States,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.39,1:06:59.10,中英,,0,0,0,,印第安人大屠杀历史的美国的\Nwith the genocide of the American Indians.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.10,1:07:00.93,中英,,0,0,0,,但不仅仅这样\NBut it's not only that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.93,1:07:04.27,中英,,0,0,0,,这也是库布里克那说个不停的暗示\NThis is a complete metaphor for what Kubrick is on about,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.28,1:07:08.56,中英,,0,0,0,,因为电梯的门一直是关着的\Nbecause the elevator's doors remain closed.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.56,1:07:10.73,中英,,0,0,0,,用其他的话说 这就是\NIn other words,it's as if it's like a symbol
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.73,1:07:11.94,中英,,0,0,0,,压抑\Nof the repression.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.95,1:07:13.40,中英,,0,0,0,,我们不愿承认\NWe don't want to admit to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.41,1:07:16.87,中英,,0,0,0,,尽管我们说这是压抑\NBut in spite of our attempting to stay repressed about it,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.87,1:07:18.59,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(653,18)}*中世纪英国诗人
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.87,1:07:18.61,中英,,0,0,0,,就像乔叟*说的\Nblood will out,murder will out,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.61,1:07:24.29,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(682,18)}其实就是纸包不住火的意思...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.61,1:07:20.58,中英,,0,0,0,,笺草难御火 吾血终横流\Nas Chaucer says in one of his tales.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.58,1:07:26.29,中英,,0,0,0,,所以血从边缘中被挤压出\NAnd so the blood comes squeezing out from the side
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.29,1:07:27.96,中英,,0,0,0,,淹没了我们\Nand overwhelms us.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.96,1:07:31.68,中英,,0,0,0,,接着在电影中它一次又一次的出现\NAnd it keeps recurring over and over through the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.68,1:07:33.29,中英,,0,0,0,,它...\NAnd it's...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.29,1:07:36.39,中英,,0,0,0,,在影片的最后 温迪\NAnd finally Wendy, when,at the very end of the movie,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.39,1:07:37.88,中英,,0,0,0,,她开始看到了鬼怪\Nshe starts seeing ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.88,1:07:39.13,中英,,0,0,0,,她看到了血涌\NShe sees the blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.14,1:07:43.14,中英,,0,0,0,,这是我们普遍共同点的象征\NIt's the symbol of what we all have in common.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.14,1:07:44.35,中英,,0,0,0,,电影里还有很多\NAnd there's lots of symbols in here
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.36,1:07:45.89,中英,,0,0,0,,关于人类共性的符号\Nof what all humans have in common.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.35,1:07:52.44,中英,,0,0,0,,- 数字42在其它方也出现过\N- 42 shows up in other places.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.44,1:07:56.90,中英,,0,0,0,,温迪和丹尼在酒店的电视上\NWendy and Danny watch The Summer of '42
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.44,1:07:58.38,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(641,18)}*英文名中有数字"42"\N这一段貌似欧洲版也被剪了
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.90,1:07:58.40,中英,,0,0,0,,在看《往事如烟》*\Non a hotel television.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.40,1:08:00.99,中英,,0,0,0,,此外 还有许多\NAnd there are a number of other
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.99,1:08:03.12,中英,,0,0,0,,关于这个数字的暗示\Nlittle references to that number.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.12,1:08:08.83,大3,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&\pos(646,307)}{\pos(927.000000,378.000000)}停车场上有42辆轿车/货车{
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.12,1:08:05.24,大,,0,0,0,,{\pos(936.000000,858.000000)}联系整部电影 库布里克\NAnd it's within a larger context
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.25,1:08:08.83,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(975.000000,858.000000)}使用了许多有关联的数字\Nthat Kubrick uses involving numbers in The Shining.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.83,1:08:11.00,中英,,0,0,0,,它们都是7的倍数\NAnd they're all multiples of seven.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.00,1:08:14.33,中英,,0,0,0,,酒店建于1907年\NThe hotel was built in 1907.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.34,1:08:17.64,中英,,0,0,0,,在电影最后 杰克合影留念的派对\NThe party in which Jack is pictured at the end of film
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.64,1:08:21.47,中英,,0,0,0,,在1921年7月举办\Noccurred in 1921 in July,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.47,1:08:24.01,中英,,0,0,0,,那一年的第七个月\Nthe seventh month of the year.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.01,1:08:29.77,中英,,0,0,0,,这些与7相关的数字 我认为\NThese multiples of seven,I think,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.77,1:08:30.94,中英,,0,0,0,,反映出一个事实\Nalso reflect the fact
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.96,1:08:34.15,中英,,0,0,0,,that Kubrick was aware of the importance
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.96,1:08:34.15,中英,,0,0,0,,那就是库布里克知道托马斯曼*
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.96,1:08:34.13,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(615,18)}*德国作家
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.15,1:08:38.03,中英,,0,0,0,,1924年的小说 《魔山》的的重要性\Nof Thomas Mann's novel of 1924,The Magic Mountain,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.03,1:08:41.03,中英,,0,0,0,,一部关于一所造在高山上的疗养院的小说\Nwhich similarly concerns a sanitarium...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.03,1:08:44.57,中英,,0,0,0,,尽管不是酒店 但很相似\Nthough not a hotel...high up in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.60,1:08:51.62,中英,,0,0,0,,托马斯·曼使用7这个数字 \NAnd Mann uses the number 7 there as a matter,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.35,1:08:53.48,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(615,515)}德语:魔山
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.62,1:08:56.75,中英,,0,0,0,,作为一个符号 来象征危险命运\Na symbol of the sort of dangerous fate
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.75,1:09:00.22,中英,,0,0,0,,一步步靠近欧洲\Nthat seems to have been stalking Europe lately.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.43,1:09:13.64,中英,,0,0,0,,在小说《洛丽塔》中 纳博科夫使用42\NAnd in the novel Lolita,Nabokov uses the number 42
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.65,1:09:17.11,中英,,0,0,0,,来作为亨伯特的命运和偏执病的象征\Nas a symbol of fate and Humbert's paranoia,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.11,1:09:21.53,中英,,0,0,0,,来表达他画地为牢的生活状态\Nthe idea that he is constantly being tracked and that his life is doomed.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.53,1:09:24.86,中英,,0,0,0,,尽管库布里克在电影《洛丽塔》中\NAnd even though Kubrick,in his film of Lolita,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.86,1:09:27.28,中英,,0,0,0,,只在酒店房间的门上\Nonly uses the number once,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.28,1:09:30.08,中英,,0,0,0,,饶有趣味地使用了一次数字42\Ninterestingly enough on a hotel room door,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.08,1:09:32.71,中英,,0,0,0,,我觉得从某种程度上来说\NI think at some level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.71,1:09:36.46,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克一直在模仿纳博科夫\NKubrick was always also drawing from Nabokov's use
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.46,1:09:38.29,中英,,0,0,0,,对那个特殊数字的使用\Nof that particular number
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.29,1:09:44.60,中英,,0,0,0,,将它作为一种危险 怨恨 甚至一种灾难\Nas a symbol of danger and malevolence and disaster.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.81,1:09:53.23,中英,,0,0,0,,- 影片开始时的背景乐取自安魂曲中\N- The opening sound is from the great funeral mass,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.23,1:09:56.10,中英,,0,0,0,,末日经唱段 意思是审判日\NDies Irae,which is the day of judgment,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.10,1:09:58.15,中英,,0,0,0,,曲中宣称 "葬礼即将到来\Nwhich announces,"This is going to be a funeral.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.15,1:10:00.49,中英,,0,0,0,,这会是全人类的审判日"\NThis is going to be about a judgment on the human race."
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.49,1:10:02.15,中英,,0,0,0,,这是关于过去的\NIt's about the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.15,1:10:05.70,中英,,0,0,0,,但我记得\NBut I think I remembered
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.70,1:10:09.20,中英,,0,0,0,,我对开场的印象\Nthat my impression from the opening scene
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.20,1:10:11.50,中英,,0,0,0,,那段航拍的镜头\Nin which that astonishing helicopter shot
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.50,1:10:13.62,中英,,0,0,0,,让我感到毛骨悚然\Ngives you a totally creepy feeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.62,1:10:16.96,中英,,0,0,0,,你正欣赏着美丽的自然风光\NYou're looking at great,beautiful nature,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.96,1:10:19.34,中英,,0,0,0,,但你感觉你在追随着什么\Nbut you know you're following something.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.34,1:10:20.59,中英,,0,0,0,,你就像...\NYou're, like, flying along
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.59,1:10:24.30,中英,,0,0,0,,在一辆渺小汽车的上空 追着它飞\Non top of this little,tiny, insignificant car.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.30,1:10:26.51,中英,,0,0,0,,尽管没有写出这段镜头的拍摄者\NIt's the ultimate point of view shot
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.51,1:10:28.97,中英,,0,0,0,,但它是非常极致的画面展现\Nwithout telling you who the point of view is.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.97,1:10:30.31,中英,,0,0,0,,如果你想暂停然后思考\NIf you want to stop and think about it,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.31,1:10:32.39,中英,,0,0,0,,你会想 "这是一段航拍镜头"\Nyou think,'This is a helicopter shot"
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.40,1:10:33.60,中英,,0,0,0,,但对于普通观众来说\NBut for the general audience,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.60,1:10:35.73,中英,,0,0,0,,你只会觉得自己就像一个游魂\Nall you know is that you are like a ghost.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.73,1:10:37.15,中英,,0,0,0,,你像一个天使\NYou are like an angel.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.15,1:10:38.27,中英,,0,0,0,,你就像一个\NYou are like something
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.27,1:10:41.02,中英,,0,0,0,,有着超能力的神奇飞侠\Nthat flies with supernatural abilities
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.02,1:10:44.32,中英,,0,0,0,,览尽这个星球的风光\Nacross the landscape of the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.32,1:10:48.32,中英,,0,0,0,,还有那飞掠而过的声音...\NAnd the soundtrack had that skittering...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.32,1:10:49.57,中英,,0,0,0,,我没有办法模仿出来\NI can't imitate it...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.57,1:10:52.20,中英,,0,0,0,,但是那个声音听起来就像...\Nbut that skittering music that sounded to me...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.20,1:10:54.50,中英,,0,0,0,,我第一次看这部电影就有这种感觉...\Nand I was conscious of this the first time I saw the movie...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.50,1:10:58.08,中英,,0,0,0,,就像历史之声在耳畔回荡\Nlike the thousands of voices from the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.08,1:11:01.33,中英,,0,0,0,,就像桃乐丝·赛儿丝\N"The cloud of witness,"as the phrase is in...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.34,1:11:03.80,中英,,0,0,0,,某篇文章的标题：云之证人\NDorothy Sayers uses it as the title for some story.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.80,1:11:05.84,中英,,0,0,0,,云之证人 史之幽灵\NThe cloud of witness,all the ghosts from the past;
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.85,1:11:07.01,中英,,0,0,0,,我不知道\NAnd I didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.01,1:11:10.51,中英,,0,0,0,,这些簇拥的声音是来自\NWere these the voices of the many crowds
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.51,1:11:13.31,中英,,0,0,0,,外星人 还是鬼怪...\Nof aliens or of ghosts or...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.31,1:11:14.35,中英,,0,0,0,,我不知道\NI didn't know what.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.35,1:11:17.56,中英,,0,0,0,,但那飞掠的 尖锐的声音\NBut already that skittering, high music
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.56,1:11:19.69,中英,,0,0,0,,伴随着穿过湖面\Nwith that follow shot across the lake
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.69,1:11:24.36,中英,,0,0,0,,穿过汽车的那个镜头\Nand then across the car itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.36,1:11:26.07,中英,,0,0,0,,让我背后发毛\Nit was the ultimate in spooky
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.07,1:11:28.20,中英,,0,0,0,,因为你感觉这辆车正被跟踪着\Nbecause you had the feeling this car is being followed
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.20,1:11:30.07,中英,,0,0,0,,而它并不知道我们在跟踪它\Nand it doesn't know it,and we're following it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.07,1:11:32.07,中英,,0,0,0,,我是说 我可以用象征派的观点\NI mean, I could go on for a long time
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.07,1:11:35.70,中英,,0,0,0,,带着对《闪灵》的尊重\Nabout the symbolism of that
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.70,1:11:38.63,中英,,0,0,0,,对此津津乐道\Nwith regard to what The Shining really is.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.63,1:11:41.96,中英,,0,0,0,,而我们对《闪灵》的理解\NAnd The Shining,as we come to understand it,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.96,1:11:44.51,中英,,0,0,0,,是看到历史的丰富以及\Nis seeing through all the layers of history
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.51,1:11:46.09,中英,,0,0,0,,历史的恐惧\Nand the horrors of history,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.09,1:11:48.34,中英,,0,0,0,,在那个回顾的场景中\Neven autobiographically in that scene
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.34,1:11:55.39,中英,,0,0,0,,格雷迪和杰克在血红色的男士卫生间里\Nwhere Grady and Jack talk in the blood-red men's room
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.39,1:11:57.64,中英,,0,0,0,,格雷迪说 "你儿子很有天赋\Nand Grady says, "Your son has a very great talent.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.64,1:11:59.14,中英,,0,0,0,,我不认为你意识到其天赋之高\N\MI don't think you realize how great it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.15,1:12:00.39,中英,,0,0,0,,但他是个调皮的小孩"\NHe's a very willful boy."
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.39,1:12:01.39,中英,,0,0,0,,接着杰克说 "是的 他很调皮..."\NAnd Jack says, "Yes, he is..."
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.40,1:12:03.52,中英,,0,0,0,,- 顽皮的熊孩子\N- A very willful boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.52,1:12:06.11,中英,,0,0,0,,- 托伦斯先生 你是否知道\N- Did you know, Mr. Torrance,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.11,1:12:11.15,中英,,0,0,0,,你儿子试图带领一个外人\Nthat your son is attempting to bring an outside party
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.16,1:12:12.82,中英,,0,0,0,,到这个派对里\Ninto this situation?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.82,1:12:15.03,中英,,0,0,0,,- 这就是老库\N- That's Kubrick.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.03,1:12:16.91,中英,,0,0,0,,他所做的就是将观众和人性\NWhat he's trying to do is bring the audience
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.91,1:12:19.29,中英,,0,0,0,,带入这部电影\Nand humanity into this situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.29,1:12:24.13,中英,,0,0,0,,在电影里 他试图让我们理解\NIn this movie, he is trying to get through to us all...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.13,1:12:26.63,中英,,0,0,0,,让在电影院里看这部电影的人明白\Nthe human race in the movie theaters watching this...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.63,1:12:30.09,中英,,0,0,0,,我们虽然存在 但是我们看不到\Nthat we are doing these things but don't see it,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.09,1:12:32.80,中英,,0,0,0,,我们在一遍又一遍地\Nthat we are committing these horrendous things
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.80,1:12:34.18,中英,,0,0,0,,犯着可怕的错误 然后忘记\Nover and over again and then forgetting them...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.18,1:12:37.56,中英,,0,0,0,,这一点他在电影中\Nwhich is... of course,he represents many, many times in the movie...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.56,1:12:40.89,中英,,0,0,0,,通过让角色似懂非懂然后忘记的方式\Nby having characters seem to know something
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.89,1:12:42.69,中英,,0,0,0,,表达了许多次\Nand then not know it and forget it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.69,1:12:49.82,中英,,0,0,0,,- 你把你的妻子和女儿剁成了肉末\N- You, uh, chopped your wife and daughter up into little bits.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.82,1:12:52.32,中英,,0,0,0,,- 可我一点都回想不起来了\N- I don't have any recollection of that at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.32,1:12:53.66,中英,,0,0,0,,- 这就像人性\N- That's like the human race.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.66,1:12:55.88,中英,,0,0,0,,我们犯下罪恶然后遗忘\NWe commit atrocities and then forget it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.88,1:13:07.30,中英,,0,0,0,,- 比尔 这是杰克·托伦斯\N- Bill, I'd like you to meet Jack Torrance.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.30,1:13:08.30,中英,,0,0,0,,你好\N - How do you do?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.30,1:13:09.30,中英,,0,0,0,,- 你好 比尔\N - Bill, how do you do?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.30,1:13:10.30,中英,,0,0,0,,- 见到你很高兴\N- It's nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.30,1:13:11.30,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我也是\N- It's a pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.30,1:13:13.34,中英,,0,0,0,,- 有些人认为电影中\N- Some people think that,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.34,1:13:15.69,中英,,0,0,0,,并不是所有的面试都是真实的\Nlike, not all of the interview is real.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.69,1:13:23.94,中英,,0,0,0,,有一些是杰克对于面试场面的幻想\NSome of it is Jack's imagination or fantasy of what the interview would be like.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.79,1:13:31.21,小2,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&\pos(970,682)}{\pos(495.000000,906.000000)}条纹的
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.79,1:13:31.21,小2,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&\pos(324,682)}{\pos(1470.000000,906.000000)}纯色的
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.94,1:13:28.86,中英,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,715)}比如 比尔·沃森衣服的变化\NLike, also, Bill Watson's clothes change.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.86,1:13:31.53,中英,,0,0,0,,他的裤子变了样\NLike,his pants change patterns.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.53,1:13:32.90,中英,,0,0,0,,同样诡异的是\NAnd what's also weird is,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.90,1:13:36.33,中英,,0,0,0,,他*在《耶稣基督万世巨星》*里还扮演了彼拉多**\Nhe plays Pontius Pilate in Jesus Christ Superstar.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.90,1:13:36.33,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(644,18)}*比尔·沃森的扮演者
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.33,1:13:41.56,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(625,18)}*2001年英国电影\N**钉死耶稣的古代罗马犹太总督
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.33,1:13:37.66,中英,,0,0,0,,-  ♪ 钉死他 ♪ \N- ♪ Crucify him ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.66,1:13:38.70,中英,,0,0,0,, ♪ 钉死他 ♪\N♪ Crucify him ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.70,1:13:41.58,中英,,0,0,0,, ♪ 钉死  钉死 钉死  ♪\N♪ Crucify, crucify, crucify ♪
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.58,1:13:42.88,中英,,0,0,0,,- 演的是个大反派\N- Really playing against type
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.88,1:13:45.71,中英,,0,0,0,,这也是一种暗示\Nand just being this sort of cipher.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.71,1:13:51.30,中英,,0,0,0,,我的意思是 某种程度上他是杰克的另一面\NI mean, in a way he's,he's kind of Jack's double
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.30,1:13:54.77,中英,,0,0,0,,有点儿像《大开眼界》中的\Nkind of in the same way that Bill Hartford has a double
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.77,1:13:57.89,中英,,0,0,0,,比尔·哈特福特\Nin Eyes Wide Shut.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.89,1:14:00.98,中英,,0,0,0,,他走进那个父亲刚去世的\NYou know, he goes to that blonde woman's house
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.98,1:14:02.32,中英,,0,0,0,,金发美女的家里\Nwhose father just died
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.32,1:14:05.85,中英,,0,0,0,,而他的未婚夫看起来十分像汤姆·克鲁斯\Nand her fiancé looks exactly like Tom Cruise,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.85,1:14:06.85,中英,,0,0,0,,他们有着一样的发型\Nhas the same haircut.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.36,1:14:12.15,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我一直都记得比尔·沃森 那个小助手...\N- I've always thought that Bill Watson, the little assistant...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.16,1:14:15.70,中英,,0,0,0,,我说小 是指相比于厄尔曼\Nand by little, I mean that he's sort of a shrunken figure...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.70,1:14:19.32,中英,,0,0,0,,比尔·沃森被叫来后 坐在那儿\Nto Ullman, who's brought in and sits there
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.33,1:14:22.87,中英,,0,0,0,,看起来严厉 忿恨而安静\Nlooking sort of dour and resentful and quiet
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.87,1:14:27.12,中英,,0,0,0,,他的肤色是有点儿...\Nand whose skin color is sort of a half...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.12,1:14:28.12,中英,,0,0,0,,不是白的\Nit's not white.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.13,1:14:30.54,中英,,0,0,0,,有点儿偏棕\NIt's sort of toward brown.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.54,1:14:34.55,中英,,0,0,0,,我一直觉得他代表着屈服...\NI've always thought that he sort of represents a subdued...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.55,1:14:36.39,中英,,0,0,0,,比赛中的输家\Nsomebody from a subdued race.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.39,1:14:39.39,中英,,0,0,0,,当厄尔曼问"你能帮他们整理一下行李吗？"时\NHe seems a little bit diffident when Ullman says,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.39,1:14:41.31,中英,,0,0,0,,他看起来有点变化\N"Will you go collect their luggage?"
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.31,1:14:42.31,中英,,0,0,0,,他说"好吧"\NHe says, "Fine."
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.31,1:14:43.60,中英,,0,0,0,,- 好吧\N- Fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.60,1:14:45.69,中英,,0,0,0,,- 而他们在参观酒店时\N- And as they're given the tour around all the hotel,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.69,1:14:47.85,中英,,0,0,0,,比尔·沃森一直跟在后面\NBill Watson is always trailing behind,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.85,1:14:50.77,中英,,0,0,0,,就像一个给人干杂活的管家\Nlike somebody who's going to be a little factotum to go get things.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.77,1:14:52.65,中英,,0,0,0,,我一直觉得他也许代表了\NI've always thought he sort of maybe represented,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.65,1:14:57.03,中英,,0,0,0,,优势条件下的傲慢文化\Nyou know, the condition in the dominant arrogant culture
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.03,1:14:59.33,中英,,0,0,0,,就像当时的印第安人\Nthat the Indians had at that time.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.83,1:15:10.92,中英,,0,0,0,,- 他是政府的无声监护人\N- He is the silent guardian for the government.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.92,1:15:15.09,中英,,0,0,0,,斯图尔特厄尔曼则代表了美国政府的外在形象\NStewart Ullman represents the face of the U.S. government.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.09,1:15:16.93,中英,,0,0,0,,因此库布里克让他戴了假发\NAnd that's why Kubrick gave him the toupee
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.93,1:15:19.93,中英,,0,0,0,,让他看起来更像肯尼迪总统\Nthat makes him look like John F. Kennedy.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.93,1:15:23.64,中英,,0,0,0,,我认为比尔·沃森\NAnd I think that he is the guy
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.64,1:15:27.48,中英,,0,0,0,,是一个默默注视着一切的人...就像\Nwho's silently watching everything and, you know...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.48,1:15:29.14,中英,,0,0,0,,中央情报局\NCIA, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.15,1:15:31.10,中英,,0,0,0,,或者国家安全局\NKind of NSA guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.11,1:15:34.27,中英,,0,0,0,,而他很有可能代表了\NAnd he probably represents
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.28,1:15:38.49,中英,,0,0,0,,这个房间 即远望酒店的\Nthe real managers of the house,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.49,1:15:42.28,中英,,0,0,0,,真正管理员 而巴里尼尔森则是...\Nof the Overlook,and Barry Nelson is the...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.28,1:15:44.41,中英,,0,0,0,,一个公关形象\Njust the person that's out in front.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.41,1:15:46.45,中英,,0,0,0,,- 比尔什么也不说\N- He doesn't say a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.45,1:15:47.79,中英,,0,0,0,,他是酒店的看门人\NHe's the summer caretaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.79,1:15:49.00,中英,,0,0,0,,对我而言他就像\NAnd he seems to me
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.00,1:15:51.13,中英,,0,0,0,,和温迪在某种程度上达成了一致\Nto have certain correspondences with Wendy.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.13,1:15:53.38,中英,,0,0,0,,杰克在酒店里不怎么干活儿\NJack really doesn't work around the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.38,1:15:55.67,中英,,0,0,0,,而温迪则一直忙里忙外\NWendy gets in there,and she does all the work.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.67,1:15:58.59,中英,,0,0,0,,- 你肯定会有一种感觉...\N- You do get the feeling that he's going...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.59,1:16:00.51,中英,,0,0,0,,那就是杰克即将替代他\Nthat Jack's going to be doing his work,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.52,1:16:04.10,中英,,0,0,0,,因为他看起来对杰克有些怀疑\Nbecause he seems a little,like, leery of Jack.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.10,1:16:05.47,中英,,0,0,0,,我曾经面试过很多次\NLike, I've been in job interviews,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.47,1:16:07.47,中英,,0,0,0,,而我总会发现 副面试官\Nand I've always found that that second person
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.48,1:16:11.56,中英,,0,0,0,,才是真正面试你的人\Nthey call in is,like, the person you're actually interviewing for.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.56,1:16:13.91,中英,,0,0,0,,他像是在做一个决定\NHe's making the decision,like, that silent person,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.91,1:16:18.32,中英,,0,0,0,,那种注视...\Nthat, like...kind of, like, glare...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.32,1:16:20.53,中英,,0,0,0,,斜眼注视着你\Nlike, squints at you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.53,1:16:26.66,中英,,0,0,0,,在被要求帮杰克搬行李时 他叹了口气\NYeah, and he sighs when he's asked to move Jack's luggage.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.66,1:16:28.16,中英,,0,0,0,,- 比尔 可以把托伦斯的东西\N- Bill, would you have the Torrances' things
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.16,1:16:29.21,中英,,0,0,0,,搬到他们的房间里吗\Nbrought to their apartment?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.21,1:16:29.94,中英,,0,0,0,,- 好吧\N- Fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.94,1:16:32.52,大,,0,0,0,,{\pos(638,578)}书中的照片
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.88,1:16:37.72,中英,,0,0,0,,- 这里有一个从广角场景淡入的叠化\N- There's a dissolve which fades from a wide shot
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.72,1:16:40.76,中英,,0,0,0,,出现了最后那张黑白照片\Nof the, you know,final black-and-white photo
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.76,1:16:43.09,中英,,0,0,0,,接着是杰克脸部的特写\Nto a close-up of Jack's face.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.09,1:16:46.93,中英,,0,0,0,,而这里大概有一秒\NAnd just for a second there,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.93,1:16:50.78,中英,,0,0,0,,当杰克的头发叠化出了希特勒的胡子\Nhis hairline fades in to form a Hitler moustache.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.24,1:17:01.78,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我觉得在这么多年里 在这家酒店里\N- I think a lot of things happened right here
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.79,1:17:05.82,中英,,0,0,0,,发生了很多事\Nin this particular hotel over the years
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.83,1:17:08.29,中英,,0,0,0,,而且不全是好事\Nand not all of 'em was good.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.20,1:17:11.58,中英,,0,0,0,,- 他曾问到\N- He once said,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.58,1:17:12.88,中英,,0,0,0,,"你怎么样才能把这么多东西"...\N"How do you get all of that"...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.88,1:17:13.97,中英,,0,0,0,,就是大屠杀\Nmeaning the Holocaust...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.97,1:17:15.79,中英,,0,0,0,,"拍成一部两个小时的电影的?"\N"into a two-hour movie?"
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.79,1:17:22.42,中英,,0,0,0,,我认为 库布里克觉得大屠杀是如此的\NI think he found the Holocaust of such evil magnitude
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.42,1:17:24.77,中英,,0,0,0,,罪恶 以至于他不能让自己\Nthat he just couldn't bring himself
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.77,1:17:26.89,中英,,0,0,0,,正确的看待他\Nto treat it directly,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.89,1:17:31.77,中英,,0,0,0,,因此他使用了恐怖片的形式\Nwhich is why he used the form of a horror film
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.77,1:17:34.14,中英,,0,0,0,,来间接的表现它\Nto treat it indirectly.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.15,1:17:37.81,中英,,0,0,0,,我认为 库布里克有意识的\N- I believe Kubrick,possibly consciously,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.82,1:17:43.07,中英,,0,0,0,,解决了一个历史问题 那就是\Nhas solved a kind of problem that history has,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.07,1:17:46.24,中英,,0,0,0,,为什么人们对过去的大屠杀\Nwhich is that it's very hard for many people
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.24,1:17:49.16,中英,,0,0,0,,很难在情感上\Nto connect emotionally to a gigantic big killing
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.17,1:17:50.95,中英,,0,0,0,,有所沟通\Nwe hear about in the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.95,1:17:53.58,中英,,0,0,0,,那些没有切身体验的人\NPeople who don't have direct family experience
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.58,1:17:55.71,中英,,0,0,0,,听到的只有数字\Nof it themselves may hear the statistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.71,1:17:57.13,中英,,0,0,0,,希特勒 光是在大屠杀中\NYou know, Hitler,among other things,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.13,1:17:59.17,中英,,0,0,0,,就屠杀了六百万的犹太人\Nkilled 6 million Jews in his Holocaust.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.17,1:18:00.67,中英,,0,0,0,,六百万是一个太大的数字\N6 million's a number too big.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.67,1:18:03.05,中英,,0,0,0,,斯大林曾有一句名言\NI mean Stalin is reputed to have said, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.05,1:18:05.22,中英,,0,0,0,,"杀一个人是犯罪和悲剧\N"You kill one person,it's a murder and a tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.22,1:18:07.84,中英,,0,0,0,,杀一百万人 就只是数据了"\NYou kill a million people,it's a statistic."
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.85,1:18:11.64,中英,,0,0,0,,他阐述了一个心理学事实\NHe was talking about a psychological fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.64,1:18:14.89,中英,,0,0,0,,而你知道 斯大林他自己...\NAnd, you know, Stalin himself was... what is it...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.89,1:18:16.32,中英,,0,0,0,,在三十年代 乌克兰西部\Nstarved about 3 million people
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.32,1:18:19.86,中英,,0,0,0,,也有意的饿死了三百万人\Nin the western Ukraine in the '30s on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.98,1:18:25.28,中英,,0,0,0,,我认为 库布里克可能意识到\NMy point is it may be that Kubrick
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.28,1:18:27.95,中英,,0,0,0,,自己提供了一条可以让我们\Nwas conscious of having offered a kind of way to bridge
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.95,1:18:32.17,中英,,0,0,0,,感受到庞大数字的桥梁\Nthat inability to feel for those gigantic statistics in that,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.17,1:18:34.71,中英,,0,0,0,,如果你第一次去看《闪灵》\Nif you go and see The Shining innocent the first time
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.71,1:18:37.21,中英,,0,0,0,,同时感到害怕 恐惧\Nand are terrified...you're just terrified
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.21,1:18:40.09,中英,,0,0,0,,然后 你会记住这种感觉...\Nand you'll always remember being terrified...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.09,1:18:44.01,中英,,0,0,0,,会意识到这部电影的象征意义和\Nand then go back aware of what the symbolism
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.01,1:18:47.72,中英,,0,0,0,,更深层次的含义\Nand the general larger pattern meanings of the movie are,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.72,1:18:50.77,中英,,0,0,0,,之后你就会思考其中的联系\Nthen you can begin to make something of a connection,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.77,1:18:53.10,中英,,0,0,0,,你就会说 "哦天哪"\Nsaying, "Oh, my God."
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.10,1:18:54.32,中英,,0,0,0,,我还记得丹尼和温迪\NI remember being terrified
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.32,1:18:57.94,中英,,0,0,0,,独处场景时的恐惧感\Nfor the individual little Danny and Wendy here.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.94,1:19:01.36,中英,,0,0,0,,那种感觉实际上是\NAnd that feeling is actually being...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.36,1:19:03.74,中英,,0,0,0,,对各种大屠杀中\Nis for people who are symbols of victims
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.74,1:19:06.58,中英,,0,0,0,,受害者的感同身受\Nof all kinds of horrendous genocides.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.49,1:19:13.70,中英,,0,0,0,,后来 库布里克的妻子谈到了\NAnd of course, his wife has subsequently talked about,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.70,1:19:16.00,中英,,0,0,0,,他曾多么接近屠杀犹太人的电影\Nyou know, how close he came to making his Holocaust movie,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.00,1:19:18.62,中英,,0,0,0,,比如《雅利安证件》*但他越来越沮丧 \NThe Aryan Papers, but that he got more and more
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.98,1:19:19.35,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(619,18)}*库布里克未拍摄的电影\N剧本由其改编自\N路易·伯格利的小说《战争谎言》
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.62,1:19:20.34,中英,,0,0,0,,最终有了借口\Nand more depressed and was relieved
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.34,1:19:22.18,中英,,0,0,0,,放弃拍摄\Nwhen he had an excuse not to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.18,1:19:24.71,中英,,0,0,0,,他提到了《辛德勒的名单》 并说\NHe used Schindler's List as saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.71,1:19:26.14,中英,,0,0,0,,"啊 它已经完成了"\N"Ah, it's already been done."
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.14,1:19:29.34,中英,,0,0,0,,这给我敲了一个警钟\NI mean, that struck a bell with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.34,1:19:31.44,中英,,0,0,0,,至今 我作为一名记者我 已经采访了\NAnd I've done a lot of stories as a journalist
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.44,1:19:34.89,中英,,0,0,0,,很多在研究\Nabout people who study...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.89,1:19:38.60,中英,,0,0,0,,研究大屠杀或其中的受害者\Neither talked to people who are victims of horrors or study it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.60,1:19:41.19,中英,,0,0,0,,弗洛伊德将此称为情感感染\NAnd there's... Freud talked about it as the contagion.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.19,1:19:42.69,中英,,0,0,0,,沮丧渗入你的体内\NThe depression seeps into you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.69,1:19:47.07,中英,,0,0,0,,你知道 库布里克关于一个问题\NIt's... you know what... Kubrick had a wonderful comment
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.07,1:19:49.32,中英,,0,0,0,,有一个著名的言论\Nabout this when somebody asked him.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.32,1:19:52.42,中英,,0,0,0,,"你的电影向我们展示了\N"Isn't it true that your movies are showing us
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.42,1:19:55.58,中英,,0,0,0,,人性的可怕 对不对？\Njust the horrendous side of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.58,1:19:57.30,中英,,0,0,0,,非常的消极"\NYou know, that's awful bleak."
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.30,1:19:58.50,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克答到\NAnd Kubrick said,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.50,1:20:02.21,中英,,0,0,0,,"但是我的电影里也有一些非常积极的东西\N”"Ah, but there's something very positive about it as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.22,1:20:04.71,中英,,0,0,0,,那就是 不管怎么样 \NAnd that is, it shows at the very least
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.71,1:20:07.76,中英,,0,0,0,,我的电影让我们认识到了恐惧是什么"\Nthat we can get our minds around what that horror is."
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.76,1:20:09.43,中英,,0,0,0,,在电影的一开始 丹尼\NAnd Danny, from the beginning,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.43,1:20:10.89,中英,,0,0,0,,就充满着各种疑问\Nhas his mind all over the problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.89,1:20:12.10,中英,,0,0,0,,他在看 在思考\NHe's looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.10,1:20:15.06,中英,,0,0,0,,丹尼反复的骑车 骑上骑下\NIn a way, Danny's big wheeling back and forth,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.06,1:20:16.23,中英,,0,0,0,,从某种程度上来说\Nup and down the hallways...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.23,1:20:18.06,中英,,0,0,0,,他是在认识这个酒店\NDanny is learning that hotel.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.06,1:20:19.06,中英,,0,0,0,,他也在认识恐惧\NHe's learning all the horrors.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.06,1:20:20.06,中英,,0,0,0,,他看到了恐惧\NHe's seeing them.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.06,1:20:21.35,中英,,0,0,0,,但它们只属于过去\NBut they're just in the past,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.35,1:20:22.73,中英,,0,0,0,,哈洛伦告诉了他那个秘密\Nand Hallorann gave him the secret.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.73,1:20:24.44,中英,,0,0,0,,他说 "记住 丹尼"\NHe said, "Remember, Danny."
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.45,1:20:26.27,中英,,0,0,0,,记住托尼说的话\NRemember what Tony tells him.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.28,1:20:27.53,中英,,0,0,0,,记住哈洛伦说的\NRemember what Mr. Hallorann said:
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.53,1:20:29.07,中英,,0,0,0,,"他们就像书里的照片\N"They're just like pictures in a book.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.07,1:20:31.03,中英,,0,0,0,,他们不是真的"\NThey're not real."
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.03,1:20:34.91,中英,,0,0,0,,这是一门很重要的课程\NNow, that's a really important lesson.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.91,1:20:37.29,中英,,0,0,0,,那些过来人 看到历史的人\NPeople who shine, who see through history,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.29,1:20:41.79,中英,,0,0,0,,他们知道 过去都是不存在的\Nunderstand that the past simply does not exist
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.79,1:20:43.04,中英,,0,0,0,,除了一个地方\Nexcept in one place.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.04,1:20:46.00,中英,,0,0,0,,那就是对于现在的即使记忆\NAnd that's the present tense instant of the mind, remembering.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.00,1:20:49.76,中英,,0,0,0,,这就是一个你可以到达但是\NThat is, exactly... that is a place you can go to somehow
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.76,1:20:51.67,中英,,0,0,0,,却不存在的地方\Nand yet it doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.68,1:20:54.89,中英,,0,0,0,,因此哈洛伦对丹尼说\NAnd so Hallorann tells Danny,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.89,1:20:56.14,中英,,0,0,0,,"你会看到一些恐怖的东西"\N"You're gonna see some horrible things."
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.14,1:20:57.14,中英,,0,0,0,,很明显 他告诉他\NApparently, he told him.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.14,1:20:58.39,中英,,0,0,0,,"你会看到一些恐怖的东西\N"You're gonna see some horrible things,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.39,1:20:59.56,中英,,0,0,0,,但是记住 他们不是真的\Nbut remember, they're not real.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.56,1:21:00.78,中英,,0,0,0,,他们就像书里的照片\NThey're like pictures in a book.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.78,1:21:02.89,中英,,0,0,0,,他们不再存在"\NThey no longer exist."
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.90,1:21:06.02,中英,,0,0,0,,这就是不感到恐惧的关键\NThat's a key to not getting depressed about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.03,1:21:11.28,中英,,0,0,0,,这也是...\NAnd that's...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.28,1:21:15.32,中英,,0,0,0,,你知道 这是一部关于过去的电影...\NYou see, this is a movie about what the past...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.32,1:21:18.87,中英,,0,0,0,,关于过去所带来的冲击\Nhow the past impinges, any past,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.87,1:21:20.87,中英,,0,0,0,,以及如何克服他们\Nand about how to get over that
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.87,1:21:22.84,中英,,0,0,0,,如何避免成为一名历史的受害者\Nand how not to be a victim of history.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.04,1:21:27.30,中英,,0,0,0,,而如果你对我的观点有所怀疑\NYou know, if you doubt what I've written about it,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.30,1:21:28.80,中英,,0,0,0,,那么去看电影吧\Njust go see the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.80,1:21:30.67,中英,,0,0,0,,我已经通过观赏它解决了这一切疑惑\NI've figured all this out from just seeing the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.67,1:21:31.96,中英,,0,0,0,,它在那儿\NIt's there.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.97,1:21:33.81,中英,,0,0,0,,很明显 而且许多人看了电影之后都会说\NIt's obvious, and most people who went and saw the movie said,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.81,1:21:35.02,中英,,0,0,0,,"天哪 它就在那儿"\N"Oh, my goodness. It is there."
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.07,1:21:39.62,大,,0,0,0,,{\pos(658,634)}如何看《闪灵》
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.39,1:21:43.85,中英,,0,0,0,,- 走你\N- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.85,1:21:47.15,中英,,0,0,0,,我对《闪灵》可以说是着了迷\NYeah, I was, I mean, obsessed with The Shining
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.15,1:21:52.82,中英,,0,0,0,,我看了所有网上对它的分析\Nand reading all the online analyses of it
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.82,1:21:55.45,中英,,0,0,0,,我也是一个\Nand was particularly a big fan
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.45,1:22:00.12,中英,,0,0,0,,分析《闪灵》影评人的脑残粉\Nof the MSTRMND's lengthy analysis of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.12,1:22:03.64,大,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,0)\pos(626,532)}{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&}影评人拒绝我们的采访
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.37,1:22:05.21,中英,,0,0,0,,他有一句话一直在我脑海里\NAnd he had one phrase that kind of stuck in my mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.21,1:22:08.29,中英,,0,0,0,,那就是  《闪灵》是一部\Nthat The Shining was a film
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.29,1:22:11.67,中英,,0,0,0,,值得反复观看的电影\Nmeant to be seen forwards and backwards.
