Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.31,1:23:07.98,中英,,0,0,0,,在奇景影院和朋友说了这些\NBut I was talking to my pals at the Spectacle Theater,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.98,1:23:12.48,中英,,0,0,0,,和他们一起重看了很多次\Nriffing about experimental ways of showing films.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.48,1:23:14.20,中英,,0,0,0,,他们说 你不觉得你？\NAnd they were like, "Well, do you think
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.20,1:23:16.90,中英,,0,0,0,,可以做点儿什么吗？\Nyou could come up with something,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.90,1:23:18.41,中英,,0,0,0,,在这儿放给大家看看\Nyou know, to show here?"
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.41,1:23:22.08,中英,,0,0,0,,我说 "对 我们应该做的就是\NI was like, "Sure, what we should do is we should show
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.08,1:23:24.75,中英,,0,0,0,,把《闪灵》的开头和结尾同时放\NThe Shining forwards and backwards at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.75,1:23:27.25,中英,,0,0,0,,不需要很创造性\NYou know not... let's not be creative.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.25,1:23:29.92,中英,,0,0,0,,只是把电影倒着放\NLet's just actually reverse the film
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.92,1:23:34.01,中英,,0,0,0,,镜像的 重叠的播放它\Nand show it exactly mirrored, superimposed."
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.72,1:23:42.10,中英,,0,0,0,,第一个画面是清澈的湖\NThe first image is of the reflective lake.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.31,1:23:48.64,中英,,0,0,0,,最后一个画面是照片上的\NAnd the last image is of the inscription
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.64,1:23:49.86,中英,,0,0,0,,题词\Non the photograph,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.86,1:23:52.45,中英,,0,0,0,,照片上 杰克被定格\Nin which Jack is frozen for all time...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.45,1:23:56.19,中英,,0,0,0,,上面写着1921年7月4号派对 远望酒店\NThe "Overlook Hotel, July 4th Ball, 1921."
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.19,1:23:59.28,中英,,0,0,0,,这些重叠让照片看起来...\NSo those superimposed make it...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.28,1:24:02.28,中英,,0,0,0,,看起来像一张明信片 一封邀请函\Nkind of make it seem like a postcard, like an invitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.28,1:24:03.28,中英,,0,0,0,,就像...\NLike...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.41,1:24:08.41,中英,,0,0,0,,"欢迎参加7月4号湖边的派对\N""Come to the July 4th Ball here in Crater Lake."
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.41,1:24:12.50,中英,,0,0,0,,这里还有一个很酷炫的地方\NThere's a really cool part where, like, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.50,1:24:16.21,中英,,0,0,0,,直升机跟随着杰克的轿车\Nthe helicopters are following his car
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.21,1:24:20.63,中英,,0,0,0,,演职表中 他的名字向上滚动\Nand his name scrolls up in the credits
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.63,1:24:24.80,中英,,0,0,0,,接着 和汽车碰在一起\Nand, like, meets the car, right...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.81,1:24:29.31,中英,,0,0,0,,并且处在照片格的位置\Nright in the same position where the grid of photographs,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.31,1:24:32.15,中英,,0,0,0,,而那张照片又刚好是他自己\Nright in that photograph that he's trapped in.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.15,1:24:34.82,中英,,0,0,0,,所以 他的轿车 他的名字和他的照片\NSo his car, his name and his photograph
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.82,1:24:37.44,中英,,0,0,0,,在那一秒排成了一条线\Nall line up for one second.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.44,1:24:38.44,中英,,0,0,0,,酷炫\NPretty cool.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.44,1:24:40.15,中英,,0,0,0,,呵呵呵呵呵
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.15,1:24:43.49,中英,,0,0,0,,面试场景...拍得很厉害\NThe interview has a, like... it's great.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.49,1:24:45.16,中英,,0,0,0,,当他们枯燥地\NWhile they're talking about...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.16,1:24:47.79,中英,,0,0,0,,谈论着酒店以前的谋杀时\Nyou know, very dryly about all the murders that happened,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.79,1:24:49.75,中英,,0,0,0,,在叠化中看\Nlike, you know, in the superimposition,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.75,1:24:52.59,中英,,0,0,0,,杰克拿着斧头 发了疯一样\NJack's running around with an axe going bananas, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.88,1:25:00.42,中英,,0,0,0,,同样精彩的叠化还有很多\NThere's a lot of just great, great, great superimpositions
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.42,1:25:04.30,中英,,0,0,0,,比如人们的脸部重合\Nof people's faces lining up, like Jack's...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.30,1:25:08.01,中英,,0,0,0,,杰克在濒死时的表情\NJack's, like, got the death look,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.02,1:25:09.56,中英,,0,0,0,,在丹尼吃三明治的时候\Nand he's staring through Danny's face
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.56,1:25:12.36,中英,,0,0,0,,盯着他\Nas Danny's eating a sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.85,1:25:16.90,中英,,0,0,0,,还有很多...很多...\NThen there's a lot of things... there's a lot of, like...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.90,1:25:18.65,中英,,0,0,0,,还有一些搞笑\Nthere's a... you know, there's some fun jokes,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.65,1:25:20.37,中英,,0,0,0,,但又严肃的地方\Nbut then there's serious stuff where,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.37,1:25:22.24,中英,,0,0,0,,比如...\Nlike, you...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.24,1:25:26.49,中英,,0,0,0,,丹尼出现的幻觉...\Nwhere the hallucination... the visions that Danny has,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.49,1:25:28.12,中英,,0,0,0,,看起来就像覆盖\Nwhere you'll see them,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.12,1:25:30.37,中英,,0,0,0,,在其他场景的上面\Nlike, overlaid on top of other situations.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.37,1:25:33.37,中英,,0,0,0,,例如 那对双胞胎女孩覆盖在温迪上面\NLike the twin girls are overlaid on top of Wendy,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.38,1:25:35.50,中英,,0,0,0,,如果你仔细观察\Nwhich, if you study the film,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.50,1:25:38.55,中英,,0,0,0,,你会发现那对双胞胎和温迪有所关联\Nyou see that the twins are associated with Wendy.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.55,1:25:42.21,中英,,0,0,0,,她们就像温迪的视觉对应点\NThey're like her, like, visionary counterpart.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.22,1:25:45.55,中英,,0,0,0,,电影中的象征符号...\NAll the symbols in the movie start...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.55,1:25:50.77,中英,,0,0,0,,在反复的叠化展现出来中\Noverlap in the superimposition, backwards/forwards superimposition.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.39,1:25:56.48,中英,,0,0,0,,被谋杀的双胞胎叠化在杰克的脸上\NThe murdered twins are overlaid across Jack's face,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.48,1:25:58.61,中英,,0,0,0,,让他看起来像个小丑\Nand he looks like a clown.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.61,1:26:00.48,中英,,0,0,0,,让他有了一个小丑面罩\NIt makes like a clown mask,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.48,1:26:01.99,中英,,0,0,0,,而四处遍布的鲜血\Nand there's blood everywhere
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.99,1:26:03.74,中英,,0,0,0,,就像在他的嘴唇上\Nand, like, blood on his lips.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.95,1:26:07.74,中英,,0,0,0,,血液从他的眼睛里流出来\NAnd blood coming out of his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.74,1:26:11.99,中英,,0,0,0,,就像丹尼...\NAnd, like, you know, Danny takes it...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.00,1:26:13.54,中英,,0,0,0,,丹尼用双手盖住脸\Nyou know, like, Danny has his hands over his face,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.54,1:26:17.46,中英,,0,0,0,,而杰克从他的头部往外看\Nand it's... Jack is looking out from his head,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.46,1:26:22.34,中英,,0,0,0,,然后丹尼张开手向外窥视 看到了格雷迪\Nand then he open... he, like, peeks out and he sees Grady.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.34,1:26:26.76,中英,,0,0,0,,接着是格雷迪和杰克在下一个\NAnd then Grady and Jack continue their conversation
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.76,1:26:27.98,中英,,0,0,0,,场景的对话\Ninto the next scene,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.98,1:26:31.68,中英,,0,0,0,,就是丹尼看电视的那个场景\Nwhich is where he's watching television.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.68,1:26:33.78,中英,,0,0,0,,看起来他们的嘴唇...\NAnd it's like they have this...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.78,1:26:36.27,中英,,0,0,0,,就像在电视里一样\Ntheir lips are, like, in the TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.27,1:26:38.74,中英,,0,0,0,,杰克和格雷迪的嘴唇在电视上\NJack and Grady's lips are in the TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.74,1:26:42.98,中英,,0,0,0,,而窗户变成了他们的面罩\NAnd these masks are formed by the windows.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.98,1:26:46.28,中英,,0,0,0,,看上去像丹尼在想象出这一切\NAnd ifs like Danny's envisioning this.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.28,1:26:49.95,中英,,0,0,0,,丹尼在想象...\NDanny's envisioning...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.95,1:26:54.29,中英,,0,0,0,,看到了格雷迪和杰克之间的约定\Nyou know, envisioning the pact between Grady and Jack.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.29,1:27:00.84,中英,,0,0,0,,就像他潜入卧室\NLike, he goes into... he sneaks into the bedroom,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.84,1:27:02.38,中英,,0,0,0,,穿过杰克脑袋的右边\Nlike, right through Jack's head,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.38,1:27:05.09,中英,,0,0,0,,刚好在他们中间\Nright in between them.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.09,1:27:10.14,中英,,0,0,0,,就像那个场景...\NAnd just like that scene is...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.14,1:27:13.51,中英,,0,0,0,,丹尼在试探他的爸爸\Nthat's the scene where Danny is testing
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.52,1:27:16.36,中英,,0,0,0,,问他"你喜不喜...\Nhis father, like, "Do you really, you know!"...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.36,1:27:18.35,中英,,0,0,0,,你喜不喜欢这个地方？\N"Do you like this place?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.35,1:27:19.78,中英,,0,0,0,,你不会伤害我们的 对吧？"\NYou're not gonna hurt us, are you?"
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.78,1:27:22.99,中英,,0,0,0,,就像丹尼已经知道爸爸迷失了自己\NLike, Danny kind of knows that his dad has lost it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.42,1:27:28.89,中英,,0,0,0,,终于翻完这个意淫狂了 T^T
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.20,1:27:31.20,中英,,0,0,0,,最后一组镜头是关于1921年\NThe last shot is 1921,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.20,1:27:36.79,中英,,0,0,0,,第一个镜头是在路上\Nand the first shot is of the road.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.79,1:27:43.71,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(693,18)}*酒店竣工是在1909年 不知道这里的1921代表什么
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.79,1:27:39.46,中英,,0,0,0,,厄尔曼提到它是在1921年*结束\NUllman mentions that it was finished in 1921.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.46,1:27:43.71,中英,,0,0,0,,所以这是首尾呼应\NSo it's, again, it's a way of returning the narrative
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.71,1:27:45.31,中英,,0,0,0,,回到最初\Nback to the beginning.
