Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.56,1:28:02.78,中英,,0,0,0,,- 哈洛伦先生 237房间里有什么？\N- Mr. Hallorann, what is in room 237?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.73,1:28:06.28,中英,,0,0,0,,- 啥都没\N- Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.28,1:28:09.90,中英,,0,0,0,,237号房间里什么都没\NThere ain't nothing in room 237.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.91,1:28:13.25,中英,,0,0,0,,总之你不要进去\NBut you ain't got no business going in there anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.25,1:28:14.99,中英,,0,0,0,,离它远点\Nso stay out.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.99,1:28:17.75,中英,,0,0,0,,- 在237那个情趣房里\N- In the sex room, 237,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.75,1:28:20.63,中英,,0,0,0,,我们看到了这个美丽的妖妇\Nwhere we see this beautiful, sexual temptress,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.63,1:28:24.54,中英,,0,0,0,,之后变成了腐烂的尸体\Nwho then becomes a rotting body...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.54,1:28:26.76,中英,,0,0,0,,十分现实而形象的腐尸\Nrealistically depicted as a rotting body...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.76,1:28:30.93,中英,,0,0,0,,而对地毯的设计 总体上利用一些\Nthe design on the rug shows basically the most...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.93,1:28:33.40,中英,,0,0,0,,几何形的圆弧曲线体现了\Nin geometric form with round curves...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.40,1:28:36.14,中英,,0,0,0,,性行为\Nthe act of intercourse itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.14,1:28:37.61,中英,,0,0,0,,一个接着一个接着一个接着一个\None after another after another after another,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.61,1:28:38.72,中英,,0,0,0,,像一幅\Nsort of like a picture
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.73,1:28:42.60,中英,,0,0,0,,传宗接代 生产生命的画\Nof down through the generations of what produces life.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.60,1:28:46.23,中英,,0,0,0,,当你回到走廊 进入了一个更大的社会\NYou go back out in the hallway, in the larger society,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.24,1:28:48.36,中英,,0,0,0,,那些圆弧曲线的地毯的设计\Nand the round curves of that very same design
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.36,1:28:50.65,中英,,0,0,0,,变成了六边形\Nhave become hexagons,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.65,1:28:52.87,中英,,0,0,0,,不再是那么圆滑 而变得更像是\Nnot so nice and round, and a little bit more
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.87,1:28:54.91,中英,,0,0,0,,六边形的蜂窝\Nlike the beehive hexagon
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.91,1:28:57.20,中英,,0,0,0,,像是历史的走廊\Nbut down the whole corridors of history.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.21,1:28:58.92,中英,,0,0,0,,我觉得库布里克在这里使用的影像\NI think he's got an image of it there,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.92,1:29:02.00,中英,,0,0,0,,是要表达家庭中的男性\Nso he's talking about the family of man,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.00,1:29:03.92,中英,,0,0,0,,既包括基本家庭\Nboth in an individual nuclear family
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.92,1:29:07.30,中英,,0,0,0,,也包括了人类的发展历史\Nand in the whole course of our genetic history.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.42,1:29:15.76,中英,,0,0,0,,- 当丹尼进入了237房间\N- Once Denny enters room 237, like, that's...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.76,1:29:17.31,中英,,0,0,0,,就有点像激活了\Nthat kind of is, like, the activation
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.31,1:29:20.72,中英,,0,0,0,,电影的余下部分\Nof the rest of the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.73,1:29:27.06,中英,,0,0,0,,那就是让杰克最终发疯的原因\NLike, that's what causes Jack to go insane finally.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.07,1:29:32.04,中英,,0,0,0,,那就是把哈洛伦带回酒店的原因\NThat's what brings Hallorann to the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.78,1:29:39.96,中英,,0,0,0,,237房间就像...\NLike, the room 237 is, like, is sort of this...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.25,1:29:45.83,中英,,0,0,0,,我将它与《2001：太空漫游》里的神秘屋\NI mean, I compare it to the mysterious hotel room
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.83,1:29:48.00,中英,,0,0,0,,进行比较\Nat the end of 2001,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.00,1:29:49.30,中英,,0,0,0,,这个奇怪的...\Nwhere there's...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.63,1:29:53.97,中英,,0,0,0,,奇怪的房间\NIt's this strange, strange place
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.97,1:29:58.14,中英,,0,0,0,,某种程度上 转变了故事后续的发展\Nthat somehow, like, transforms the rest of the narrative.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.12,1:30:19.79,中英,,0,0,0,,《闪灵》是在一座山上拍摄（发生）的\NThe Shining takes place on the top of a mountain
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.79,1:30:22.29,中英,,0,0,0,,这是一个...\Nin kind of like a, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.29,1:30:26.04,中英,,0,0,0,,魔幻的 变形的环境\Nmagical shape-shifting environment.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.04,1:30:29.63,中英,,0,0,0,,走出...\NAnd, like, travel is...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.63,1:30:30.80,中英,,0,0,0,,走出它就是...\Ntraveling out of it is...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.17,1:30:35.68,中英,,0,0,0,,它不像《2001：太空漫游》 感觉自己是在哪儿游玩\NYou know, instead of 2001, where you're traveling to something,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.68,1:30:40.35,中英,,0,0,0,,《闪灵》的重点是走出 是逃脱\Nthe point of The Shining is to escape, is to travel out.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.39,1:30:44.06,中英,,0,0,0,,而237房间\NAnd room 237 is, like...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.06,1:30:52.82,中英,,0,0,0,,它就像这个酒店的逃生舱\Nit's kind of like the escape pod of... of the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.28,1:31:06.25,中英,,0,0,0,,如果你把2 3 7 相乘 你得到42\N- If you multiply the numbers 2, 3 and 7, you get 42.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.25,1:31:09.34,中英,,0,0,0,,我承认我也许在垂死挣扎\NNow, I admit, perhaps I'm grasping at straws there,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.34,1:31:14.55,中英,,0,0,0,,但它是电影中的一个始终如一的参考\Nbut it is consistent with the pattern of reference in the film.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.55,1:31:16.97,中英,,0,0,0,,- 另一件事在我的电影《库布里克的奥德赛》中\N - Another thing which my film Kubrick's Odyssey
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.97,1:31:19.47,中英,,0,0,0,,会揭露\Nreally reveals
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.47,1:31:21.43,中英,,0,0,0,,在那个丹尼玩小车的场景中\Nis the carpeting on the floor
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.43,1:31:23.06,中英,,0,0,0,,他穿着阿波罗十一号的毛衣\Nduring the famous Danny scene,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.06,1:31:27.23,中英,,0,0,0,,站在地毯上\Nwhere he stands up with his Apollo 11 shirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.23,1:31:34.32,中英,,0,0,0,,地毯的图案与39-A*发射台完全对应\NThe patterns in the carpeting exactly match launch pad 39-A.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.23,1:31:34.32,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(642,18)}*位于佛罗里达州肯尼迪航天中心
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.32,1:31:36.99,中英,,0,0,0,,包括车道和一切一切\NYou know, even the driveway and everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.99,1:31:42.74,中英,,0,0,0,,不知道你有没有注意到 当丹尼站起来时 地毯上的图案\NAnd if you notice in that shot, the pattern on the rug changes
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.74,1:31:44.84,中英,,0,0,0,,变化过了\Nwhen Danny stands up.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.33,1:31:48.83,中英,,0,0,0,,地毯的方向被调过了\N- The carpet's reversed,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.23,1:32:12.96,小2,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&\pos(324,596)}棕色条纹指向丹尼
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.23,1:32:12.96,小2,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFF64E&\1a&H00&\pos(892,596)}棕色条纹在丹尼身后
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.83,1:31:51.13,中英,,0,0,0,,那个棕线不见了\Nand there's no pathway there anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.13,1:31:54.76,中英,,0,0,0,,那个球顺着滚向丹尼的线条\NThe pathway that the ball took rolling down towards Danny
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.76,1:31:56.59,中英,,0,0,0,,不见了\Nis gone now.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.59,1:31:58.43,中英,,0,0,0,,因为地毯被倒过来铺\NIt's no longer there 'cause it's reversed.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.43,1:32:00.55,中英,,0,0,0,,你感觉到了终止\NAnd you get a sense of a closure.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.55,1:32:02.30,中英,,0,0,0,,六边形关上了\NNow the hexagon is closed.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.31,1:32:04.60,中英,,0,0,0,,就像他被关在了里面\NIt's almost like he's been closed in.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.99,1:32:20.71,中英,,0,0,0,,- 《闪灵》上映七年后\N- Seven years after The Shining had come out,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.30,1:32:20.93,大3,,0,0,0,,{\pos(610,550)}《闪灵》之后
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.71,1:32:22.83,中英,,0,0,0,,让我吃惊的是 没有人可以\Nto my surprise, nobody had written,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.83,1:32:24.29,中英,,0,0,0,,写下我所说的那些\Nas far as I could tell,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.29,1:32:26.63,中英,,0,0,0,,除了电影中的那个家庭和酒店\Nabout what the major themes of the movie were,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.63,1:32:30.62,中英,,0,0,0,,所带给我们的让人欣喜的恐惧之外\Nbeyond the delightfully scary immediate story
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.62,1:32:33.79,中英,,0,0,0,,电影的真正主题是什么\Nof the family and the hotel itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.79,1:32:38.05,中英,,0,0,0,,而我的确在欧洲某个地方写着一部小说\NAnd I was actually doing a story somewhere over in Europe,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.05,1:32:41.05,中英,,0,0,0,,有人在电话里跟我说 《全金属外壳》的\Nand I was told over the phone that the posters were out
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.05,1:32:42.35,中英,,0,0,0,,海报张贴出来了\Nfor Full Metal Jacket.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.35,1:32:45.14,中英,,0,0,0,,我问了海报上的描述\NI asked about the description,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.14,1:32:48.64,中英,,0,0,0,,他说 是一个和平标志和一句话\Nand I was told it had a peace sign right next to the words
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.64,1:32:49.64,中英,,0,0,0,,"天生杀人狂"\N"Born to kill."
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.64,1:32:50.89,中英,,0,0,0,,然后我说 "哦天哪\NAnd I said, "Oh, my goodness.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.89,1:32:53.32,中英,,0,0,0,,他的下一部应该还是同样的主题"\NHis next movie's gonna be about some of the same themes."
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.32,1:32:54.91,中英,,0,0,0,,总之 艾玛我去\NAnyway, I thought, "My goodness."
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.91,1:32:58.98,中英,,0,0,0,,我推测它的主题会很明显\NI had presumed that it would have become obvious,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.99,1:33:00.08,中英,,0,0,0,,所以我想...什么情况？\Nso I thought, "What the heck?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.08,1:33:03.99,中英,,0,0,0,,我要看看能不能写一篇文章来让\N"I'll just see if I can write an article about it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.99,1:33:06.49,中英,,0,0,0,,人们看《全金属外壳》的时候更觉得有趣\Nto give people more fun when they see Full Metal Jacket,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.49,1:33:07.75,中英,,0,0,0,,更广义的让大家知道 他的上一部电影\Nto know what his last movie was about,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.75,1:33:09.04,中英,,0,0,0,,在说些什么\Nin larger senses.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.02,1:33:13.90,中英,,0,0,0,,只工作不玩耍,聪明的孩子也变傻
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.04,1:33:18.67,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我遭受到了许多在美国宇航局工作人员的谴责\N- I've gotten a lot of flak from people who work for NASA.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.67,1:33:21.47,中英,,0,0,0,,而我想告诉他们\NAnd, you know, I want to tell them, that I, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.47,1:33:23.88,中英,,0,0,0,,我不是说我们没上过月球\NI'm not saying that we didn't go to the moon.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.89,1:33:25.51,中英,,0,0,0,,我也不是说他们所创造出\NAnd I'm not saying that their technology
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.51,1:33:26.85,中英,,0,0,0,,的科技\Nthat they helped build
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.85,1:33:29.47,中英,,0,0,0,,不伟大 不好 等等\Nisn't great and awesome and everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.47,1:33:31.35,中英,,0,0,0,,我只是说 我们所看到的 是假的\NI'm just saying that what we saw was faked.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.35,1:33:33.60,中英,,0,0,0,,而且我已经用前屏投影\NAnd I know I have it proved
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.60,1:33:36.52,中英,,0,0,0,,证明了这一点\Nwith the front-screen projection process.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.52,1:33:39.48,中英,,0,0,0,,目前为止 政府所做的\NAs far as what the government has done,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.48,1:33:42.66,中英,,0,0,0,,老实说 我十分期待明年我的税收\NI fully expect my taxes to be audited next year,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.66,1:33:43.95,中英,,0,0,0,,被审计\Nto be honest with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.95,1:33:49.16,中英,,0,0,0,,我也被正式访问过\NAnd, you know, I've had visitations, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.16,1:33:52.00,中英,,0,0,0,,而且他们肯定在监视着我\NAnd they're definitely watching me for sure,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.00,1:33:54.71,中英,,0,0,0,,而且他们并不乐意我正接受采访\Nand they're not too happy with what's going on here.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.71,1:33:56.00,中英,,0,0,0,,我认为他们很担心\NAnd I think they're probably very worried
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.01,1:33:58.04,中英,,0,0,0,,下一部电影\Nabout the next film.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.04,1:34:01.42,中英,,0,0,0,,而且它肯定会是一部爆炸性的电影\NAnd that one will be the really explosive film.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.97,1:34:09.31,中英,,0,0,0,,- 假期里 我们走在哥斯达黎加\N- We were walking along the beach on vacation
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.32,1:34:12.47,中英,,0,0,0,,的沙滩边\Nwith some people in Costa Rica.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.69,1:34:14.78,中英,,0,0,0,,这是个美好的经历\NI had this delightful experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.78,1:34:16.57,中英,,0,0,0,,我们和一对来自旧金山的小情侣\NWe were walking along with a young couple
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.57,1:34:18.28,中英,,0,0,0,,一起散步\Nwho were from San Francisco.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.28,1:34:19.90,中英,,0,0,0,,我们走了很久\NAnd it was a long walk.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.90,1:34:22.90,中英,,0,0,0,,我们穿过了一个美丽的丛林\N的We'd gone through this big, beautiful jungle.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.90,1:34:24.49,中英,,0,0,0,,然后我们从沙滩边走回来\NAnd were coming back on the beach
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.49,1:34:26.16,中英,,0,0,0,,走到我们扎营的地方\Nto walk back to where the tent camp was.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.16,1:34:27.24,中英,,0,0,0,,然后我们开始...\NAnd the guy started...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.24,1:34:28.37,中英,,0,0,0,,我们开始谈论库布里克\Nwe started chatting about Kubrick.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.37,1:34:29.46,中英,,0,0,0,,我说 "库布里克很伟大"\NI said, "Oh, Kubrick's great,"
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.46,1:34:30.74,中英,,0,0,0,,那个人说：\NAnd the guy said, "You know,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.74,1:34:32.54,中英,,0,0,0,,"《闪灵》 实际上是关于美国印第安人的电影"\NThe Shining, it's actually about the American Indians."
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.54,1:34:33.58,中英,,0,0,0,,我说 "真的吗？"\NI said, "Really?"
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.59,1:34:37.08,中英,,0,0,0,,然后他接着说下去 而我一直说 "真的吗？"\NAnd he went on talking, and I said, "Really?"
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.08,1:34:39.92,中英,,0,0,0,,在他跟我说这些的时候\NAnd I just couldn't resist just playing dumb for while
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.92,1:34:41.84,中英,,0,0,0,,我就是忍不住装傻充愣\Nwhile he told me the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.84,1:34:44.01,中英,,0,0,0,,我也很开心\NI was delighted!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.76,1:34:53.10,中英,,0,0,0,, 那一天 愤怒之日\NDies irae, dies illa
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.10,1:34:54.94,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克建立了一个同步的场景\N- Kubrick just sets up synchronous space.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.94,1:34:57.23,中英,,0,0,0,,他的电影...\NHis movies are...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.23,1:34:59.98,中英,,0,0,0,,他们在彼此之间创造出了共时性场景\Nthey create synchronous situations in themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.98,1:35:01.28,中英,,0,0,0,,这个人 他嘴上说\NThere's this man who says, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.28,1:35:02.90,中英,,0,0,0,,"真是好玩的派对 不是吗？"\N"Quite a party, isn't it?"
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.90,1:35:04.82,中英,,0,0,0,,库布里克为什么要设立一个\NWhy did Kubrick put him there,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.82,1:35:06.74,中英,,0,0,0,,头裂开的人在这里？\Nwith the split down his head?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.74,1:35:08.49,中英,,0,0,0,,为什么不放在其他场景？\NWhy did he put him there?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.49,1:35:10.46,中英,,0,0,0,,我苦思冥想\NAnd I was contemplating that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.46,1:35:13.91,中英,,0,0,0,,然后我儿子进来了\NAnd in comes my son.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.91,1:35:16.25,中英,,0,0,0,,他那时九岁\NAnd he was nine years old at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.25,1:35:17.96,中英,,0,0,0,,不知道我正在忙些什么\NAnd he didn't know what I was working on.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.96,1:35:20.96,中英,,0,0,0,,他走进来 跟我说了一个故事\NAnd he came in, and he began to tell me a story.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.96,1:35:23.26,中英,,0,0,0,,他说 "这个是我刚想到的"\NAnd he said, "I've just thought this up."
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.26,1:35:27.51,中英,,0,0,0,,故事里 人物的头被闪电劈开了\NAnd his characters head was split open with a chaos bolt.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.51,1:35:31.39,中英,,0,0,0,,然后人物说 "我的头裂开了"\NAnd the character says, "Talk about a splitting headache."
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.39,1:35:33.61,中英,,0,0,0,,而从他的头里跳出了\NAnd out of the contents of his head
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.61,1:35:37.18,中英,,0,0,0,,一个小人 这才是真正的他\Nleaps a small person who is his real self.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.19,1:35:39.65,中英,,0,0,0,,然后他跑了 用一个尖锐的声音喊着\NAnd it goes running off, saying in a high, squeaky voice,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.66,1:35:41.90,中英,,0,0,0,,"别想了 我回家了“”\N"Forget this. I'm going home."
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.90,1:35:45.45,中英,,0,0,0,,这就是一个极好的共时性\NAnd, yeah, I thought that was really stunning synchronicity,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.45,1:35:47.99,中英,,0,0,0,,我是说 你已经看到了所有的元素\NI mean, 'cause you've got all the elements there.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.99,1:35:49.24,中英,,0,0,0,,你有了斧头\NYou've got the ax.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.24,1:35:50.91,中英,,0,0,0,,你被雷电击中\NYou've got the whole idea of the lightning bolt,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.91,1:35:52.87,中英,,0,0,0,,闪电劈在那个人的头上\Nthe chaos bolt, striking the person's head,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.87,1:35:54.24,中英,,0,0,0,,劈裂的头\Nthe splitting headache.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.24,1:35:55.83,中英,,0,0,0,,还有托尼\NYou've got Tony...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.83,1:35:57.33,中英,,0,0,0,,托尼尖锐的声音\NTony's squeaky voice, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.87,1:36:00.96,中英,,0,0,0,,我认为这是一个很好的共时性场景\NI thought that was quite a synchronicity.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.96,1:36:02.63,中英,,0,0,0,,- 对于库布里克 人们总对他\N- One can always argue that Kubrick
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.63,1:36:06.55,中英,,0,0,0,,是否有意为之争论不休\Nhad only some or even none of these in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.55,1:36:09.52,中英,,0,0,0,,但是我们从后现代主义电影批评中了解到\NBut we all know from postmodern film criticism
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.52,1:36:14.97,中英,,0,0,0,,作者目的 只是各种艺术作品中的一部分\Nthat author intent is only part of the story of any work of art.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.97,1:36:18.89,中英,,0,0,0,,这就意味着 不用去管创作者\NAnd those meanings are there regardless
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.89,1:36:24.02,中英,,0,0,0,,对作品是否有主观意识\Nof whether the creator of the work was conscious of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.02,1:36:26.02,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我认为...\N- I think... if you want to know what I think,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.03,1:36:28.45,中英,,0,0,0,,我认为 酒店是如此的诡异\NI think the hotel is so whacked out
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.45,1:36:30.70,中英,,0,0,0,,以至于我在开始时 根本不知道\Nthat I don't have any clue what's going on
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.70,1:36:32.20,中英,,0,0,0,,发生了什么\Nfrom the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.20,1:36:34.45,中英,,0,0,0,,当你坐下好好思考时\NWhen you really sit and think about it, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.45,1:36:36.54,中英,,0,0,0,,我是说 因为整部电影如此诡异\Nbecause the whole thing is so whacked out,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.55,1:36:38.70,中英,,0,0,0,,如此的分散\Nand it's so not put together...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.71,1:36:42.04,中英,,0,0,0,,它是如此...每件事都显得不合适\Nit's so... everything is so wildly out of place
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.04,1:36:44.84,中英,,0,0,0,,以至于当你...思考 调查的更多\Nthat when you... the more... the closer you get
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.84,1:36:48.01,中英,,0,0,0,,你也就会看到得更多\Ninto looking at things, the more you look at them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.01,1:36:51.60,中英,,0,0,0,,这就像 在《大开眼界》里的场景\NIt's kind of like, you know, the scene in Eyes Wide Shut
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.60,1:36:55.05,中英,,0,0,0,,当比尔出去 又回来\Nwhere Bill goes... you know, he returns.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.05,1:36:56.89,中英,,0,0,0,,他找寻自己的脚印\NHe retraces his footsteps,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.89,1:37:00.81,中英,,0,0,0,,他回到了那个大楼里\Nand he goes back to the mansion where he was.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.81,1:37:03.44,中英,,0,0,0,,但是他被告知 停止打探\NAnd he's told, you know, to stop your inquiries.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.44,1:37:05.03,中英,,0,0,0,,他们不会告诉你任何内幕的\NThey will serve you no purpose.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.03,1:37:07.90,中英,,0,0,0,,这与《闪灵》很相像\NIt's almost like it gets to that with The Shining.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.90,1:37:10.78,中英,,0,0,0,,你越是看的清楚 越是注意他们\NThe more you magnify things, the more you look at them,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.78,1:37:14.58,中英,,0,0,0,,你得到的也越少 因为它是如此的混乱\Nthe less purpose it serves 'cause it's so out of whack.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.58,1:37:17.24,中英,,0,0,0,,在开头时 这一切都没有用\NNone of it makes sense from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.24,1:37:18.71,中英,,0,0,0,,这里一定有许多\N- There must be a lot of stuff in there
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.71,1:37:21.12,中英,,0,0,0,,人们没有注意到的东西\Nthat nobody has yet seen,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.12,1:37:23.42,中英,,0,0,0,,所以人们应该一直观看它\Nso people ought to keep watching it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.09,1:37:32.88,中英,,0,0,0,,- 但是 为什么库布里克让电影这么复杂呢\N- But why would he make the movie so complicated?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.88,1:37:38.79,中英,,0,0,0,,- 我是说 为什么乔伊斯*要写《芬尼根彻夜祭》？\N - Yeah, I mean, but why did Joyce write Finnegan's Wake?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.86,1:37:38.79,注释,,0,0,0,,{\pos(638,18)}*爱尔兰意识流小说家
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.60,1:37:43.44,中英,,0,0,0,,这就像一扇开着的门\NIt's a way of, like, opening doors
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.44,1:37:45.61,中英,,0,0,0,,就像从密封的现实\Nfrom, like, a hermetically sealed reality
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.61,1:37:49.82,中英,,0,0,0,,进入了可能性\Ninto possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.82,1:37:52.54,中英,,0,0,0,,这也是困住人们 比如我 的一种方式\NAnd it's also a way of trapping someone like me.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.70,1:37:59.58,中英,,0,0,0,,困住那个想要寻找线索 并坚持下去的人\NLike, who goes looking for clues and, like, keeps finding them.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.58,1:38:02.79,中英,,0,0,0,,还有一件事情就是 我要永远被困在\NAnd next thing you know, you're like, Man, I've been...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.79,1:38:04.96,中英,,0,0,0,,这个酒店里了\NI've been trapped in this hotel forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.96,1:38:08.17,中英,,0,0,0,,这是我梦寐以求的地方\NI'm dreaming about this place.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.17,1:38:09.29,中英,,0,0,0,,我就像杰克\NYou know, I'm like Jack.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.30,1:38:11.47,中英,,0,0,0,,我就是 只工作不玩耍,聪明的孩子也变傻\NI'm, like, all work and no play.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.42,1:38:14.47,中英,,0,0,0,,或者说我只玩耍不工作\NOr the other way around.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.47,1:38:16.01,中英,,0,0,0,,这并不重要...\NIt doesn't really matter, like...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.97,1:38:19.56,中英,,0,0,0,,你就像在一个圆圈里\NYou're, like, in this loop.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.48,1:38:26.48,中英,,0,0,0,,但是你有逃出去的线路\NBut, you know, there are escape routes, like the...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.48,1:38:29.02,中英,,0,0,0,,我觉得库布里克把线路藏在了\Nlike, I think he puts escape routes
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.02,1:38:33.53,中英,,0,0,0,,那个迷宫里 地图里\Ninto it, into this maze, into this trap.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.53,1:38:35.70,中英,,0,0,0,,我是说 有很多出去的路\NI mean, there are ways out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.70,1:38:38.82,中英,,0,0,0,,丹尼通过不断的\NAnd Danny finds a way out of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.83,1:38:41.20,中英,,0,0,0,,找寻自己的脚印\Nyou know, by retracing his steps,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.20,1:38:43.08,中英,,0,0,0,,发现了其中一条\Nby going backwards and forwards.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.66,1:38:48.04,中英,,0,0,0,,而你一旦开始学习\NAnd once you start, you know, studying, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.04,1:38:51.09,中英,,0,0,0,,共时性和象征性\Nsynchronicity and symbolism,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.09,1:38:52.18,中英,,0,0,0,,突然间\Nthen, like, suddenly, like,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.18,1:38:54.01,中英,,0,0,0,,你注意到了自己的生活\Nyou're noticing in your own life,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.01,1:38:56.10,中英,,0,0,0,,事物开始跳出来\Nlike, things start popping out.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.51,1:39:01.85,中英,,0,0,0,,那些你之前没有注意到的事物\NThings that you hadn't noticed before, you know, like your...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.85,1:39:05.85,中英,,0,0,0,,那些被长期学习所改变的观点\Npoint of view is being altered by your study.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.44,1:39:12.65,中英,,0,0,0,,这就像...\NAnd, you know, it's the...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.65,1:39:14.45,中英,,0,0,0,,量子物理学\NIt's quantum physics, you know, like,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.45,1:39:17.86,中英,,0,0,0,,你的观察力 情绪\Nthe act of observing, like, affects
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.86,1:39:20.71,中英,,0,0,0,,那些被观察到的事物\Nyou know, the thing observed.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.54,1:39:24.24,中英,,0,0,0,,- 嗨 劳埃德\N- Hi, Lloyd.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.25,1:39:25.62,中英,,0,0,0,,- 是的\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.62,1:39:29.05,中英,,0,0,0,,我的意思是 这变的诡异\NYeah, I mean, it gets weird because, like, I'd... you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.05,1:39:33.67,中英,,0,0,0,,我一直被这件事困扰 我一直在家里休养\Nas I've been obsessing over this thing, you know, I've been home,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.67,1:39:37.05,中英,,0,0,0,,我失业已经有一阵子了\Nlike, I'd been out of work for a while, like...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.05,1:39:39.14,中英,,0,0,0,,我还有个儿子\NI have a small son.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.47,1:39:43.52,中英,,0,0,0,,我们打算搬到一个\NYou know, we're thinking of moving out to, like,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.52,1:39:44.81,中英,,0,0,0,,与世隔绝的地方\Nsomewhere isolated.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.81,1:39:47.56,中英,,0,0,0,,我是说 事情变的奇怪起来\NI mean, things get strange, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.56,1:39:49.39,中英,,0,0,0,,就好像...\NLike, you're...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.40,1:39:52.11,中英,,0,0,0,,就好像我的生活\Nlike, wow, my life has actually become
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.11,1:39:53.23,中英,,0,0,0,,成了《闪灵》\NThe Shining, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.30,1:40:00.30,中英,,0,0,0,,翻译 SlimChen
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.00,1:40:04.30,中英,,0,0,0,,制作 SlimChen
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.00,1:40:09.00,中英,,0,0,0,,校对 SlimChen
